606 #if defined(_DEBUG) && defined(PA_ENABLE_DEBUG_OUTPUT)
607 #define PA_WDMKS_SET_TREF
608 static PaTime tRef = 0;
609 
610 static void PaWinWdmDebugPrintf(const char* fmt, ...)
611 {
612  va_list list;
613  char buffer[1024];
614  PaTime t = PaUtil_GetTime() - tRef;
615  va_start(list, fmt);
616  _vsnprintf(buffer, 1023, fmt, list);
617  va_end(list);
618  PaUtil_DebugPrint("%6.3lf: %s", t, buffer);
619 }

624 #endif
625 #endif
626 
627 static BOOL IsDeviceTheSame(const PaWinWdmDeviceInfo* pDev1,
628  const PaWinWdmDeviceInfo* pDev2)
629 {
630  if (pDev1 == NULL || pDev2 == NULL)
631  return FALSE;
632 
633  if (pDev1 == pDev2)
634  return TRUE;
635 
636  if (strcmp(pDev1->compositeName, pDev2->compositeName) == 0)
637  return TRUE;
638 
639  return FALSE;
640 }

642 static BOOL IsEarlierThanVista()
643 {
644 /*
645 NOTE: GetVersionEx() is deprecated as of Windows 8.1 and can not be used to reliably detect
646 versions of Windows higher than Windows 8 (due to manifest requirements for reporting higher versions).
647 Microsoft recommends switching to VerifyVersionInfo (available on Win 2k and later), however GetVersionEx
648 is is faster, for now we just disable the deprecation warning.
649 See: https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms724451(v=vs.85).aspx
650 See: http://www.codeproject.com/Articles/678606/Part-Overcoming-Windows-s-deprecation-of-GetVe
651 */
652 #pragma warning (disable : 4996) /* use of GetVersionEx */
653 
654  OSVERSIONINFO osvi;
655  osvi.dwOSVersionInfoSize = sizeof(osvi);
656  if (GetVersionEx(&osvi) && osvi.dwMajorVersion<6)
657  {
658  return TRUE;
659  }
660  return FALSE;
661 
662 #pragma warning (default : 4996)
663 }

694 static void PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(long errCode, const char* fmt, ...)
695 {
696  va_list list;
697  char buffer[1024];
698  va_start(list, fmt);
699  _vsnprintf(buffer, 1023, fmt, list);
700  va_end(list);
701  PaUtil_SetLastHostErrorInfo(paWDMKS, errCode, buffer);
702 }
703 
704 /*
705 Low level pin/filter access functions
706 */
707 static PaError WdmSyncIoctl(
708  HANDLE handle,
709  unsigned long ioctlNumber,
710  void* inBuffer,
711  unsigned long inBufferCount,
712  void* outBuffer,
713  unsigned long outBufferCount,
714  unsigned long* bytesReturned)
715 {
716  PaError result = paNoError;
717  unsigned long dummyBytesReturned = 0;
718  BOOL bRes;
719 
720  if( !bytesReturned )
721  {
722  /* Use a dummy as the caller hasn't supplied one */
723  bytesReturned = &dummyBytesReturned;
724  }
725 
726  bRes = DeviceIoControl(handle, ioctlNumber, inBuffer, inBufferCount, outBuffer, outBufferCount, bytesReturned, NULL);
727  if (!bRes)
728  {
729  unsigned long error = GetLastError();
730  if ( !(((error == ERROR_INSUFFICIENT_BUFFER ) || ( error == ERROR_MORE_DATA )) &&
731  ( ioctlNumber == IOCTL_KS_PROPERTY ) &&
732  ( outBufferCount == 0 ) ) )
733  {
734  KSPROPERTY* ksProperty = (KSPROPERTY*)inBuffer;
735 
736  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "WdmSyncIoctl: DeviceIoControl GLE = 0x%08X (prop_set = {%08X-%04X-%04X-%02X%02X-%02X%02X%02X%02X%02X%02X}, prop_id = %u)",
737  error,
738  ksProperty->Set.Data1, ksProperty->Set.Data2, ksProperty->Set.Data3,
739  ksProperty->Set.Data4[0], ksProperty->Set.Data4[1],
740  ksProperty->Set.Data4[2], ksProperty->Set.Data4[3],
741  ksProperty->Set.Data4[4], ksProperty->Set.Data4[5],
742  ksProperty->Set.Data4[6], ksProperty->Set.Data4[7],
743  ksProperty->Id
744  );
745  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
746  }
747  }
748  return result;
749 }

751 static PaError WdmGetPropertySimple(HANDLE handle,
752  const GUID* const guidPropertySet,
753  unsigned long property,
754  void* value,
755  unsigned long valueCount)
756 {
757  PaError result;
758  KSPROPERTY ksProperty;
759 
760  ksProperty.Set = *guidPropertySet;
761  ksProperty.Id = property;
762  ksProperty.Flags = KSPROPERTY_TYPE_GET;
763 
764  result = WdmSyncIoctl(
765  handle,
766  IOCTL_KS_PROPERTY,
767  &ksProperty,
768  sizeof(KSPROPERTY),
769  value,
770  valueCount,
771  NULL);
772 
773  return result;
774 }

776 static PaError WdmSetPropertySimple(
777  HANDLE handle,
778  const GUID* const guidPropertySet,
779  unsigned long property,
780  void* value,
781  unsigned long valueCount,
782  void* instance,
783  unsigned long instanceCount)
784 {
785  PaError result;
786  KSPROPERTY* ksProperty;
787  unsigned long propertyCount = 0;
788 
789  propertyCount = sizeof(KSPROPERTY) + instanceCount;
790  ksProperty = (KSPROPERTY*)_alloca( propertyCount );
791  if( !ksProperty )
792  {
793  return paInsufficientMemory;
794  }
795 
796  ksProperty->Set = *guidPropertySet;
797  ksProperty->Id = property;
798  ksProperty->Flags = KSPROPERTY_TYPE_SET;
799 
800  if( instance )
801  {
802  memcpy((void*)((char*)ksProperty + sizeof(KSPROPERTY)), instance, instanceCount);
803  }
804 
805  result = WdmSyncIoctl(
806  handle,
807  IOCTL_KS_PROPERTY,
808  ksProperty,
809  propertyCount,
810  value,
811  valueCount,
812  NULL);
813 
814  return result;
815 }

847 static PaError WdmGetPinPropertyMulti(

850  const GUID* const guidPropertySet,
851  unsigned long property,
852  KSMULTIPLE_ITEM** ksMultipleItem)
853 {

857 
858  ksPProp.Property.Set = *guidPropertySet;
859  ksPProp.Property.Id = property;
860  ksPProp.Property.Flags = KSPROPERTY_TYPE_GET;
861  ksPProp.PinId = pinId;

890  NULL);

895  }

966 /* Used when traversing topology for outputs */
967 static const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* GetConnectionTo(const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* pFrom, PaWinWdmFilter* filter, int muxIdx)
968 {
969  unsigned i;
970  const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* retval = NULL;
971  const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* connections = (const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION*)(filter->connections + 1);
972  (void)muxIdx;
973  PA_DEBUG(("GetConnectionTo: Checking %u connections... (pFrom = %p)", filter->connections->Count, pFrom));
974  for (i = 0; i < filter->connections->Count; ++i)
975  {
976  const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* pConn = connections + i;
977  if (pConn == pFrom)
978  continue;
979 
980  if (pConn->FromNode == pFrom->ToNode)
981  {
982  retval = pConn;
983  break;
984  }
985  }
986  PA_DEBUG(("GetConnectionTo: Returning %p\n", retval));
987  return retval;
988 }
989 
990 /* Used when traversing topology for inputs */
991 static const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* GetConnectionFrom(const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* pTo, PaWinWdmFilter* filter, int muxIdx)
992 {
993  unsigned i;
994  const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* retval = NULL;
995  const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* connections = (const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION*)(filter->connections + 1);
996  int muxCntr = 0;
997  PA_DEBUG(("GetConnectionFrom: Checking %u connections... (pTo = %p)\n", filter->connections->Count, pTo));
998  for (i = 0; i < filter->connections->Count; ++i)
999  {
1000  const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* pConn = connections + i;
1001  if (pConn == pTo)
1002  continue;
1003 
1004  if (pConn->ToNode == pTo->FromNode)
1005  {
1006  if (muxIdx >= 0)
1007  {
1008  if (muxCntr < muxIdx)
1009  {
1010  ++muxCntr;
1011  continue;
1012  }
1013  }
1014  retval = pConn;
1015  break;
1016  }
1017  }
1018  PA_DEBUG(("GetConnectionFrom: Returning %p\n", retval));
1019  return retval;
1020 }
1021 
1022 static ULONG GetNumberOfConnectionsTo(const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* pTo, PaWinWdmFilter* filter)
1023 {
1024  ULONG retval = 0;
1025  unsigned i;
1026  const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* connections = (const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION*)(filter->connections + 1);
1027  PA_DEBUG(("GetNumberOfConnectionsTo: Checking %u connections...\n", filter->connections->Count));
1028  for (i = 0; i < filter->connections->Count; ++i)
1029  {
1030  const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* pConn = connections + i;
1031  if (pConn->ToNode == pTo->FromNode &&
1032  (pTo->FromNode != KSFILTER_NODE || pConn->ToNodePin == pTo->FromNodePin))
1033  {
1034  ++retval;
1035  }
1036  }
1037  PA_DEBUG(("GetNumberOfConnectionsTo: Returning %d\n", retval));
1038  return retval;
1039 }

1041 typedef const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION *(*TFnGetConnection)(const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION*, PaWinWdmFilter*, int);
1042 
1043 static const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* FindStartConnectionFrom(ULONG startPin, PaWinWdmFilter* filter)
1044 {
1045  unsigned i;
1046  const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* connections = (const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION*)(filter->connections + 1);
1047  PA_DEBUG(("FindStartConnectionFrom: Startpin %u, Checking %u connections...\n", startPin, filter->connections->Count));
1048  for (i = 0; i < filter->connections->Count; ++i)
1049  {
1050  const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* pConn = connections + i;
1051  if (pConn->ToNode == KSFILTER_NODE && pConn->ToNodePin == startPin)
1052  {
1053  PA_DEBUG(("FindStartConnectionFrom: returning %p\n", pConn));
1054  return pConn;
1055  }
1056  }
1057 
1058  PA_DEBUG(("FindStartConnectionFrom: returning NULL\n"));
1059  assert(FALSE);
1060  return 0;
1061 }

1063 static const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* FindStartConnectionTo(ULONG startPin, PaWinWdmFilter* filter)
1064 {
1065  unsigned i;
1066  const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* connections = (const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION*)(filter->connections + 1);
1067  PA_DEBUG(("FindStartConnectionTo: Startpin %u, Checking %u connections...\n", startPin, filter->connections->Count));
1068  for (i = 0; i < filter->connections->Count; ++i)
1069  {
1070  const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* pConn = connections + i;
1071  if (pConn->FromNode == KSFILTER_NODE && pConn->FromNodePin == startPin)
1072  {
1073  PA_DEBUG(("FindStartConnectionTo: returning %p\n", pConn));
1074  return pConn;
1075  }
1076  }
1077 
1078  PA_DEBUG(("FindStartConnectionTo: returning NULL\n"));
1079  assert(FALSE);
1080  return 0;
1081 }

1083 static ULONG GetConnectedPin(ULONG startPin, BOOL forward, PaWinWdmFilter* filter, int muxPosition, ULONG *muxInputPinId, ULONG *muxNodeId)
1084 {
1085  int limit=1000;
1086  const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION *conn = NULL;
1087  TFnGetConnection fnGetConnection = forward ? GetConnectionTo : GetConnectionFrom ;
1088  PA_LOGE_;
1089  while (1)
1090  {
1091  limit--;
1092  if (limit == 0) {
1093  PA_DEBUG(("GetConnectedPin: LOOP LIMIT REACHED\n"));
1094  break;
1095  }
1096 
1097  if (conn == NULL)
1098  {
1099  conn = forward ? FindStartConnectionTo(startPin, filter) : FindStartConnectionFrom(startPin, filter);
1100  }
1101  else
1102  {
1103  conn = fnGetConnection(conn, filter, -1);
1104  }
1105 
1106  /* Handling case of erroneous connection list */
1107  if (conn == NULL)
1108  {
1109  break;
1110  }
1111 
1112  if (forward ? conn->ToNode == KSFILTER_NODE : conn->FromNode == KSFILTER_NODE)
1113  {
1114  return forward ? conn->ToNodePin : conn->FromNodePin;
1115  }
1116  else
1117  {
1118  PA_DEBUG(("GetConnectedPin: count=%d, forward=%d, muxPosition=%d\n", filter->nodes->Count, forward, muxPosition));
1119  if (filter->nodes->Count > 0 && !forward && muxPosition >= 0)
1120  {
1121  const GUID* nodes = (const GUID*)(filter->nodes + 1);
1122  if (IsEqualGUID(&nodes[conn->FromNode], &KSNODETYPE_MUX))
1123  {
1124  ULONG nConn = GetNumberOfConnectionsTo(conn, filter);
1125  conn = fnGetConnection(conn, filter, muxPosition);
1126  if (conn == NULL)
1127  {
1128  break;
1129  }
1130  if (muxInputPinId != 0)
1131  {
1132  *muxInputPinId = conn->ToNodePin;
1133  }
1134  if (muxNodeId != 0)
1135  {
1136  *muxNodeId = conn->ToNode;
1137  }
1138  }
1139  }
1140  }
1141  }
1142  PA_LOGL_;
1143  return KSFILTER_NODE;
1144 }
1145 
1146 static void DumpConnectionsAndNodes(PaWinWdmFilter* filter)
1147 {
1148  unsigned i;
1149  const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* connections = (const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION*)(filter->connections + 1);
1150  const GUID* nodes = (const GUID*)(filter->nodes + 1);
1151 
1152  PA_LOGE_;
1153  PA_DEBUG(("DumpConnectionsAndNodes: connections=%d, nodes=%d\n", filter->connections->Count, filter->nodes->Count));
1154 
1155  for (i=0; i < filter->connections->Count; ++i)
1156  {
1157  const KSTOPOLOGY_CONNECTION* pConn = connections + i;
1158  PA_DEBUG((" Connection: %u - FromNode=%u,FromPin=%u -> ToNode=%u,ToPin=%u\n",
1159  i,
1160  pConn->FromNode, pConn->FromNodePin,
1161  pConn->ToNode, pConn->ToNodePin
1162  ));
1163  }
1164 
1165  for (i=0; i < filter->nodes->Count; ++i)
1166  {
1167  const GUID* pConn = nodes + i;
1168  PA_DEBUG((" Node: %d - {%08X-%04X-%04X-%02X%02X-%02X%02X%02X%02X%02X%02X}\n",
1169  i,
1170  pConn->Data1, pConn->Data2, pConn->Data3,
1171  pConn->Data4[0], pConn->Data4[1],
1172  pConn->Data4[2], pConn->Data4[3],
1173  pConn->Data4[4], pConn->Data4[5],
1174  pConn->Data4[6], pConn->Data4[7]
1175  ));
1176  }
1177  PA_LOGL_;
1178 
1179 }

1181 typedef struct __PaUsbTerminalGUIDToName
1182 {
1183  USHORT usbGUID;
1184  wchar_t name[64];
1185 } PaUsbTerminalGUIDToName;
1186 
1187 static const PaUsbTerminalGUIDToName kNames[] =
1188 {
1189  /* Types copied from: http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ff537742(v=vs.85).aspx */
1190  /* Input terminal types */
1191  { 0x0201, L"Microphone" },
1192  { 0x0202, L"Desktop Microphone" },
1193  { 0x0203, L"Personal Microphone" },
1194  { 0x0204, L"Omni Directional Microphone" },
1195  { 0x0205, L"Microphone Array" },
1196  { 0x0206, L"Processing Microphone Array" },
1197  /* Output terminal types */
1198  { 0x0301, L"Speakers" },
1199  { 0x0302, L"Headphones" },
1200  { 0x0303, L"Head Mounted Display Audio" },
1201  { 0x0304, L"Desktop Speaker" },
1202  { 0x0305, L"Room Speaker" },
1203  { 0x0306, L"Communication Speaker" },
1204  { 0x0307, L"LFE Speakers" },
1205  /* External terminal types */
1206  { 0x0601, L"Analog" },
1207  { 0x0602, L"Digital" },
1208  { 0x0603, L"Line" },
1209  { 0x0604, L"Audio" },
1210  { 0x0605, L"SPDIF" },
1211 };
1212 
1213 static const unsigned kNamesCnt = sizeof(kNames)/sizeof(PaUsbTerminalGUIDToName);
1214 
1215 static int PaUsbTerminalGUIDToNameCmp(const void* lhs, const void* rhs)
1216 {
1217  const PaUsbTerminalGUIDToName* pL = (const PaUsbTerminalGUIDToName*)lhs;
1218  const PaUsbTerminalGUIDToName* pR = (const PaUsbTerminalGUIDToName*)rhs;
1219  return ((int)(pL->usbGUID) - (int)(pR->usbGUID));
1220 }
1221 
1222 static PaError GetNameFromCategory(const GUID* pGUID, BOOL input, wchar_t* name, unsigned length)
1223 {
1224  PaError result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
1225  USHORT usbTerminalGUID = (USHORT)(pGUID->Data1 - 0xDFF219E0);
1226 
1227  PA_LOGE_;
1228  if (input && usbTerminalGUID >= 0x301 && usbTerminalGUID < 0x400)
1229  {
1230  /* Output terminal name for an input !? Set it to Line! */
1231  usbTerminalGUID = 0x603;
1232  }
1233  if (!input && usbTerminalGUID >= 0x201 && usbTerminalGUID < 0x300)
1234  {
1235  /* Input terminal name for an output !? Set it to Line! */
1236  usbTerminalGUID = 0x603;
1237  }
1238  if (usbTerminalGUID >= 0x201 && usbTerminalGUID < 0x713)
1239  {
1240  PaUsbTerminalGUIDToName s = { usbTerminalGUID };
1241  const PaUsbTerminalGUIDToName* ptr = bsearch(
1242  &s,
1243  kNames,
1244  kNamesCnt,
1245  sizeof(PaUsbTerminalGUIDToName),
1246  PaUsbTerminalGUIDToNameCmp
1247  );
1248  if (ptr != 0)
1249  {
1250  PA_DEBUG(("GetNameFromCategory: USB GUID %04X -> '%S'\n", usbTerminalGUID, ptr->name));
1251 
1252  if (name != NULL && length > 0)
1253  {
1254  int n = _snwprintf(name, length, L"%s", ptr->name);
1255  if (usbTerminalGUID >= 0x601 && usbTerminalGUID < 0x700)
1256  {
1257  _snwprintf(name + n, length - n, L" %s", (input ? L"In":L"Out"));
1258  }
1259  }
1260  result = paNoError;
1261  }
1262  }
1263  else
1264  {
1265  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "GetNameFromCategory: usbTerminalGUID = %04X ", usbTerminalGUID);
1266  }
1267  PA_LOGL_;
1268  return result;
1269 }
1270 
1271 static BOOL IsFrequencyWithinRange(const KSDATARANGE_AUDIO* range, int frequency)
1272 {
1273  if (frequency < (int)range->MinimumSampleFrequency)
1274  return FALSE;
1275  if (frequency > (int)range->MaximumSampleFrequency)
1276  return FALSE;
1277  return TRUE;
1278 }
1279 
1280 static BOOL IsBitsWithinRange(const KSDATARANGE_AUDIO* range, int noOfBits)
1281 {
1282  if (noOfBits < (int)range->MinimumBitsPerSample)
1283  return FALSE;
1284  if (noOfBits > (int)range->MaximumBitsPerSample)
1285  return FALSE;
1286  return TRUE;
1287 }
1288 
1289 /* Note: Somewhat different order compared to WMME implementation, as we want to focus on fidelity first */
1290 static const int defaultSampleRateSearchOrder[] =
1291 { 44100, 48000, 88200, 96000, 192000, 32000, 24000, 22050, 16000, 12000, 11025, 9600, 8000 };
1292 static const int defaultSampleRateSearchOrderCount = sizeof(defaultSampleRateSearchOrder)/sizeof(defaultSampleRateSearchOrder[0]);
1293 
1294 static int DefaultSampleFrequencyIndex(const KSDATARANGE_AUDIO* range)
1295 {
1296  int i;
1297 
1298  for(i=0; i < defaultSampleRateSearchOrderCount; ++i)
1299  {
1300  int currentFrequency = defaultSampleRateSearchOrder[i];
1301 
1302  if (IsFrequencyWithinRange(range, currentFrequency))
1303  {
1304  return i;
1305  }
1306  }
1307 
1308  return -1;
1309 }
1310 
1311 /*
1312 Create a new pin object belonging to a filter
1313 The pin object holds all the configuration information about the pin
1314 before it is opened, and then the handle of the pin after is opened
1315 */
1316 static PaWinWdmPin* PinNew(PaWinWdmFilter* parentFilter, unsigned long pinId, PaError* error)
1317 {
1318  PaWinWdmPin* pin;
1319  PaError result;
1320  unsigned long i;
1321  KSMULTIPLE_ITEM* item = NULL;
1322  KSIDENTIFIER* identifier;
1323  KSDATARANGE* dataRange;
1324  const ULONG streamingId = (parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType == Type_kWaveRT) ? KSINTERFACE_STANDARD_LOOPED_STREAMING : KSINTERFACE_STANDARD_STREAMING;
1325  int defaultSampleRateIndex = defaultSampleRateSearchOrderCount;
1326 
1327  PA_LOGE_;
1328  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Creating pin %d:\n",pinId));
1329 
1330  /* Allocate the new PIN object */
1331  pin = (PaWinWdmPin*)PaUtil_AllocateMemory( sizeof(PaWinWdmPin) );
1332  if( !pin )
1333  {
1334  result = paInsufficientMemory;
1335  goto error;
1336  }
1337 
1338  /* Zero the pin object */
1339  /* memset( (void*)pin, 0, sizeof(PaWinWdmPin) ); */
1340 
1341  pin->parentFilter = parentFilter;
1342  pin->pinId = pinId;
1343 
1344  /* Allocate a connect structure */
1345  pin->pinConnectSize = sizeof(KSPIN_CONNECT) + sizeof(KSDATAFORMAT_WAVEFORMATEX);
1346  pin->pinConnect = (KSPIN_CONNECT*)PaUtil_AllocateMemory( pin->pinConnectSize );
1347  if( !pin->pinConnect )
1348  {
1349  result = paInsufficientMemory;
1350  goto error;
1351  }
1352 
1353  /* Configure the connect structure with default values */
1354  pin->pinConnect->Interface.Set = KSINTERFACESETID_Standard;
1355  pin->pinConnect->Interface.Id = streamingId;
1356  pin->pinConnect->Interface.Flags = 0;
1357  pin->pinConnect->Medium.Set = KSMEDIUMSETID_Standard;
1358  pin->pinConnect->Medium.Id = KSMEDIUM_TYPE_ANYINSTANCE;
1359  pin->pinConnect->Medium.Flags = 0;
1360  pin->pinConnect->PinId = pinId;
1361  pin->pinConnect->PinToHandle = NULL;
1362  pin->pinConnect->Priority.PriorityClass = KSPRIORITY_NORMAL;
1363  pin->pinConnect->Priority.PrioritySubClass = 1;
1364  pin->ksDataFormatWfx = (KSDATAFORMAT_WAVEFORMATEX*)(pin->pinConnect + 1);
1365  pin->ksDataFormatWfx->DataFormat.FormatSize = sizeof(KSDATAFORMAT_WAVEFORMATEX);
1366  pin->ksDataFormatWfx->DataFormat.Flags = 0;
1367  pin->ksDataFormatWfx->DataFormat.Reserved = 0;
1368  pin->ksDataFormatWfx->DataFormat.MajorFormat = KSDATAFORMAT_TYPE_AUDIO;
1369  pin->ksDataFormatWfx->DataFormat.SubFormat = KSDATAFORMAT_SUBTYPE_PCM;
1370  pin->ksDataFormatWfx->DataFormat.Specifier = KSDATAFORMAT_SPECIFIER_WAVEFORMATEX;
1371 
1372  pin->frameSize = 0; /* Unknown until we instantiate pin */
1373 
1374  /* Get the COMMUNICATION property */
1375  result = WdmGetPinPropertySimple(
1376  parentFilter->handle,
1377  pinId,
1378  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1379  KSPROPERTY_PIN_COMMUNICATION,
1380  &pin->communication,
1381  sizeof(KSPIN_COMMUNICATION),
1382  NULL);
1383  if( result != paNoError )
1384  goto error;
1385 
1386  if( /*(pin->communication != KSPIN_COMMUNICATION_SOURCE) &&*/
1387  (pin->communication != KSPIN_COMMUNICATION_SINK) &&
1388  (pin->communication != KSPIN_COMMUNICATION_BOTH) )
1389  {
1390  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Not source/sink\n"));
1391  result = paInvalidDevice;
1392  goto error;
1393  }
1394 
1395  /* Get dataflow information */
1396  result = WdmGetPinPropertySimple(
1397  parentFilter->handle,
1398  pinId,
1399  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1400  KSPROPERTY_PIN_DATAFLOW,
1401  &pin->dataFlow,
1402  sizeof(KSPIN_DATAFLOW),
1403  NULL);
1404 
1405  if( result != paNoError )
1406  goto error;
1407 
1408  /* Get the INTERFACE property list */
1409  result = WdmGetPinPropertyMulti(
1410  parentFilter->handle,
1411  pinId,
1412  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1413  KSPROPERTY_PIN_INTERFACES,
1414  &item);
1415 
1416  if( result != paNoError )
1417  goto error;
1418 
1419  identifier = (KSIDENTIFIER*)(item+1);
1420 
1421  /* Check that at least one interface is STANDARD_STREAMING */
1422  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
1423  for( i = 0; i < item->Count; i++ )
1424  {
1425  if( IsEqualGUID(&identifier[i].Set, &KSINTERFACESETID_Standard) && ( identifier[i].Id == streamingId ) )
1426  {
1427  result = paNoError;
1428  break;
1429  }
1430  }
1431 
1432  if( result != paNoError )
1433  {
1434  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: No %s streaming\n", streamingId==KSINTERFACE_STANDARD_LOOPED_STREAMING?"looped":"standard"));
1435  goto error;
1436  }
1437 
1438  /* Don't need interfaces any more */
1439  PaUtil_FreeMemory( item );
1440  item = NULL;
1441 
1442  /* Get the MEDIUM properties list */
1443  result = WdmGetPinPropertyMulti(
1444  parentFilter->handle,
1445  pinId,
1446  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1447  KSPROPERTY_PIN_MEDIUMS,
1448  &item);
1449 
1450  if( result != paNoError )
1451  goto error;
1452 
1453  identifier = (KSIDENTIFIER*)(item+1); /* Not actually necessary... */
1454 
1455  /* Check that at least one medium is STANDARD_DEVIO */
1456  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
1457  for( i = 0; i < item->Count; i++ )
1458  {
1459  if( IsEqualGUID(&identifier[i].Set, &KSMEDIUMSETID_Standard) && ( identifier[i].Id == KSMEDIUM_STANDARD_DEVIO ) )
1460  {
1461  result = paNoError;
1462  break;
1463  }
1464  }
1465 
1466  if( result != paNoError )
1467  {
1468  PA_DEBUG(("No standard devio\n"));
1469  goto error;
1470  }
1471  /* Don't need mediums any more */
1472  PaUtil_FreeMemory( item );
1473  item = NULL;
1474 
1475  /* Get DATARANGES */
1476  result = WdmGetPinPropertyMulti(
1477  parentFilter->handle,
1478  pinId,
1479  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1480  KSPROPERTY_PIN_DATARANGES,
1481  &pin->dataRangesItem);
1482 
1483  if( result != paNoError )
1484  goto error;
1485 
1486  pin->dataRanges = (KSDATARANGE*)(pin->dataRangesItem +1);
1487 
1488  /* Check that at least one datarange supports audio */
1489  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
1490  dataRange = pin->dataRanges;
1491  pin->maxChannels = 0;
1492  pin->defaultSampleRate = 0;
1493  pin->formats = 0;
1494  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Checking %u no of dataranges...\n", pin->dataRangesItem->Count));
1495  for( i = 0; i < pin->dataRangesItem->Count; i++)
1496  {
1497  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: DR major format %x\n",*(unsigned long*)(&(dataRange->MajorFormat))));
1498  /* Check that subformat is WAVEFORMATEX, PCM or WILDCARD */
1499  if( IS_VALID_WAVEFORMATEX_GUID(&dataRange->SubFormat) ||
1500  IsEqualGUID(&dataRange->SubFormat, &KSDATAFORMAT_SUBTYPE_PCM) ||
1501  IsEqualGUID(&dataRange->SubFormat, &KSDATAFORMAT_SUBTYPE_IEEE_FLOAT) ||
1502  IsEqualGUID(&dataRange->SubFormat, &KSDATAFORMAT_SUBTYPE_WILDCARD) ||
1503  IsEqualGUID(&dataRange->MajorFormat, &KSDATAFORMAT_TYPE_AUDIO) )
1504  {
1505  int defaultIndex;
1506  result = paNoError;
1507  /* Record the maximum possible channels with this pin */
1508  if( ((KSDATARANGE_AUDIO*)dataRange)->MaximumChannels == (ULONG) -1 )
1509  {
1510  pin->maxChannels = MAXIMUM_NUMBER_OF_CHANNELS;
1511  }
1512  else if( (int) ((KSDATARANGE_AUDIO*)dataRange)->MaximumChannels > pin->maxChannels )
1513  {
1514  pin->maxChannels = (int) ((KSDATARANGE_AUDIO*)dataRange)->MaximumChannels;
1515  }
1516  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: MaxChannel: %d\n",pin->maxChannels));
1517 
1518  /* Record the formats (bit depths) that are supported */
1519  if( IsBitsWithinRange((KSDATARANGE_AUDIO*)dataRange, 8) )
1520  {
1521  pin->formats |= paInt8;
1522  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Format PCM 8 bit supported\n"));
1523  }
1524  if( IsBitsWithinRange((KSDATARANGE_AUDIO*)dataRange, 16) )
1525  {
1526  pin->formats |= paInt16;
1527  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Format PCM 16 bit supported\n"));
1528  }
1529  if( IsBitsWithinRange((KSDATARANGE_AUDIO*)dataRange, 24) )
1530  {
1531  pin->formats |= paInt24;
1532  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Format PCM 24 bit supported\n"));
1533  }
1534  if( IsBitsWithinRange((KSDATARANGE_AUDIO*)dataRange, 32) )
1535  {
1536  if (IsEqualGUID(&dataRange->SubFormat, &KSDATAFORMAT_SUBTYPE_IEEE_FLOAT))
1537  {
1538  pin->formats |= paFloat32;
1539  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Format IEEE float 32 bit supported\n"));
1540  }
1541  else
1542  {
1543  pin->formats |= paInt32;
1544  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Format PCM 32 bit supported\n"));
1545  }
1546  }
1547 
1548  defaultIndex = DefaultSampleFrequencyIndex((KSDATARANGE_AUDIO*)dataRange);
1549  if (defaultIndex >= 0 && defaultIndex < defaultSampleRateIndex)
1550  {
1551  defaultSampleRateIndex = defaultIndex;
1552  }
1553  }
1554  dataRange = (KSDATARANGE*)( ((char*)dataRange) + dataRange->FormatSize);
1555  }
1556 
1557  if( result != paNoError )
1558  goto error;
1559 
1560  /* If none of the frequencies searched for are present, there's something seriously wrong */
1561  if (defaultSampleRateIndex == defaultSampleRateSearchOrderCount)
1562  {
1563  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: No default sample rate found, skipping pin!\n"));
1564  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paUnanticipatedHostError, "PinNew: No default sample rate found");
1565  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
1566  goto error;
1567  }
1568 
1569  /* Set the default sample rate */
1570  pin->defaultSampleRate = defaultSampleRateSearchOrder[defaultSampleRateIndex];
1571  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Default sample rate = %d Hz\n", pin->defaultSampleRate));
1572 
1573  /* Get instance information */
1574  result = WdmGetPinPropertySimple(
1575  parentFilter->handle,
1576  pinId,
1577  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1578  KSPROPERTY_PIN_CINSTANCES,
1579  &pin->instances,
1580  sizeof(KSPIN_CINSTANCES),
1581  NULL);
1582 
1583  if( result != paNoError )
1584  goto error;
1585 
1586  /* If WaveRT, check if pin supports notification mode */
1587  if (parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType == Type_kWaveRT)
1588  {
1589  BOOL bSupportsNotification = FALSE;
1590  if (PinQueryNotificationSupport(pin, &bSupportsNotification) == paNoError)
1591  {
1592  pin->pinKsSubType = bSupportsNotification ? SubType_kNotification : SubType_kPolled;
1593  }
1594  }
1595 
1596  /* Query pin name (which means we need to traverse to non IRP pin, via physical connection to topology filter pin, through
1597  its nodes to the endpoint pin, and get that ones name... phew...) */
1598  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Finding topology pin...\n"));
1599 
1600  {
1601  ULONG topoPinId = GetConnectedPin(pinId, (pin->dataFlow == KSPIN_DATAFLOW_IN), parentFilter, -1, NULL, NULL);
1602  const wchar_t kInputName[] = L"Input";
1603  const wchar_t kOutputName[] = L"Output";
1604 
1605  if (topoPinId != KSFILTER_NODE)
1606  {
1607  /* Get physical connection for topo pin */
1608  unsigned long cbBytes = 0;
1609  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Getting physical connection...\n"));
1610  result = WdmGetPinPropertySimple(parentFilter->handle,
1611  topoPinId,
1612  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1613  KSPROPERTY_PIN_PHYSICALCONNECTION,
1614  0,
1615  0,
1616  &cbBytes
1617  );
1618 
1619  if (result != paNoError)
1620  {
1621  /* No physical connection -> there is no topology filter! So we get the name of the pin! */
1622  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: No physical connection! Getting the pin name\n"));
1623  result = WdmGetPinPropertySimple(parentFilter->handle,
1624  topoPinId,
1625  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1626  KSPROPERTY_PIN_NAME,
1627  pin->friendlyName,
1628  MAX_PATH,
1629  NULL);
1630  if (result != paNoError)
1631  {
1632  GUID category = {0};
1633 
1634  /* Get pin category information */
1635  result = WdmGetPinPropertySimple(parentFilter->handle,
1636  topoPinId,
1637  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1638  KSPROPERTY_PIN_CATEGORY,
1639  &category,
1640  sizeof(GUID),
1641  NULL);
1642 
1643  if (result == paNoError)
1644  {
1645  result = GetNameFromCategory(&category, (pin->dataFlow == KSPIN_DATAFLOW_OUT), pin->friendlyName, MAX_PATH);
1646  }
1647  }
1648 
1649  /* Make sure pin gets a name here... */
1650  if (wcslen(pin->friendlyName) == 0)
1651  {
1652  wcscpy(pin->friendlyName, (pin->dataFlow == KSPIN_DATAFLOW_IN) ? kOutputName : kInputName);
1653 #ifdef UNICODE
1654  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Setting pin friendly name to '%s'\n", pin->friendlyName));
1655 #else
1656  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Setting pin friendly name to '%S'\n", pin->friendlyName));
1657 #endif
1658  }
1659 
1660  /* This is then == the endpoint pin */
1661  pin->endpointPinId = (pin->dataFlow == KSPIN_DATAFLOW_IN) ? pinId : topoPinId;
1662  }
1663  else
1664  {
1665  KSPIN_PHYSICALCONNECTION* pc = (KSPIN_PHYSICALCONNECTION*)PaUtil_AllocateMemory(cbBytes + 2);
1666  ULONG pcPin;
1667  wchar_t symbLinkName[MAX_PATH];
1668  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Physical connection found!\n"));
1669  if (pc == NULL)
1670  {
1671  result = paInsufficientMemory;
1672  goto error;
1673  }
1674  result = WdmGetPinPropertySimple(parentFilter->handle,
1675  topoPinId,
1676  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1677  KSPROPERTY_PIN_PHYSICALCONNECTION,
1678  pc,
1679  cbBytes,
1680  NULL
1681  );
1682 
1683  pcPin = pc->Pin;
1684  wcsncpy(symbLinkName, pc->SymbolicLinkName, MAX_PATH);
1685  PaUtil_FreeMemory( pc );
1686 
1687  if (result != paNoError)
1688  {
1689  /* Shouldn't happen, but fail if it does */
1690  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: failed to retrieve physical connection!\n"));
1691  goto error;
1692  }
1693 
1694  if (symbLinkName[1] == TEXT('?'))
1695  {
1696  symbLinkName[1] = TEXT('\\');
1697  }
1698 
1699  if (pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter == NULL)
1700  {
1701  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Creating topology filter '%S'\n", symbLinkName));
1702 
1703  pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter = FilterNew(Type_kNotUsed, 0, symbLinkName, L"", &result);
1704  if (pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter == NULL)
1705  {
1706  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Failed creating topology filter\n"));
1707  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
1708  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "Failed to create topology filter '%S'", symbLinkName);
1709  goto error;
1710  }
1711 
1712  /* Copy info so we have it in device info */
1713  wcsncpy(pin->parentFilter->devInfo.topologyPath, symbLinkName, MAX_PATH);
1714  }
1715  else
1716  {
1717  /* Must be the same */
1718  assert(wcscmp(symbLinkName, pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter->devInfo.filterPath) == 0);
1719  }
1720 
1721  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Opening topology filter..."));
1722 
1723  result = FilterUse(pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter);
1724  if (result == paNoError)
1725  {
1726  unsigned long endpointPinId;
1727 
1728  if (pin->dataFlow == KSPIN_DATAFLOW_IN)
1729  {
1730  /* The "endpointPinId" is what WASAPI looks at for pin names */
1731  GUID category = {0};
1732 
1733  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Checking for output endpoint pin id...\n"));
1734 
1735  endpointPinId = GetConnectedPin(pcPin, TRUE, pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter, -1, NULL, NULL);
1736 
1737  if (endpointPinId == KSFILTER_NODE)
1738  {
1739  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
1740  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "Failed to get endpoint pin ID on topology filter!");
1741  goto error;
1742  }
1743 
1744  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Found endpoint pin id %u\n", endpointPinId));
1745 
1746  /* Get pin category information */
1747  result = WdmGetPinPropertySimple(pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter->handle,
1748  endpointPinId,
1749  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1750  KSPROPERTY_PIN_CATEGORY,
1751  &category,
1752  sizeof(GUID),
1753  NULL);
1754 
1755  if (result == paNoError)
1756  {
1757 #if !PA_WDMKS_USE_CATEGORY_FOR_PIN_NAMES
1758  wchar_t pinName[MAX_PATH];
1759 
1760  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Getting pin name property..."));
1761 
1762  /* Ok, try pin name also, and favor that if available */
1763  result = WdmGetPinPropertySimple(pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter->handle,
1764  endpointPinId,
1765  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1766  KSPROPERTY_PIN_NAME,
1767  pinName,
1768  MAX_PATH,
1769  NULL);
1770 
1771  if (result == paNoError && wcslen(pinName)>0)
1772  {
1773  wcsncpy(pin->friendlyName, pinName, MAX_PATH);
1774  }
1775  else
1776 #endif
1777  {
1778  result = GetNameFromCategory(&category, (pin->dataFlow == KSPIN_DATAFLOW_OUT), pin->friendlyName, MAX_PATH);
1779  }
1780  }
1781 
1782  /* Make sure we get a name for the pin */
1783  if (wcslen(pin->friendlyName) == 0)
1784  {
1785  wcscpy(pin->friendlyName, kOutputName);
1786  }
1787 #ifdef UNICODE
1788  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Pin name '%s'\n", pin->friendlyName));
1789 #else
1790  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Pin name '%S'\n", pin->friendlyName));
1791 #endif
1792 
1793  /* Set endpoint pin ID (this is the topology INPUT pin, since portmixer will always traverse the
1794  filter in audio streaming direction, see http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/hardware/ff536331(v=vs.85).aspx
1795  for more information)
1796  */
1797  pin->endpointPinId = pcPin;
1798  }
1799  else
1800  {
1801  unsigned muxCount = 0;
1802  int muxPos = 0;
1803  /* Max 64 multiplexer inputs... sanity check :) */
1804  for (i = 0; i < 64; ++i)
1805  {
1806  ULONG muxNodeIdTest = (unsigned)-1;
1807  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Checking for input endpoint pin id (%d)...\n", i));
1808 
1809  endpointPinId = GetConnectedPin(pcPin,
1810  FALSE,
1811  pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter,
1812  (int)i,
1813  NULL,
1814  &muxNodeIdTest);
1815 
1816  if (endpointPinId == KSFILTER_NODE)
1817  {
1818  /* We're done */
1819  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Done with inputs.\n", endpointPinId));
1820  break;
1821  }
1822  else
1823  {
1824  /* The "endpointPinId" is what WASAPI looks at for pin names */
1825  GUID category = {0};
1826 
1827  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Found endpoint pin id %u\n", endpointPinId));
1828 
1829  /* Get pin category information */
1830  result = WdmGetPinPropertySimple(pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter->handle,
1831  endpointPinId,
1832  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1833  KSPROPERTY_PIN_CATEGORY,
1834  &category,
1835  sizeof(GUID),
1836  NULL);
1837 
1838  if (result == paNoError)
1839  {
1840  if (muxNodeIdTest == (unsigned)-1)
1841  {
1842  /* Ok, try pin name, and favor that if available */
1843  result = WdmGetPinPropertySimple(pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter->handle,
1844  endpointPinId,
1845  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1846  KSPROPERTY_PIN_NAME,
1847  pin->friendlyName,
1848  MAX_PATH,
1849  NULL);
1850 
1851  if (result != paNoError)
1852  {
1853  result = GetNameFromCategory(&category, TRUE, pin->friendlyName, MAX_PATH);
1854  }
1855  break;
1856  }
1857  else
1858  {
1859  result = GetNameFromCategory(&category, TRUE, NULL, 0);
1860 
1861  if (result == paNoError)
1862  {
1863  ++muxCount;
1864  }
1865  }
1866  }
1867  else
1868  {
1869  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Failed to get pin category"));
1870  }
1871  }
1872  }
1873 
1874  if (muxCount == 0)
1875  {
1876  pin->endpointPinId = endpointPinId;
1877  /* Make sure we get a name for the pin */
1878  if (wcslen(pin->friendlyName) == 0)
1879  {
1880  wcscpy(pin->friendlyName, kInputName);
1881  }
1882 #ifdef UNICODE
1883  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Input friendly name '%s'\n", pin->friendlyName));
1884 #else
1885  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Input friendly name '%S'\n", pin->friendlyName));
1886 #endif
1887  }
1888  else // muxCount > 0
1889  {
1890  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Setting up %u inputs\n", muxCount));
1891 
1892  /* Now we redo the operation once known how many multiplexer positions there are */
1893  pin->inputs = (PaWinWdmMuxedInput**)PaUtil_AllocateMemory(muxCount * sizeof(PaWinWdmMuxedInput*));
1894  if (pin->inputs == NULL)
1895  {
1896  FilterRelease(pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter);
1897  result = paInsufficientMemory;
1898  goto error;
1899  }
1900  pin->inputCount = muxCount;
1901 
1902  for (i = 0; i < muxCount; ++muxPos)
1903  {
1904  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Setting up input %u...\n", i));
1905 
1906  if (pin->inputs[i] == NULL)
1907  {
1908  pin->inputs[i] = (PaWinWdmMuxedInput*)PaUtil_AllocateMemory(sizeof(PaWinWdmMuxedInput));
1909  if (pin->inputs[i] == NULL)
1910  {
1911  FilterRelease(pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter);
1912  result = paInsufficientMemory;
1913  goto error;
1914  }
1915  }
1916 
1917  endpointPinId = GetConnectedPin(pcPin,
1918  FALSE,
1919  pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter,
1920  muxPos,
1921  &pin->inputs[i]->muxPinId,
1922  &pin->inputs[i]->muxNodeId);
1923 
1924  if (endpointPinId != KSFILTER_NODE)
1925  {
1926  /* The "endpointPinId" is what WASAPI looks at for pin names */
1927  GUID category = {0};
1928 
1929  /* Set input endpoint ID */
1930  pin->inputs[i]->endpointPinId = endpointPinId;
1931 
1932  /* Get pin category information */
1933  result = WdmGetPinPropertySimple(pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter->handle,
1934  endpointPinId,
1935  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1936  KSPROPERTY_PIN_CATEGORY,
1937  &category,
1938  sizeof(GUID),
1939  NULL);
1940 
1941  if (result == paNoError)
1942  {
1943  /* Try pin name first, and if that is not defined, use category instead */
1944  result = WdmGetPinPropertySimple(pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter->handle,
1945  endpointPinId,
1946  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
1947  KSPROPERTY_PIN_NAME,
1948  pin->inputs[i]->friendlyName,
1949  MAX_PATH,
1950  NULL);
1951 
1952  if (result != paNoError)
1953  {
1954  result = GetNameFromCategory(&category, TRUE, pin->inputs[i]->friendlyName, MAX_PATH);
1955  if (result != paNoError)
1956  {
1957  /* Only specify name, let name hash in ScanDeviceInfos fix postfix enumerators */
1958  wcscpy(pin->inputs[i]->friendlyName, kInputName);
1959  }
1960  }
1961 #ifdef UNICODE
1962  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Input (%u) friendly name '%s'\n", i, pin->inputs[i]->friendlyName));
1963 #else
1964  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Input (%u) friendly name '%S'\n", i, pin->inputs[i]->friendlyName));
1965 #endif
1966  ++i;
1967  }
1968  }
1969  else
1970  {
1971  /* Should never come here! */
1972  assert(FALSE);
1973  }
1974  }
1975  }
1976  }
1977  }
1978  }
1979  }
1980  else
1981  {
1982  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: No topology pin id found. Bad...\n"));
1983  /* No TOPO pin id ??? This is bad. Ok, so we just say it is an input or output... */
1984  wcscpy(pin->friendlyName, (pin->dataFlow == KSPIN_DATAFLOW_IN) ? kOutputName : kInputName);
1985  }
1986  }
1987 
1988  /* Release topology filter if it has been used */
1989  if (pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter && pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter->handle != NULL)
1990  {
1991  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Releasing topology filter...\n"));
1992  FilterRelease(pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter);
1993  }
1994 
1995  /* Success */
1996  *error = paNoError;
1997  PA_DEBUG(("Pin created successfully\n"));
1998  PA_LOGL_;
1999  return pin;
2000 
2001 error:
2002  PA_DEBUG(("PinNew: Error %d\n", result));
2003  /*
2004  Error cleanup
2005  */
2006 
2007  if (pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter && pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter->handle != NULL)
2008  {
2009  FilterRelease(pin->parentFilter->topologyFilter);
2010  }
2011 
2012  PaUtil_FreeMemory( item );
2013  PinFree(pin);
2014 
2015  *error = result;
2016  PA_LOGL_;
2017  return NULL;
2018 }
2019 
2020 /*
2021 Safely free all resources associated with the pin
2022 */
2023 static void PinFree(PaWinWdmPin* pin)
2024 {
2025  unsigned i;
2026  PA_LOGE_;
2027  if( pin )
2028  {
2029  PinClose(pin);
2030  if( pin->pinConnect )
2031  {
2032  PaUtil_FreeMemory( pin->pinConnect );
2033  }
2034  if( pin->dataRangesItem )
2035  {
2036  PaUtil_FreeMemory( pin->dataRangesItem );
2037  }
2038  if( pin->inputs )
2039  {
2040  for (i = 0; i < pin->inputCount; ++i)
2041  {
2042  PaUtil_FreeMemory( pin->inputs[i] );
2043  }
2044  PaUtil_FreeMemory( pin->inputs );
2045  }
2046  PaUtil_FreeMemory( pin );
2047  }
2048  PA_LOGL_;
2049 }

2051 /*
2052 If the pin handle is open, close it
2053 */
2054 static void PinClose(PaWinWdmPin* pin)
2055 {
2056  PA_LOGE_;

2061  return;
2062  }
2063  if( pin->handle != NULL )
2064  {
2065  PinSetState( pin, KSSTATE_PAUSE );
2066  PinSetState( pin, KSSTATE_STOP );
2067  CloseHandle( pin->handle );
2068  pin->handle = NULL;
2069  FilterRelease(pin->parentFilter);
2070  }
2071  PA_LOGL_;
2072 }

2098 static PaError PinInstantiate(PaWinWdmPin* pin)
2099 {
2100  PaError result;
2101  unsigned long createResult;
2102  KSALLOCATOR_FRAMING ksaf;
2103  KSALLOCATOR_FRAMING_EX ksafex;
2104 
2105  PA_LOGE_;
2106 
2107  if( pin == NULL )
2108  return paInternalError;
2109  if(!pin->pinConnect)
2110  return paInternalError;
2111 
2112  FilterUse(pin->parentFilter);
2113 
2114  createResult = FunctionKsCreatePin(
2115  pin->parentFilter->handle,
2116  pin->pinConnect,
2117  GENERIC_WRITE | GENERIC_READ,
2118  &pin->handle
2119  );
2120 
2121  PA_DEBUG(("Pin create result = 0x%08x\n",createResult));
2122  if( createResult != ERROR_SUCCESS )
2123  {
2124  FilterRelease(pin->parentFilter);
2125  pin->handle = NULL;
2126  switch (createResult)
2127  {
2128  case ERROR_INVALID_PARAMETER:
2129  /* First case when pin actually don't support the format */
2130  return paSampleFormatNotSupported;
2131  case ERROR_BAD_COMMAND:
2132  /* Case when pin is occupied (by another application) */
2133  return paDeviceUnavailable;
2134  default:
2135  /* All other cases */
2136  return paInvalidDevice;
2137  }
2138  }
2139 
2140  if (pin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType == Type_kWaveCyclic)
2141  {
2142  /* Framing size query only valid for WaveCyclic devices */
2143  result = WdmGetPropertySimple(
2144  pin->handle,
2145  &KSPROPSETID_Connection,
2146  KSPROPERTY_CONNECTION_ALLOCATORFRAMING,
2147  &ksaf,
2148  sizeof(ksaf));
2149 
2150  if( result != paNoError )
2151  {
2152  result = WdmGetPropertySimple(
2153  pin->handle,
2154  &KSPROPSETID_Connection,
2155  KSPROPERTY_CONNECTION_ALLOCATORFRAMING_EX,
2156  &ksafex,
2157  sizeof(ksafex));
2158  if( result == paNoError )
2159  {
2160  pin->frameSize = ksafex.FramingItem[0].FramingRange.Range.MinFrameSize;
2161  }
2162  }
2163  else
2164  {
2165  pin->frameSize = ksaf.FrameSize;
2166  }
2167  }
2168 
2169  PA_LOGL_;
2170 
2171  return paNoError;
2172 }
2173 
2174 static PaError PinSetFormat(PaWinWdmPin* pin, const WAVEFORMATEX* format)
2175 {
2176  unsigned long size;
2177  void* newConnect;
2178 
2179  PA_LOGE_;
2180 
2181  if( pin == NULL )
2182  return paInternalError;
2183  if( format == NULL )
2184  return paInternalError;
2185 
2186  size = GetWfexSize(format) + sizeof(KSPIN_CONNECT) + sizeof(KSDATAFORMAT_WAVEFORMATEX) - sizeof(WAVEFORMATEX);
2187 
2188  if( pin->pinConnectSize != size )
2189  {
2190  newConnect = PaUtil_AllocateMemory( size );
2191  if( newConnect == NULL )
2192  return paInsufficientMemory;
2193  memcpy( newConnect, (void*)pin->pinConnect, min(pin->pinConnectSize,size) );
2194  PaUtil_FreeMemory( pin->pinConnect );
2195  pin->pinConnect = (KSPIN_CONNECT*)newConnect;
2196  pin->pinConnectSize = size;
2197  pin->ksDataFormatWfx = (KSDATAFORMAT_WAVEFORMATEX*)((KSPIN_CONNECT*)newConnect + 1);
2198  pin->ksDataFormatWfx->DataFormat.FormatSize = size - sizeof(KSPIN_CONNECT);
2199  }
2200 
2201  memcpy( (void*)&(pin->ksDataFormatWfx->WaveFormatEx), format, GetWfexSize(format) );
2202  pin->ksDataFormatWfx->DataFormat.SampleSize = (unsigned short)(format->nChannels * (format->wBitsPerSample / 8));
2203 
2204  PA_LOGL_;
2205 
2206  return paNoError;
2207 }
2208 
2209 static PaError PinIsFormatSupported(PaWinWdmPin* pin, const WAVEFORMATEX* format)
2210 {
2211  KSDATARANGE_AUDIO* dataRange;
2212  unsigned long count;
2213  GUID guid = DYNAMIC_GUID( DEFINE_WAVEFORMATEX_GUID(format->wFormatTag) );
2214  PaError result = paInvalidDevice;
2215  const WAVEFORMATEXTENSIBLE* pFormatExt = (format->wFormatTag == WAVE_FORMAT_EXTENSIBLE) ? (const WAVEFORMATEXTENSIBLE*)format : 0;
2216 
2217  PA_LOGE_;
2218 
2219  if( pFormatExt != 0 )
2220  {
2221  guid = pFormatExt->SubFormat;
2222  }
2223  dataRange = (KSDATARANGE_AUDIO*)pin->dataRanges;
2224  for(count = 0;
2225  count<pin->dataRangesItem->Count;
2226  count++,
2227  dataRange = (KSDATARANGE_AUDIO*)( ((char*)dataRange) + dataRange->DataRange.FormatSize)) /* Need to update dataRange here, due to 'continue' !! */
2228  {
2229  /* Check major format*/
2230  if (!(IsEqualGUID(&(dataRange->DataRange.MajorFormat), &KSDATAFORMAT_TYPE_AUDIO) ||
2231  IsEqualGUID(&(dataRange->DataRange.MajorFormat), &KSDATAFORMAT_TYPE_WILDCARD)))
2232  {
2233  continue;
2234  }
2235 
2236  /* This is an audio or wildcard datarange... */
2237  if (! (IsEqualGUID(&(dataRange->DataRange.SubFormat), &KSDATAFORMAT_SUBTYPE_WILDCARD) ||
2238  IsEqualGUID(&(dataRange->DataRange.SubFormat), &KSDATAFORMAT_SUBTYPE_PCM) ||
2239  IsEqualGUID(&(dataRange->DataRange.SubFormat), &guid) ))
2240  {
2241  continue;
2242  }
2243 
2244  /* Check specifier... */
2245  if (! (IsEqualGUID(&(dataRange->DataRange.Specifier), &KSDATAFORMAT_SPECIFIER_WILDCARD) ||
2246  IsEqualGUID(&(dataRange->DataRange.Specifier), &KSDATAFORMAT_SPECIFIER_WAVEFORMATEX)) )
2247  {
2248  continue;
2249  }
2250 
2251  PA_DEBUG(("Pin:%x, DataRange:%d\n",(void*)pin,count));
2252  PA_DEBUG(("\tFormatSize:%d, SampleSize:%d\n",dataRange->DataRange.FormatSize,dataRange->DataRange.SampleSize));
2253  PA_DEBUG(("\tMaxChannels:%d\n",dataRange->MaximumChannels));
2254  PA_DEBUG(("\tBits:%d-%d\n",dataRange->MinimumBitsPerSample,dataRange->MaximumBitsPerSample));
2255  PA_DEBUG(("\tSampleRate:%d-%d\n",dataRange->MinimumSampleFrequency,dataRange->MaximumSampleFrequency));
2256 
2257  if( dataRange->MaximumChannels != (ULONG)-1 &&
2258  dataRange->MaximumChannels < format->nChannels )
2259  {
2260  result = paInvalidChannelCount;
2261  continue;
2262  }
2263 
2264  if (pFormatExt != 0)
2265  {
2266  if (!IsBitsWithinRange(dataRange, pFormatExt->Samples.wValidBitsPerSample))
2267  {
2268  result = paSampleFormatNotSupported;
2269  continue;
2270  }
2271  }
2272  else
2273  {
2274  if (!IsBitsWithinRange(dataRange, format->wBitsPerSample))
2275  {
2276  result = paSampleFormatNotSupported;
2277  continue;
2278  }
2279  }
2280 
2281  if (!IsFrequencyWithinRange(dataRange, format->nSamplesPerSec))
2282  {
2283  result = paInvalidSampleRate;
2284  continue;
2285  }
2286 
2287  /* Success! */
2288  result = paNoError;
2289  break;
2290  }
2291 
2292  PA_LOGL_;
2293  return result;
2294 }

2396 /* greatest common divisor - PGCD in French */
2397 static unsigned long PaWinWDMGCD( unsigned long a, unsigned long b )
2398 {
2399  return (b==0) ? a : PaWinWDMGCD( b, a%b);
2400 }
2401 
2402 
2403 /* This function will handle getting the cyclic buffer from a WaveRT driver. Certain WaveRT drivers needs to have
2404 requested buffer size on multiples of 128 bytes:
2405 
2406 */
2407 static PaError PinGetBuffer(PaWinWdmPin* pPin, void** pBuffer, DWORD* pRequestedBufSize, BOOL* pbCallMemBarrier)
2408 {
2409  PaError result = paNoError;
2410  int limit = 1000;
2411  PA_LOGE_;
2412 
2413  while (1)
2414  {
2415  limit--;
2416  if (limit == 0) {
2417  PA_DEBUG(("PinGetBuffer: LOOP LIMIT REACHED\n"));
2418  break;
2419  }
2420 
2421  if (pPin->pinKsSubType != SubType_kPolled)
2422  {
2423  /* In case of unknown (or notification), we try both modes */
2424  result = PinGetBufferWithNotification(pPin, pBuffer, pRequestedBufSize, pbCallMemBarrier);
2425  if (result == paNoError)
2426  {
2427  PA_DEBUG(("PinGetBuffer: SubType_kNotification\n"));
2428  pPin->pinKsSubType = SubType_kNotification;
2429  break;
2430  }
2431  }
2432 
2433  result = PinGetBufferWithoutNotification(pPin, pBuffer, pRequestedBufSize, pbCallMemBarrier);
2434  if (result == paNoError)
2435  {
2436  PA_DEBUG(("PinGetBuffer: SubType_kPolled\n"));
2437  pPin->pinKsSubType = SubType_kPolled;
2438  break;
2439  }
2440 
2441  /* Check if requested size is on a 128 byte boundary */
2442  if (((*pRequestedBufSize) % 128UL) == 0)
2443  {
2444  PA_DEBUG(("Buffer size on 128 byte boundary, still fails :(\n"));
2445  /* Ok, can't do much more */
2446  break;
2447  }
2448  else
2449  {
2450  /* Compute LCM so we know which sizes are on a 128 byte boundary */
2451  const unsigned gcd = PaWinWDMGCD(128UL, pPin->ksDataFormatWfx->WaveFormatEx.nBlockAlign);
2452  const unsigned lcm = (128UL * pPin->ksDataFormatWfx->WaveFormatEx.nBlockAlign) / gcd;
2453  DWORD dwOldSize = *pRequestedBufSize;
2454 
2455  /* Align size to (next larger) LCM byte boundary, and then we try again. Note that LCM is not necessarily a
2456  power of 2. */
2457  *pRequestedBufSize = ((*pRequestedBufSize + lcm - 1) / lcm) * lcm;
2458 
2459  PA_DEBUG(("Adjusting buffer size from %u to %u bytes (128 byte boundary, LCM=%u)\n", dwOldSize, *pRequestedBufSize, lcm));
2460  }
2461  }
2462 
2463  PA_LOGL_;
2464 
2465  return result;
2466 }

2618  IOCTL_KS_PROPERTY,
2619  &propIn, sizeof(KSPROPERTY),
2620  &propOut, sizeof(KSAUDIO_POSITION),
2621  NULL);

2624  {
2625  *pPosition = (ULONG)(propOut.PlayOffset);
2626  }
2627  else
2628  {
2629  PA_DEBUG(("Failed to get audio play position!\n"));
2630  }
2631 
2632  PA_LOGL_;
2633 
2634  return result;
2635 
2636 }

2677 static PaWinWdmFilter* FilterNew( PaWDMKSType type, DWORD devNode, const wchar_t* filterName, const wchar_t* friendlyName, PaError* error )
2678 {
2679  PaWinWdmFilter* filter = 0;
2680  PaError result;
2681 
2682  /* Allocate the new filter object */
2683  filter = (PaWinWdmFilter*)PaUtil_AllocateMemory( sizeof(PaWinWdmFilter) );
2684  if( !filter )
2685  {
2686  result = paInsufficientMemory;
2687  goto error;
2688  }
2689 
2690  PA_DEBUG(("FilterNew: Creating filter '%S'\n", friendlyName));
2691 
2692  /* Set type flag */
2693  filter->devInfo.streamingType = type;
2694 
2695  /* Store device node */
2696  filter->deviceNode = devNode;
2697 
2698  /* Zero the filter object - done by AllocateMemory */
2699  /* memset( (void*)filter, 0, sizeof(PaWinWdmFilter) ); */
2700 
2701  /* Copy the filter name */
2702  wcsncpy(filter->devInfo.filterPath, filterName, MAX_PATH);
2703 
2704  /* Copy the friendly name */
2705  wcsncpy(filter->friendlyName, friendlyName, MAX_PATH);
2706 
2707  PA_DEBUG(("FilterNew: Opening filter...\n", friendlyName));
2708 
2709  /* Open the filter handle */
2710  result = FilterUse(filter);
2711  if( result != paNoError )
2712  {
2713  goto error;
2714  }
2715 
2716  /* Get pin count */
2717  result = WdmGetPinPropertySimple
2718  (
2719  filter->handle,
2720  0,
2721  &KSPROPSETID_Pin,
2722  KSPROPERTY_PIN_CTYPES,
2723  &filter->pinCount,
2724  sizeof(filter->pinCount),
2725  NULL);
2726 
2727  if( result != paNoError)
2728  {
2729  goto error;
2730  }
2731 
2732  /* Get connections & nodes for filter */
2733  result = WdmGetPropertyMulti(
2734  filter->handle,
2735  &KSPROPSETID_Topology,
2736  KSPROPERTY_TOPOLOGY_CONNECTIONS,
2737  &filter->connections);
2738 
2739  if( result != paNoError)
2740  {
2741  goto error;
2742  }
2743 
2744  result = WdmGetPropertyMulti(
2745  filter->handle,
2746  &KSPROPSETID_Topology,
2747  KSPROPERTY_TOPOLOGY_NODES,
2748  &filter->nodes);
2749 
2750  if( result != paNoError)
2751  {
2752  goto error;
2753  }
2754 
2755  /* For debugging purposes */
2756  DumpConnectionsAndNodes(filter);
2757 
2758  /* Get product GUID (it might not be supported) */
2759  {
2760  KSCOMPONENTID compId;
2761  if (WdmGetPropertySimple(filter->handle, &KSPROPSETID_General, KSPROPERTY_GENERAL_COMPONENTID, &compId, sizeof(KSCOMPONENTID)) == paNoError)
2762  {
2763  filter->devInfo.deviceProductGuid = compId.Product;
2764  }
2765  }
2766 
2767  /* This section is not executed for topology filters */
2768  if (type != Type_kNotUsed)
2769  {
2770  /* Initialize the pins */
2771  result = FilterInitializePins(filter);
2772 
2773  if( result != paNoError)
2774  {
2775  goto error;
2776  }
2777  }
2778 
2779  /* Close the filter handle for now
2780  * It will be opened later when needed */
2781  FilterRelease(filter);
2782 
2783  *error = paNoError;
2784  return filter;
2785 
2786 error:
2787  PA_DEBUG(("FilterNew: Error %d\n", result));
2788  /*
2789  Error cleanup
2790  */
2791  FilterFree(filter);
2792 
2793  *error = result;
2794  return NULL;
2795 }

2800 static void FilterAddRef( PaWinWdmFilter* filter )

2813 PaError FilterInitializePins( PaWinWdmFilter* filter )
2814 {
2815  PaError result = paNoError;
2816  int pinId;
2817 
2818  if (filter->devInfo.streamingType == Type_kNotUsed)
2819  return paNoError;
2820 
2821  if (filter->pins != NULL)
2822  return paNoError;
2823 
2824  /* Allocate pointer array to hold the pins */
2825  filter->pins = (PaWinWdmPin**)PaUtil_AllocateMemory( sizeof(PaWinWdmPin*) * filter->pinCount );
2826  if( !filter->pins )
2827  {
2828  result = paInsufficientMemory;
2829  goto error;
2830  }
2831 
2832  /* Create all the pins we can */
2833  for(pinId = 0; pinId < filter->pinCount; pinId++)
2834  {
2835  /* Create the pin with this Id */
2836  PaWinWdmPin* newPin;
2837  newPin = PinNew(filter, pinId, &result);
2838  if( result == paInsufficientMemory )
2839  goto error;
2840  if( newPin != NULL )
2841  {
2842  filter->pins[pinId] = newPin;
2843  ++filter->validPinCount;
2844  }
2845  }
2846 
2847  if (filter->validPinCount == 0)
2848  {
2849  result = paDeviceUnavailable;
2850  goto error;
2851  }
2852 
2853  return paNoError;
2854 
2855 error:
2856 
2857  if (filter->pins)
2858  {
2859  for (pinId = 0; pinId < filter->pinCount; ++pinId)
2860  {
2861  if (filter->pins[pinId])
2862  {
2863  PinFree(filter->pins[pinId]);
2864  filter->pins[pinId] = 0;
2865  }
2866  }
2867  PaUtil_FreeMemory( filter->pins );
2868  filter->pins = 0;
2869  }
2870 
2871  return result;
2872 }

2878 static void FilterFree(PaWinWdmFilter* filter)
2879 {
2880  PA_LOGL_;
2881  if( filter )
2882  {
2883  if (--filter->filterRefCount > 0)
2884  {
2885  /* Ok, a stream has a ref count to this filter */
2886  return;
2887  }
2888 
2889  if ( filter->topologyFilter )
2890  {
2891  FilterFree(filter->topologyFilter);
2892  filter->topologyFilter = 0;
2893  }
2894  if ( filter->pins )
2895  {
2896  int pinId;
2897  for( pinId = 0; pinId < filter->pinCount; pinId++ )
2898  PinFree(filter->pins[pinId]);
2899  PaUtil_FreeMemory( filter->pins );
2900  filter->pins = 0;
2901  }
2902  if( filter->connections )
2903  {
2904  PaUtil_FreeMemory(filter->connections);
2905  filter->connections = 0;
2906  }
2907  if( filter->nodes )
2908  {
2909  PaUtil_FreeMemory(filter->nodes);
2910  filter->nodes = 0;
2911  }
2912  if( filter->handle )
2913  CloseHandle( filter->handle );
2914  PaUtil_FreeMemory( filter );
2915  }
2916  PA_LOGE_;
2917 }

2922 static PaError FilterUse(PaWinWdmFilter* filter)
2923 {

2932  GENERIC_READ | GENERIC_WRITE,
2933  0,
2934  NULL,

2936  FILE_ATTRIBUTE_NORMAL | FILE_FLAG_OVERLAPPED,
2937  NULL);
2938 
2939  if( filter->handle == NULL )
2940  {
2941  return paDeviceUnavailable;
2942  }
2943  }
2944  filter->usageCount++;
2945  PA_LOGL_;
2946  return paNoError;

2952 static void FilterRelease(PaWinWdmFilter* filter)
2953 {

2960  {
2961  FilterRelease(filter->topologyFilter);
2962  }
2963 
2964  filter->usageCount--;
2965  if( filter->usageCount == 0 )
2966  {
2967  if( filter->handle != NULL )
2968  {
2969  CloseHandle( filter->handle );
2970  filter->handle = NULL;
2971  }
2972  }

3016 typedef enum _tag_EAlias

3023 /* Trim whitespace from string */
3024 static void TrimString(wchar_t* str, size_t length)
3025 {
3026  wchar_t* s = str;
3027  wchar_t* e = 0;
3028 
3029  /* Find start of string */
3030  while (iswspace(*s)) ++s;
3031  e=s+min(length,wcslen(s))-1;
3032 
3033  /* Find end of string */
3034  while(e>s && iswspace(*e)) --e;
3035  ++e;
3036 
3037  length = e - s;
3038  memmove(str, s, length * sizeof(wchar_t));
3039  str[length] = 0;
3040 }

3052 //PaError BuildFilterList( PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation* wdmHostApi, int* noOfPaDevices )
3053 PaWinWdmFilter** BuildFilterList( int* pFilterCount, int* pNoOfPaDevices, PaError* pResult )
3054 {
3055  PaWinWdmFilter** ppFilters = NULL;
3056  HDEVINFO handle = NULL;
3057  int device;
3058  int invalidDevices;
3059  int slot;
3060  SP_DEVICE_INTERFACE_DATA interfaceData;
3061  SP_DEVICE_INTERFACE_DATA aliasData;
3062  SP_DEVINFO_DATA devInfoData;
3063  int noError;
3064  const int sizeInterface = sizeof(SP_DEVICE_INTERFACE_DETAIL_DATA) + (MAX_PATH * sizeof(WCHAR));
3065  unsigned char interfaceDetailsArray[sizeof(SP_DEVICE_INTERFACE_DETAIL_DATA) + (MAX_PATH * sizeof(WCHAR))];
3066  SP_DEVICE_INTERFACE_DETAIL_DATA_W* devInterfaceDetails = (SP_DEVICE_INTERFACE_DETAIL_DATA_W*)interfaceDetailsArray;
3067  const GUID* category = (const GUID*)&KSCATEGORY_AUDIO;
3068  const GUID* alias_render = (const GUID*)&KSCATEGORY_RENDER;
3069  const GUID* alias_capture = (const GUID*)&KSCATEGORY_CAPTURE;
3070  const GUID* category_realtime = (const GUID*)&KSCATEGORY_REALTIME;
3071  DWORD aliasFlags;
3072  PaWDMKSType streamingType;
3073  int filterCount = 0;
3074  int noOfPaDevices = 0;
3075 
3076  PA_LOGE_;
3077 
3078  assert(pFilterCount != NULL);
3079  assert(pNoOfPaDevices != NULL);
3080  assert(pResult != NULL);
3081 
3082  devInterfaceDetails->cbSize = sizeof(SP_DEVICE_INTERFACE_DETAIL_DATA_W);
3083  *pFilterCount = 0;
3084  *pNoOfPaDevices = 0;
3085 
3086  /* Open a handle to search for devices (filters) */
3087  handle = SetupDiGetClassDevs(category,NULL,NULL,DIGCF_PRESENT | DIGCF_DEVICEINTERFACE);
3088  if( handle == INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE )
3089  {
3090  *pResult = paUnanticipatedHostError;
3091  return NULL;
3092  }
3093  PA_DEBUG(("Setup called\n"));
3094 
3095  /* First let's count the number of devices so we can allocate a list */
3096  invalidDevices = 0;
3097  for( device = 0;;device++ )
3098  {
3099  interfaceData.cbSize = sizeof(SP_DEVICE_INTERFACE_DATA);
3100  interfaceData.Reserved = 0;
3101  aliasData.cbSize = sizeof(SP_DEVICE_INTERFACE_DATA);
3102  aliasData.Reserved = 0;
3103  noError = SetupDiEnumDeviceInterfaces(handle,NULL,category,device,&interfaceData);
3104  PA_DEBUG(("Enum called\n"));
3105  if( !noError )
3106  break; /* No more devices */
3107 
3108  /* Check this one has the render or capture alias */
3109  aliasFlags = 0;
3110  noError = SetupDiGetDeviceInterfaceAlias(handle,&interfaceData,alias_render,&aliasData);
3111  PA_DEBUG(("noError = %d\n",noError));
3112  if(noError)
3113  {
3114  if(aliasData.Flags && (!(aliasData.Flags & SPINT_REMOVED)))
3115  {
3116  PA_DEBUG(("Device %d has render alias\n",device));
3117  aliasFlags |= Alias_kRender; /* Has render alias */
3118  }
3119  else
3120  {
3121  PA_DEBUG(("Device %d has no render alias\n",device));
3122  }
3123  }
3124  noError = SetupDiGetDeviceInterfaceAlias(handle,&interfaceData,alias_capture,&aliasData);
3125  if(noError)
3126  {
3127  if(aliasData.Flags && (!(aliasData.Flags & SPINT_REMOVED)))
3128  {
3129  PA_DEBUG(("Device %d has capture alias\n",device));
3130  aliasFlags |= Alias_kCapture; /* Has capture alias */
3131  }
3132  else
3133  {
3134  PA_DEBUG(("Device %d has no capture alias\n",device));
3135  }
3136  }
3137  if(!aliasFlags)
3138  invalidDevices++; /* This was not a valid capture or render audio device */
3139  }
3140  /* Remember how many there are */
3141  filterCount = device-invalidDevices;
3142 
3143  PA_DEBUG(("Interfaces found: %d\n",device-invalidDevices));
3144 
3145  /* Now allocate the list of pointers to devices */
3146  ppFilters = (PaWinWdmFilter**)PaUtil_AllocateMemory( sizeof(PaWinWdmFilter*) * filterCount);
3147  if( ppFilters == 0 )
3148  {
3149  if(handle != NULL)
3150  SetupDiDestroyDeviceInfoList(handle);
3151  *pResult = paInsufficientMemory;
3152  return NULL;
3153  }
3154 
3155  /* Now create filter objects for each interface found */
3156  slot = 0;
3157  for( device = 0;;device++ )
3158  {
3159  interfaceData.cbSize = sizeof(SP_DEVICE_INTERFACE_DATA);
3160  interfaceData.Reserved = 0;
3161  aliasData.cbSize = sizeof(SP_DEVICE_INTERFACE_DATA);
3162  aliasData.Reserved = 0;
3163  devInfoData.cbSize = sizeof(SP_DEVINFO_DATA);
3164  devInfoData.Reserved = 0;
3165  streamingType = Type_kWaveCyclic;
3166 
3167  noError = SetupDiEnumDeviceInterfaces(handle,NULL,category,device,&interfaceData);
3168  if( !noError )
3169  break; /* No more devices */
3170 
3171  /* Check this one has the render or capture alias */
3172  aliasFlags = 0;
3173  noError = SetupDiGetDeviceInterfaceAlias(handle,&interfaceData,alias_render,&aliasData);
3174  if(noError)
3175  {
3176  if(aliasData.Flags && (!(aliasData.Flags & SPINT_REMOVED)))
3177  {
3178  PA_DEBUG(("Device %d has render alias\n",device));
3179  aliasFlags |= Alias_kRender; /* Has render alias */
3180  }
3181  }
3182  noError = SetupDiGetDeviceInterfaceAlias(handle,&interfaceData,alias_capture,&aliasData);
3183  if(noError)
3184  {
3185  if(aliasData.Flags && (!(aliasData.Flags & SPINT_REMOVED)))
3186  {
3187  PA_DEBUG(("Device %d has capture alias\n",device));
3188  aliasFlags |= Alias_kCapture; /* Has capture alias */
3189  }
3190  }
3191  if(!aliasFlags)
3192  {
3193  continue; /* This was not a valid capture or render audio device */
3194  }
3195  else
3196  {
3197  /* Check if filter is WaveRT, if not it is a WaveCyclic */
3198  noError = SetupDiGetDeviceInterfaceAlias(handle,&interfaceData,category_realtime,&aliasData);
3199  if (noError)
3200  {
3201  PA_DEBUG(("Device %d has realtime alias\n",device));
3202  aliasFlags |= Alias_kRealtime;
3203  streamingType = Type_kWaveRT;
3204  }
3205  }
3206 
3207  noError = SetupDiGetDeviceInterfaceDetailW(handle,&interfaceData,devInterfaceDetails,sizeInterface,NULL,&devInfoData);
3208  if( noError )
3209  {
3210  DWORD type;
3211  WCHAR friendlyName[MAX_PATH] = {0};
3212  DWORD sizeFriendlyName;
3213  PaWinWdmFilter* newFilter = 0;
3214 
3215  PaError result = paNoError;
3216  /* Try to get the "friendly name" for this interface */
3217  sizeFriendlyName = sizeof(friendlyName);
3218 
3219  if (IsEarlierThanVista() && IsUSBDevice(devInterfaceDetails->DevicePath))
3220  {
3221  /* XP and USB audio device needs to look elsewhere, otherwise it'll only be a "USB Audio Device". Not
3222  very literate. */
3223  if (!SetupDiGetDeviceRegistryPropertyW(handle,
3224  &devInfoData,
3225  SPDRP_LOCATION_INFORMATION,
3226  &type,
3227  (BYTE*)friendlyName,
3228  sizeof(friendlyName),
3229  NULL))
3230  {
3231  friendlyName[0] = 0;
3232  }
3233  }
3234 
3235  if (friendlyName[0] == 0 || IsNameUSBAudioDevice(friendlyName))
3236  {
3237  /* Fix contributed by Ben Allison
3238  * Removed KEY_SET_VALUE from flags on following call
3239  * as its causes failure when running without admin rights
3240  * and it was not required */
3241  HKEY hkey=SetupDiOpenDeviceInterfaceRegKey(handle,&interfaceData,0,KEY_QUERY_VALUE);
3242  if(hkey!=INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE)
3243  {
3244  noError = RegQueryValueExW(hkey,L"FriendlyName",0,&type,(BYTE*)friendlyName,&sizeFriendlyName);
3245  if( noError == ERROR_SUCCESS )
3246  {
3247  PA_DEBUG(("Interface %d, Name: %s\n",device,friendlyName));
3248  RegCloseKey(hkey);
3249  }
3250  else
3251  {
3252  friendlyName[0] = 0;
3253  }
3254  }
3255  }
3256 
3257  TrimString(friendlyName, sizeFriendlyName);
3258 
3259  newFilter = FilterNew(streamingType,
3260  devInfoData.DevInst,
3261  devInterfaceDetails->DevicePath,
3262  friendlyName,
3263  &result);
3264 
3265  if( result == paNoError )
3266  {
3267  int pin;
3268  unsigned filterIOs = 0;
3269 
3270  /* Increment number of "devices" */
3271  for (pin = 0; pin < newFilter->pinCount; ++pin)
3272  {
3273  PaWinWdmPin* pPin = newFilter->pins[pin];
3274  if (pPin == NULL)
3275  continue;
3276 
3277  filterIOs += max(1, pPin->inputCount);
3278  }
3279 
3280  noOfPaDevices += filterIOs;
3281 
3282  PA_DEBUG(("Filter (%s) created with %d valid pins (total I/Os: %u)\n", ((newFilter->devInfo.streamingType==Type_kWaveRT)?"WaveRT":"WaveCyclic"), newFilter->validPinCount, filterIOs));
3283 
3284  assert(slot < filterCount);
3285 
3286  ppFilters[slot] = newFilter;
3287 
3288  slot++;
3289  }
3290  else
3291  {
3292  PA_DEBUG(("Filter NOT created\n"));
3293  /* As there are now less filters than we initially thought
3294  * we must reduce the count by one */
3295  filterCount--;
3296  }
3297  }
3298  }
3299 
3300  /* Clean up */
3301  if(handle != NULL)
3302  SetupDiDestroyDeviceInfoList(handle);
3303 
3304  *pFilterCount = filterCount;
3305  *pNoOfPaDevices = noOfPaDevices;
3306 
3307  return ppFilters;
3308 }
