3310 typedef struct PaNameHashIndex
3311 {
3312  unsigned index;
3313  unsigned count;
3314  ULONG hash;
3315  struct PaNameHashIndex *next;
3316 } PaNameHashIndex;
3317 
3318 typedef struct PaNameHashObject
3319 {
3320  PaNameHashIndex* list;
3321  PaUtilAllocationGroup* allocGroup;
3322 } PaNameHashObject;
3323 
3324 static ULONG GetNameHash(const wchar_t* str, const BOOL input)
3325 {
3326  /* This is to make sure that a name that exists as both input & output won't get the same hash value */
3327  const ULONG fnv_prime = (input ? 0x811C9DD7 : 0x811FEB0B);
3328  ULONG hash = 0;
3329  for(; *str != 0; str++)
3330  {
3331  hash *= fnv_prime;
3332  hash ^= (*str);
3333  }
3334  assert(hash != 0);
3335  return hash;
3336 }
3337 
3338 static PaError CreateHashEntry(PaNameHashObject* obj, const wchar_t* name, const BOOL input)
3339 {
3340  ULONG hash = GetNameHash(name, input);
3341  PaNameHashIndex * pLast = NULL;
3342  PaNameHashIndex * p = obj->list;
3343  while (p != 0)
3344  {
3345  if (p->hash == hash)
3346  {
3347  break;
3348  }
3349  pLast = p;
3350  p = p->next;
3351  }
3352  if (p == NULL)
3353  {
3354  p = (PaNameHashIndex*)PaUtil_GroupAllocateMemory(obj->allocGroup, sizeof(PaNameHashIndex));
3355  if (p == NULL)
3356  {
3357  return paInsufficientMemory;
3358  }
3359  p->hash = hash;
3360  p->count = 1;
3361  if (pLast != 0)
3362  {
3363  assert(pLast->next == 0);
3364  pLast->next = p;
3365  }
3366  if (obj->list == 0)
3367  {
3368  obj->list = p;
3369  }
3370  }
3371  else
3372  {
3373  ++p->count;
3374  }
3375  return paNoError;
3376 }
3377 
3378 static PaError InitNameHashObject(PaNameHashObject* obj, PaWinWdmFilter* pFilter)
3379 {
3380  int i;
3381 
3382  obj->allocGroup = PaUtil_CreateAllocationGroup();
3383  if (obj->allocGroup == NULL)
3384  {
3385  return paInsufficientMemory;
3386  }
3387 
3388  for (i = 0; i < pFilter->pinCount; ++i)
3389  {
3390  unsigned m;
3391  PaWinWdmPin* pin = pFilter->pins[i];
3392 
3393  if (pin == NULL)
3394  continue;
3395 
3396  for (m = 0; m < max(1, pin->inputCount); ++m)
3397  {
3398  const BOOL isInput = (pin->dataFlow == KSPIN_DATAFLOW_OUT);
3399  const wchar_t* name = (pin->inputs == NULL) ? pin->friendlyName : pin->inputs[m]->friendlyName;
3400 
3401  PaError result = CreateHashEntry(obj, name, isInput);
3402 
3403  if (result != paNoError)
3404  {
3405  return result;
3406  }
3407  }
3408  }
3409  return paNoError;
3410 }
3411 
3412 static void DeinitNameHashObject(PaNameHashObject* obj)
3413 {
3414  assert(obj != 0);
3415  PaUtil_FreeAllAllocations(obj->allocGroup);
3416  PaUtil_DestroyAllocationGroup(obj->allocGroup);
3417  memset(obj, 0, sizeof(PaNameHashObject));
3418 }
3419 
3420 static unsigned GetNameIndex(PaNameHashObject* obj, const wchar_t* name, const BOOL input)
3421 {
3422  ULONG hash = GetNameHash(name, input);
3423  PaNameHashIndex* p = obj->list;
3424  while (p != NULL)
3425  {
3426  if (p->hash == hash)
3427  {
3428  if (p->count > 1)
3429  {
3430  return (++p->index);
3431  }
3432  else
3433  {
3434  return 0;
3435  }
3436  }
3437 
3438  p = p->next;
3439  }
3440  // Should never get here!!
3441  assert(FALSE);
3442  return 0;
3443 }
3444 
3445 static PaError ScanDeviceInfos( struct PaUtilHostApiRepresentation *hostApi, PaHostApiIndex hostApiIndex, void **scanResults, int *newDeviceCount )
3446 {
3447  PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation *wdmHostApi = (PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation*)hostApi;
3448  PaError result = paNoError;
3449  PaWinWdmFilter** ppFilters = 0;
3450  PaWinWDMScanDeviceInfosResults *outArgument = 0;
3451  int filterCount = 0;
3452  int totalDeviceCount = 0;
3453  int idxDevice = 0;
3454  DWORD defaultInDevPathSize = 0;
3455  DWORD defaultOutDevPathSize = 0;
3456  wchar_t* defaultInDevPath = 0;
3457  wchar_t* defaultOutDevPath = 0;
3458 
3459  ppFilters = BuildFilterList( &filterCount, &totalDeviceCount, &result );
3460  if( result != paNoError )
3461  {
3462  goto error;
3463  }
3464 
3465  // Get hold of default device paths for capture & playback
3466  if( waveInMessage(0, DRV_QUERYDEVICEINTERFACESIZE, (DWORD_PTR)&defaultInDevPathSize, 0 ) == MMSYSERR_NOERROR )
3467  {
3468  defaultInDevPath = (wchar_t *)PaUtil_AllocateMemory((defaultInDevPathSize + 1) * sizeof(wchar_t));
3469  waveInMessage(0, DRV_QUERYDEVICEINTERFACE, (DWORD_PTR)defaultInDevPath, defaultInDevPathSize);
3470  }
3471  if( waveOutMessage(0, DRV_QUERYDEVICEINTERFACESIZE, (DWORD_PTR)&defaultOutDevPathSize, 0 ) == MMSYSERR_NOERROR )
3472  {
3473  defaultOutDevPath = (wchar_t *)PaUtil_AllocateMemory((defaultOutDevPathSize + 1) * sizeof(wchar_t));
3474  waveOutMessage(0, DRV_QUERYDEVICEINTERFACE, (DWORD_PTR)defaultOutDevPath, defaultOutDevPathSize);
3475  }
3476 
3477  if( totalDeviceCount > 0 )
3478  {
3479  PaWinWdmDeviceInfo *deviceInfoArray = 0;
3480  int idxFilter;
3481  int i;
3482  unsigned devIsDefaultIn = 0, devIsDefaultOut = 0;
3483 
3484  /* Allocate the out param for all the info we need */
3485  outArgument = (PaWinWDMScanDeviceInfosResults *) PaUtil_GroupAllocateMemory(
3486  wdmHostApi->allocations, sizeof(PaWinWDMScanDeviceInfosResults) );
3487  if( !outArgument )
3488  {
3489  result = paInsufficientMemory;
3490  goto error;
3491  }
3492 
3493  outArgument->defaultInputDevice = paNoDevice;
3494  outArgument->defaultOutputDevice = paNoDevice;
3495 
3496  outArgument->deviceInfos = (PaDeviceInfo**)PaUtil_GroupAllocateMemory(
3497  wdmHostApi->allocations, sizeof(PaDeviceInfo*) * totalDeviceCount );
3498  if( !outArgument->deviceInfos )
3499  {
3500  result = paInsufficientMemory;
3501  goto error;
3502  }
3503 
3504  /* allocate all device info structs in a contiguous block */
3505  deviceInfoArray = (PaWinWdmDeviceInfo*)PaUtil_GroupAllocateMemory(
3506  wdmHostApi->allocations, sizeof(PaWinWdmDeviceInfo) * totalDeviceCount );
3507  if( !deviceInfoArray )
3508  {
3509  result = paInsufficientMemory;
3510  goto error;
3511  }
3512 
3513  /* Make sure all items in array */
3514  for( i = 0 ; i < totalDeviceCount; ++i )
3515  {
3516  PaDeviceInfo *deviceInfo = &deviceInfoArray[i].inheritedDeviceInfo;
3517  deviceInfo->structVersion = 2;
3518  deviceInfo->hostApi = hostApiIndex;
3519  deviceInfo->name = 0;
3520  outArgument->deviceInfos[ i ] = deviceInfo;
3521  }
3522 
3523  idxDevice = 0;
3524  for (idxFilter = 0; idxFilter < filterCount; ++idxFilter)
3525  {
3526  PaNameHashObject nameHash = {0};
3527  PaWinWdmFilter* pFilter = ppFilters[idxFilter];
3528  if( pFilter == NULL )
3529  continue;
3530 
3531  if (InitNameHashObject(&nameHash, pFilter) != paNoError)
3532  {
3533  DeinitNameHashObject(&nameHash);
3534  continue;
3535  }
3536 
3537  devIsDefaultIn = (defaultInDevPath && (_wcsicmp(pFilter->devInfo.filterPath, defaultInDevPath) == 0));
3538  devIsDefaultOut = (defaultOutDevPath && (_wcsicmp(pFilter->devInfo.filterPath, defaultOutDevPath) == 0));
3539 
3540  for (i = 0; i < pFilter->pinCount; ++i)
3541  {
3542  unsigned m;
3543  ULONG nameIndex = 0;
3544  ULONG nameIndexHash = 0;
3545  PaWinWdmPin* pin = pFilter->pins[i];
3546 
3547  if (pin == NULL)
3548  continue;
3549 
3550  for (m = 0; m < max(1, pin->inputCount); ++m)
3551  {
3552  PaWinWdmDeviceInfo *wdmDeviceInfo = (PaWinWdmDeviceInfo *)outArgument->deviceInfos[idxDevice];
3553  PaDeviceInfo *deviceInfo = &wdmDeviceInfo->inheritedDeviceInfo;
3554  wchar_t localCompositeName[MAX_PATH];
3555  unsigned nameIndex = 0;
3556  const BOOL isInput = (pin->dataFlow == KSPIN_DATAFLOW_OUT);
3557 
3558  wdmDeviceInfo->filter = pFilter;
3559 
3560  deviceInfo->structVersion = 2;
3561  deviceInfo->hostApi = hostApiIndex;
3562  deviceInfo->name = wdmDeviceInfo->compositeName;
3563  /* deviceInfo->hostApiSpecificDeviceInfo = &pFilter->devInfo; */
3564 
3565  wdmDeviceInfo->pin = pin->pinId;
3566 
3567  /* Get the name of the "device" */
3568  if (pin->inputs == NULL)
3569  {
3570  wcsncpy(localCompositeName, pin->friendlyName, MAX_PATH);
3571  wdmDeviceInfo->muxPosition = -1;
3572  wdmDeviceInfo->endpointPinId = pin->endpointPinId;
3573  }
3574  else
3575  {
3576  PaWinWdmMuxedInput* input = pin->inputs[m];
3577  wcsncpy(localCompositeName, input->friendlyName, MAX_PATH);
3578  wdmDeviceInfo->muxPosition = (int)m;
3579  wdmDeviceInfo->endpointPinId = input->endpointPinId;
3580  }
3581 
3582  {
3583  /* Get base length */
3584  size_t n = wcslen(localCompositeName);
3585 
3586  /* Check if there are more entries with same name (which might very well be the case), if there
3587  are, the name will be postfixed with an index. */
3588  nameIndex = GetNameIndex(&nameHash, localCompositeName, isInput);
3589  if (nameIndex > 0)
3590  {
3591  /* This name has multiple instances, so we post fix with a number */
3592  n += _snwprintf(localCompositeName + n, MAX_PATH - n, L" %u", nameIndex);
3593  }
3594  /* Postfix with filter name */
3595  _snwprintf(localCompositeName + n, MAX_PATH - n, L" (%s)", pFilter->friendlyName);
3596  }
3597 
3598  /* Convert wide char string to utf-8 */
3599  WideCharToMultiByte(CP_UTF8, 0, localCompositeName, -1, wdmDeviceInfo->compositeName, MAX_PATH, NULL, NULL);
3600 
3601  /* NB! WDM/KS has no concept of a full-duplex device, each pin is either an input or an output */
3602  if (isInput)
3603  {
3604  /* INPUT ! */
3605  deviceInfo->maxInputChannels = pin->maxChannels;
3606  deviceInfo->maxOutputChannels = 0;
3607 
3608  /* RoBi NB: Due to the fact that input audio endpoints in Vista (& later OSs) can be the same device, but with
3609  different input mux settings, there might be a discrepancy between the default input device chosen, and
3610  that which will be used by Portaudio. Not much to do about that unfortunately.
3611  */
3612  if ((defaultInDevPath == 0 || devIsDefaultIn) &&
3613  outArgument->defaultInputDevice == paNoDevice)
3614  {
3615  outArgument->defaultInputDevice = idxDevice;
3616  }
3617  }
3618  else
3619  {
3620  /* OUTPUT ! */
3621  deviceInfo->maxInputChannels = 0;
3622  deviceInfo->maxOutputChannels = pin->maxChannels;
3623 
3624  if ((defaultOutDevPath == 0 || devIsDefaultOut) &&
3625  outArgument->defaultOutputDevice == paNoDevice)
3626  {
3627  outArgument->defaultOutputDevice = idxDevice;
3628  }
3629  }
3630 
3631  /* These low values are not very useful because
3632  * a) The lowest latency we end up with can depend on many factors such
3633  * as the device buffer sizes/granularities, sample rate, channels and format
3634  * b) We cannot know the device buffer sizes until we try to open/use it at
3635  * a particular setting
3636  * So: we give 512x48000Hz frames as the default low input latency
3637  **/
3638  switch (pFilter->devInfo.streamingType)
3639  {
3640  case Type_kWaveCyclic:
3641  if (IsEarlierThanVista())
3642  {
3643  /* XP doesn't tolerate low latency, unless the Process Priority Class is set to REALTIME_PRIORITY_CLASS
3644  through SetPriorityClass, then 10 ms is quite feasible. However, one should then bear in mind that ALL of
3645  the process is running in REALTIME_PRIORITY_CLASS, which might not be appropriate for an application with
3646  a GUI . In this case it is advisable to separate the audio engine in another process and use IPC to communicate
3647  with it. */
3648  deviceInfo->defaultLowInputLatency = 0.02;
3649  deviceInfo->defaultLowOutputLatency = 0.02;
3650  }
3651  else
3652  {
3653  /* This is a conservative estimate. Most WaveCyclic drivers will limit the available latency, but f.i. my Edirol
3654  PCR-A30 can reach 3 ms latency easily... */
3655  deviceInfo->defaultLowInputLatency = 0.01;
3656  deviceInfo->defaultLowOutputLatency = 0.01;
3657  }
3658  deviceInfo->defaultHighInputLatency = (4096.0/48000.0);
3659  deviceInfo->defaultHighOutputLatency = (4096.0/48000.0);
3660  deviceInfo->defaultSampleRate = (double)(pin->defaultSampleRate);
3661  break;
3662  case Type_kWaveRT:
3663  /* This is also a conservative estimate, based on WaveRT polled mode. In polled mode, the latency will be dictated
3664  by the buffer size given by the driver. */
3665  deviceInfo->defaultLowInputLatency = 0.01;
3666  deviceInfo->defaultLowOutputLatency = 0.01;
3667  deviceInfo->defaultHighInputLatency = 0.04;
3668  deviceInfo->defaultHighOutputLatency = 0.04;
3669  deviceInfo->defaultSampleRate = (double)(pin->defaultSampleRate);
3670  break;
3671  default:
3672  assert(0);
3673  break;
3674  }
3675 
3676  /* Add reference to filter */
3677  FilterAddRef(wdmDeviceInfo->filter);
3678 
3679  assert(idxDevice < totalDeviceCount);
3680  ++idxDevice;
3681  }
3682  }
3683 
3684  /* If no one has add ref'd the filter, drop it */
3685  if (pFilter->filterRefCount == 0)
3686  {
3687  FilterFree(pFilter);
3688  }
3689 
3690  /* Deinitialize name hash object */
3691  DeinitNameHashObject(&nameHash);
3692  }
3693  }
3694 
3695  *scanResults = outArgument;
3696  *newDeviceCount = idxDevice;
3697  return result;
3698 
3699 error:
3700  result = DisposeDeviceInfos(hostApi, outArgument, totalDeviceCount);
3701 
3702  return result;
3703 }
3704 
3705 static PaError CommitDeviceInfos( struct PaUtilHostApiRepresentation *hostApi, PaHostApiIndex index, void *scanResults, int deviceCount )
3706 {
3707  PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation *wdmHostApi = (PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation*)hostApi;
3708 
3709  hostApi->info.deviceCount = 0;
3710  hostApi->info.defaultInputDevice = paNoDevice;
3711  hostApi->info.defaultOutputDevice = paNoDevice;
3712 
3713  /* Free any old memory which might be in the device info */
3714  if( hostApi->deviceInfos )
3715  {
3716  PaWinWDMScanDeviceInfosResults* localScanResults = (PaWinWDMScanDeviceInfosResults*)PaUtil_GroupAllocateMemory(
3717  wdmHostApi->allocations, sizeof(PaWinWDMScanDeviceInfosResults));
3718  localScanResults->deviceInfos = hostApi->deviceInfos;
3719 
3720  DisposeDeviceInfos(hostApi, &localScanResults, hostApi->info.deviceCount);
3721 
3722  hostApi->deviceInfos = NULL;
3723  }
3724 
3725  if( scanResults != NULL )
3726  {
3727  PaWinWDMScanDeviceInfosResults *scanDeviceInfosResults = ( PaWinWDMScanDeviceInfosResults * ) scanResults;
3728 
3729  if( deviceCount > 0 )
3730  {
3731  /* use the array allocated in ScanDeviceInfos() as our deviceInfos */
3732  hostApi->deviceInfos = scanDeviceInfosResults->deviceInfos;
3733 
3734  hostApi->info.defaultInputDevice = scanDeviceInfosResults->defaultInputDevice;
3735  hostApi->info.defaultOutputDevice = scanDeviceInfosResults->defaultOutputDevice;
3736 
3737  hostApi->info.deviceCount = deviceCount;
3738  }
3739 
3740  PaUtil_GroupFreeMemory( wdmHostApi->allocations, scanDeviceInfosResults );
3741  }
3742 
3743  return paNoError;
3744 
3745 }
3746 
3747 static PaError DisposeDeviceInfos( struct PaUtilHostApiRepresentation *hostApi, void *scanResults, int deviceCount )
3748 {
3749  PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation *winDsHostApi = (PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation*)hostApi;
3750 
3751  if( scanResults != NULL )
3752  {
3753  PaWinWDMScanDeviceInfosResults *scanDeviceInfosResults = ( PaWinWDMScanDeviceInfosResults * ) scanResults;
3754 
3755  if( scanDeviceInfosResults->deviceInfos )
3756  {
3757  int i;
3758  for (i = 0; i < deviceCount; ++i)
3759  {
3760  PaWinWdmDeviceInfo* pDevice = (PaWinWdmDeviceInfo*)scanDeviceInfosResults->deviceInfos[i];
3761  if (pDevice->filter != 0)
3762  {
3763  FilterFree(pDevice->filter);
3764  }
3765  }
3766 
3767  PaUtil_GroupFreeMemory( winDsHostApi->allocations, scanDeviceInfosResults->deviceInfos[0] ); /* all device info structs are allocated in a block so we can destroy them here */
3768  PaUtil_GroupFreeMemory( winDsHostApi->allocations, scanDeviceInfosResults->deviceInfos );
3769  }
3770 
3771  PaUtil_GroupFreeMemory( winDsHostApi->allocations, scanDeviceInfosResults );
3772  }
3773 
3774  return paNoError;
3775 
3776 }
3777 
3778 PaError PaWinWdm_Initialize( PaUtilHostApiRepresentation **hostApi, PaHostApiIndex hostApiIndex )
3779 {
3780  PaError result = paNoError;
3781  int deviceCount = 0;
3782  void *scanResults = 0;
3783  PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation *wdmHostApi = NULL;
3784 
3785  PA_LOGE_;
3786 
3787 #ifdef PA_WDMKS_SET_TREF
3788  tRef = PaUtil_GetTime();
3789 #endif
3790 
3791  /*
3792  Attempt to load the KSUSER.DLL without which we cannot create pins
3793  We will unload this on termination
3794  */
3795  if(DllKsUser == NULL)
3796  {
3797  DllKsUser = LoadLibrary(TEXT("ksuser.dll"));
3798  if(DllKsUser == NULL)
3799  goto error;
3800  }
3801  FunctionKsCreatePin = (KSCREATEPIN*)GetProcAddress(DllKsUser, "KsCreatePin");
3802  if(FunctionKsCreatePin == NULL)
3803  goto error;
3804 
3805  /* Attempt to load AVRT.DLL, if we can't, then we'll just use time critical prio instead... */
3806  if(paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.hInstance == NULL)
3807  {
3808  paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.hInstance = LoadLibrary(TEXT("avrt.dll"));
3809  if (paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.hInstance != NULL)
3810  {
3811  paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.AvSetMmThreadCharacteristics =
3812  (HANDLE(WINAPI*)(LPCSTR,LPDWORD))GetProcAddress(paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.hInstance,"AvSetMmThreadCharacteristicsA");
3813  paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.AvRevertMmThreadCharacteristics =
3814  (BOOL(WINAPI*)(HANDLE))GetProcAddress(paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.hInstance, "AvRevertMmThreadCharacteristics");
3815  paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.AvSetMmThreadPriority =
3816  (BOOL(WINAPI*)(HANDLE,PA_AVRT_PRIORITY))GetProcAddress(paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.hInstance, "AvSetMmThreadPriority");
3817  }
3818  }
3819 
3820  wdmHostApi = (PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation*)PaUtil_AllocateMemory( sizeof(PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation) );
3821  if( !wdmHostApi )
3822  {
3823  result = paInsufficientMemory;
3824  goto error;
3825  }
3826 
3827  wdmHostApi->allocations = PaUtil_CreateAllocationGroup();
3828  if( !wdmHostApi->allocations )
3829  {
3830  result = paInsufficientMemory;
3831  goto error;
3832  }
3833 
3834  *hostApi = &wdmHostApi->inheritedHostApiRep;
3835  (*hostApi)->info.structVersion = 1;
3836  (*hostApi)->info.type = paWDMKS;
3837  (*hostApi)->info.name = "Windows WDM-KS";
3838 
3839  /* these are all updated by CommitDeviceInfos() */
3840  (*hostApi)->info.deviceCount = 0;
3841  (*hostApi)->info.defaultInputDevice = paNoDevice;
3842  (*hostApi)->info.defaultOutputDevice = paNoDevice;
3843  (*hostApi)->deviceInfos = 0;
3844 
3845  result = ScanDeviceInfos(&wdmHostApi->inheritedHostApiRep, hostApiIndex, &scanResults, &deviceCount);
3846  if (result != paNoError)
3847  {
3848  goto error;
3849  }
3850 
3851  CommitDeviceInfos(&wdmHostApi->inheritedHostApiRep, hostApiIndex, scanResults, deviceCount);
3852 
3853  (*hostApi)->Terminate = Terminate;
3854  (*hostApi)->OpenStream = OpenStream;
3855  (*hostApi)->IsFormatSupported = IsFormatSupported;
3856  /* In preparation for hotplug
3857  (*hostApi)->ScanDeviceInfos = ScanDeviceInfos;
3858  (*hostApi)->CommitDeviceInfos = CommitDeviceInfos;
3859  (*hostApi)->DisposeDeviceInfos = DisposeDeviceInfos;
3860  */
3861  PaUtil_InitializeStreamInterface( &wdmHostApi->callbackStreamInterface, CloseStream, StartStream,
3862  StopStream, AbortStream, IsStreamStopped, IsStreamActive,
3863  GetStreamTime, GetStreamCpuLoad,
3864  PaUtil_DummyRead, PaUtil_DummyWrite,
3865  PaUtil_DummyGetReadAvailable, PaUtil_DummyGetWriteAvailable );
3866 
3867  PaUtil_InitializeStreamInterface( &wdmHostApi->blockingStreamInterface, CloseStream, StartStream,
3868  StopStream, AbortStream, IsStreamStopped, IsStreamActive,
3869  GetStreamTime, PaUtil_DummyGetCpuLoad,
3870  ReadStream, WriteStream, GetStreamReadAvailable, GetStreamWriteAvailable );
3871 
3872  PA_LOGL_;
3873  return result;
3874 
3875 error:
3876  Terminate( (PaUtilHostApiRepresentation*)wdmHostApi );
3877 
3878  PA_LOGL_;
3879  return result;
3880 }
3881 
3882 
3883 static void Terminate( struct PaUtilHostApiRepresentation *hostApi )
3884 {
3885  PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation *wdmHostApi = (PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation*)hostApi;
3886  PA_LOGE_;
3887 
3888  /* Do not unload the libraries */
3889  if( DllKsUser != NULL )
3890  {
3891  FreeLibrary( DllKsUser );
3892  DllKsUser = NULL;
3893  }
3894 
3895  if( paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.hInstance != NULL )
3896  {
3897  FreeLibrary( paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.hInstance );
3898  paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.hInstance = NULL;
3899  }
3900 
3901  if( wdmHostApi)
3902  {
3903  PaWinWDMScanDeviceInfosResults* localScanResults = (PaWinWDMScanDeviceInfosResults*)PaUtil_GroupAllocateMemory(
3904  wdmHostApi->allocations, sizeof(PaWinWDMScanDeviceInfosResults));
3905  localScanResults->deviceInfos = hostApi->deviceInfos;
3906  DisposeDeviceInfos(hostApi, localScanResults, hostApi->info.deviceCount);
3907 
3908  if( wdmHostApi->allocations )
3909  {
3910  PaUtil_FreeAllAllocations( wdmHostApi->allocations );
3911  PaUtil_DestroyAllocationGroup( wdmHostApi->allocations );
3912  }
3913  PaUtil_FreeMemory( wdmHostApi );
3914  }
3915  PA_LOGL_;
3916 }
3917 
3918 static PaError IsFormatSupported( struct PaUtilHostApiRepresentation *hostApi,
3919  const PaStreamParameters *inputParameters,
3920  const PaStreamParameters *outputParameters,
3921  double sampleRate )
3922 {
3923  int inputChannelCount, outputChannelCount;
3924  PaSampleFormat inputSampleFormat, outputSampleFormat;
3925  PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation *wdmHostApi = (PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation*)hostApi;
3926  PaWinWdmFilter* pFilter;
3927  int result = paFormatIsSupported;
3928  WAVEFORMATEXTENSIBLE wfx;
3929  PaWinWaveFormatChannelMask channelMask;
3930 
3931  PA_LOGE_;
3932 
3933  if( inputParameters )
3934  {
3935  PaWinWdmDeviceInfo* pDeviceInfo = (PaWinWdmDeviceInfo*)wdmHostApi->inheritedHostApiRep.deviceInfos[inputParameters->device];
3936  PaWinWdmPin* pin;
3937  unsigned fmt;
3938  unsigned long testFormat = 0;
3939  unsigned validBits = 0;
3940 
3941  inputChannelCount = inputParameters->channelCount;
3942  inputSampleFormat = inputParameters->sampleFormat;
3943 
3944  /* all standard sample formats are supported by the buffer adapter,
3945  this implementation doesn't support any custom sample formats */
3946  if( inputSampleFormat & paCustomFormat )
3947  {
3948  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paSampleFormatNotSupported, "IsFormatSupported: Custom input format not supported");
3949  return paSampleFormatNotSupported;
3950  }
3951 
3952  /* unless alternate device specification is supported, reject the use of
3953  paUseHostApiSpecificDeviceSpecification */
3954 
3955  if( inputParameters->device == paUseHostApiSpecificDeviceSpecification )
3956  {
3957  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paInvalidDevice, "IsFormatSupported: paUseHostApiSpecificDeviceSpecification not supported");
3958  return paInvalidDevice;
3959  }
3960 
3961  /* check that input device can support inputChannelCount */
3962  if( inputChannelCount > hostApi->deviceInfos[ inputParameters->device ]->maxInputChannels )
3963  {
3964  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paInvalidChannelCount, "IsFormatSupported: Invalid input channel count");
3965  return paInvalidChannelCount;
3966  }
3967 
3968  /* validate inputStreamInfo */
3969  if( inputParameters->hostApiSpecificStreamInfo )
3970  {
3971  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paIncompatibleHostApiSpecificStreamInfo, "Host API stream info not supported");
3972  return paIncompatibleHostApiSpecificStreamInfo; /* this implementation doesn't use custom stream info */
3973  }
3974 
3975  pFilter = pDeviceInfo->filter;
3976  pin = pFilter->pins[pDeviceInfo->pin];
3977 
3978  /* Find out the testing format */
3979  for (fmt = paFloat32; fmt <= paUInt8; fmt <<= 1)
3980  {
3981  if ((fmt & pin->formats) != 0)
3982  {
3983  /* Found a matching format! */
3984  testFormat = fmt;
3985  break;
3986  }
3987  }
3988  if (testFormat == 0)
3989  {
3990  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "IsFormatSupported(capture) failed: no testformat found!");
3991  return paUnanticipatedHostError;
3992  }
3993 
3994  /* Due to special considerations, WaveRT devices with paInt24 should be tested with paInt32 and
3995  valid bits = 24 (instead of 24 bit samples) */
3996  if (pFilter->devInfo.streamingType == Type_kWaveRT && testFormat == paInt24)
3997  {
3998  PA_DEBUG(("IsFormatSupported (capture): WaveRT overriding testFormat paInt24 with paInt32 (24 valid bits)"));
3999  testFormat = paInt32;
4000  validBits = 24;
4001  }
4002 
4003  /* Check that the input format is supported */
4004  channelMask = PaWin_DefaultChannelMask(inputChannelCount);
4005  PaWin_InitializeWaveFormatExtensible((PaWinWaveFormat*)&wfx,
4006  inputChannelCount,
4007  testFormat,
4008  PaWin_SampleFormatToLinearWaveFormatTag(testFormat),
4009  sampleRate,
4010  channelMask );
4011  if (validBits != 0)
4012  {
4013  wfx.Samples.wValidBitsPerSample = validBits;
4014  }
4015 
4016  result = PinIsFormatSupported(pin, (const WAVEFORMATEX*)&wfx);
4017  if( result != paNoError )
4018  {
4019  /* Try a WAVE_FORMAT_PCM instead */
4020  PaWin_InitializeWaveFormatEx((PaWinWaveFormat*)&wfx,
4021  inputChannelCount,
4022  testFormat,
4023  PaWin_SampleFormatToLinearWaveFormatTag(testFormat),
4024  sampleRate);
4025 
4026  if (validBits != 0)
4027  {
4028  wfx.Samples.wValidBitsPerSample = validBits;
4029  }
4030 
4031  result = PinIsFormatSupported(pin, (const WAVEFORMATEX*)&wfx);
4032  if( result != paNoError )
4033  {
4034  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "IsFormatSupported(capture) failed: sr=%u,ch=%u,bits=%u", wfx.Format.nSamplesPerSec, wfx.Format.nChannels, wfx.Format.wBitsPerSample);
4035  return result;
4036  }
4037  }
4038  }
4039  else
4040  {
4041  inputChannelCount = 0;
4042  }
4043 
4044  if( outputParameters )
4045  {
4046  PaWinWdmDeviceInfo* pDeviceInfo = (PaWinWdmDeviceInfo*)wdmHostApi->inheritedHostApiRep.deviceInfos[outputParameters->device];
4047  PaWinWdmPin* pin;
4048  unsigned fmt;
4049  unsigned long testFormat = 0;
4050  unsigned validBits = 0;
4051 
4052  outputChannelCount = outputParameters->channelCount;
4053  outputSampleFormat = outputParameters->sampleFormat;
4054 
4055  /* all standard sample formats are supported by the buffer adapter,
4056  this implementation doesn't support any custom sample formats */
4057  if( outputSampleFormat & paCustomFormat )
4058  {
4059  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paSampleFormatNotSupported, "IsFormatSupported: Custom output format not supported");
4060  return paSampleFormatNotSupported;
4061  }
4062 
4063  /* unless alternate device specification is supported, reject the use of
4064  paUseHostApiSpecificDeviceSpecification */
4065 
4066  if( outputParameters->device == paUseHostApiSpecificDeviceSpecification )
4067  {
4068  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paInvalidDevice, "IsFormatSupported: paUseHostApiSpecificDeviceSpecification not supported");
4069  return paInvalidDevice;
4070  }
4071 
4072  /* check that output device can support outputChannelCount */
4073  if( outputChannelCount > hostApi->deviceInfos[ outputParameters->device ]->maxOutputChannels )
4074  {
4075  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paInvalidChannelCount, "Invalid output channel count");
4076  return paInvalidChannelCount;
4077  }
4078 
4079  /* validate outputStreamInfo */
4080  if( outputParameters->hostApiSpecificStreamInfo )
4081  {
4082  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paIncompatibleHostApiSpecificStreamInfo, "Host API stream info not supported");
4083  return paIncompatibleHostApiSpecificStreamInfo; /* this implementation doesn't use custom stream info */
4084  }
4085 
4086  pFilter = pDeviceInfo->filter;
4087  pin = pFilter->pins[pDeviceInfo->pin];
4088 
4089  /* Find out the testing format */
4090  for (fmt = paFloat32; fmt <= paUInt8; fmt <<= 1)
4091  {
4092  if ((fmt & pin->formats) != 0)
4093  {
4094  /* Found a matching format! */
4095  testFormat = fmt;
4096  break;
4097  }
4098  }
4099  if (testFormat == 0)
4100  {
4101  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "IsFormatSupported(render) failed: no testformat found!");
4102  return paUnanticipatedHostError;
4103  }
4104 
4105  /* Due to special considerations, WaveRT devices with paInt24 should be tested with paInt32 and
4106  valid bits = 24 (instead of 24 bit samples) */
4107  if (pFilter->devInfo.streamingType == Type_kWaveRT && testFormat == paInt24)
4108  {
4109  PA_DEBUG(("IsFormatSupported (render): WaveRT overriding testFormat paInt24 with paInt32 (24 valid bits)"));
4110  testFormat = paInt32;
4111  validBits = 24;
4112  }
4113 
4114  /* Check that the output format is supported */
4115  channelMask = PaWin_DefaultChannelMask(outputChannelCount);
4116  PaWin_InitializeWaveFormatExtensible((PaWinWaveFormat*)&wfx,
4117  outputChannelCount,
4118  testFormat,
4119  PaWin_SampleFormatToLinearWaveFormatTag(testFormat),
4120  sampleRate,
4121  channelMask );
4122 
4123  if (validBits != 0)
4124  {
4125  wfx.Samples.wValidBitsPerSample = validBits;
4126  }
4127 
4128  result = PinIsFormatSupported(pin, (const WAVEFORMATEX*)&wfx);
4129  if( result != paNoError )
4130  {
4131  /* Try a WAVE_FORMAT_PCM instead */
4132  PaWin_InitializeWaveFormatEx((PaWinWaveFormat*)&wfx,
4133  outputChannelCount,
4134  testFormat,
4135  PaWin_SampleFormatToLinearWaveFormatTag(testFormat),
4136  sampleRate);
4137 
4138  if (validBits != 0)
4139  {
4140  wfx.Samples.wValidBitsPerSample = validBits;
4141  }
4142 
4143  result = PinIsFormatSupported(pin, (const WAVEFORMATEX*)&wfx);
4144  if( result != paNoError )
4145  {
4146  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "IsFormatSupported(render) failed: %u,%u,%u", wfx.Format.nSamplesPerSec, wfx.Format.nChannels, wfx.Format.wBitsPerSample);
4147  return result;
4148  }
4149  }
4150 
4151  }
4152  else
4153  {
4154  outputChannelCount = 0;
4155  }
4156 
4157  /*
4158  IMPLEMENT ME:
4159 
4160  - if a full duplex stream is requested, check that the combination
4161  of input and output parameters is supported if necessary
4162 
4163  - check that the device supports sampleRate
4164 
4165  Because the buffer adapter handles conversion between all standard
4166  sample formats, the following checks are only required if paCustomFormat
4167  is implemented, or under some other unusual conditions.
4168 
4169  - check that input device can support inputSampleFormat, or that
4170  we have the capability to convert from inputSampleFormat to
4171  a native format
4172 
4173  - check that output device can support outputSampleFormat, or that
4174  we have the capability to convert from outputSampleFormat to
4175  a native format
4176  */
4177  if((inputChannelCount == 0)&&(outputChannelCount == 0))
4178  {
4179  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paSampleFormatNotSupported, "No input or output channels defined");
4180  result = paSampleFormatNotSupported; /* Not right error */
4181  }
4182 
4183  PA_LOGL_;
4184  return result;
4185 }
4186 
4187 static void ResetStreamEvents(PaWinWdmStream* stream)
4188 {
4189  unsigned i;
4190  ResetEvent(stream->eventAbort);
4191  ResetEvent(stream->eventStreamStart[StreamStart_kOk]);
4192  ResetEvent(stream->eventStreamStart[StreamStart_kFailed]);
4193 
4194  for (i=0; i<stream->capture.noOfPackets; ++i)
4195  {
4196  if (stream->capture.events && stream->capture.events[i])
4197  {
4198  ResetEvent(stream->capture.events[i]);
4199  }
4200  }
4201 
4202  for (i=0; i<stream->render.noOfPackets; ++i)
4203  {
4204  if (stream->render.events && stream->render.events[i])
4205  {
4206  ResetEvent(stream->render.events[i]);
4207  }
4208  }
4209 }
4210 
4211 static void CloseStreamEvents(PaWinWdmStream* stream)
4212 {
4213  unsigned i;
4214  PaWinWdmIOInfo* ios[2] = { &stream->capture, &stream->render };
4215 
4216  if (stream->eventAbort)
4217  {
4218  CloseHandle(stream->eventAbort);
4219  stream->eventAbort = 0;
4220  }
4221  if (stream->eventStreamStart[StreamStart_kOk])
4222  {
4223  CloseHandle(stream->eventStreamStart[StreamStart_kOk]);
4224  }
4225  if (stream->eventStreamStart[StreamStart_kFailed])
4226  {
4227  CloseHandle(stream->eventStreamStart[StreamStart_kFailed]);
4228  }
4229 
4230  for (i = 0; i < 2; ++i)
4231  {
4232  unsigned j;
4233  /* Unregister notification handles for WaveRT */
4234  if (ios[i]->pPin && ios[i]->pPin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType == Type_kWaveRT &&
4235  ios[i]->pPin->pinKsSubType == SubType_kNotification &&
4236  ios[i]->events != 0)
4237  {
4238  PinUnregisterNotificationHandle(ios[i]->pPin, ios[i]->events[0]);
4239  }
4240 
4241  for (j=0; j < ios[i]->noOfPackets; ++j)
4242  {
4243  if (ios[i]->events && ios[i]->events[j])
4244  {
4245  CloseHandle(ios[i]->events[j]);
4246  ios[i]->events[j] = 0;
4247  }
4248  }
4249  }
4250 }
4251 
4252 static unsigned NextPowerOf2(unsigned val)
4253 {
4254  val--;
4255  val = (val >> 1) | val;
4256  val = (val >> 2) | val;
4257  val = (val >> 4) | val;
4258  val = (val >> 8) | val;
4259  val = (val >> 16) | val;
4260  return ++val;
4261 }
4262 
4263 static PaError ValidateSpecificStreamParameters(
4264  const PaStreamParameters *streamParameters,
4265  const PaWinWDMKSInfo *streamInfo,
4266  unsigned isInput)
4267 {
4268  if( streamInfo )
4269  {
4270  if( streamInfo->size != sizeof( PaWinWDMKSInfo )
4271  || streamInfo->version != 1 )
4272  {
4273  PA_DEBUG(("Stream parameters: size or version not correct"));
4274  return paIncompatibleHostApiSpecificStreamInfo;
4275  }
4276 
4277  if (!!(streamInfo->flags & ~(paWinWDMKSOverrideFramesize | paWinWDMKSUseGivenChannelMask)))
4278  {
4279  PA_DEBUG(("Stream parameters: non supported flags set"));
4280  return paIncompatibleHostApiSpecificStreamInfo;
4281  }
4282 
4283  if (streamInfo->noOfPackets != 0 &&
4284  (streamInfo->noOfPackets < 2 || streamInfo->noOfPackets > 8))
4285  {
4286  PA_DEBUG(("Stream parameters: noOfPackets %u out of range [2,8]", streamInfo->noOfPackets));
4287  return paIncompatibleHostApiSpecificStreamInfo;
4288  }
4289 
4290  if (streamInfo->flags & paWinWDMKSUseGivenChannelMask)
4291  {
4292  if (isInput)
4293  {
4294  PA_DEBUG(("Stream parameters: Channels mask setting not supported for input stream"));
4295  return paIncompatibleHostApiSpecificStreamInfo;
4296  }
4297 
4298  if (streamInfo->channelMask & PAWIN_SPEAKER_RESERVED)
4299  {
4300  PA_DEBUG(("Stream parameters: Given channels mask 0x%08X not supported", streamInfo->channelMask));
4301  return paIncompatibleHostApiSpecificStreamInfo;
4302  }
4303  }
4304 
4305  }
4306 
4307  return paNoError;
4308 }

4312 
4313 /* see pa_hostapi.h for a list of validity guarantees made about OpenStream parameters */
4314 
4315 static PaError OpenStream( struct PaUtilHostApiRepresentation *hostApi,
4316  PaStream** s,
4317  const PaStreamParameters *inputParameters,
4318  const PaStreamParameters *outputParameters,
4319  double sampleRate,
4320  unsigned long framesPerUserBuffer,
4321  PaStreamFlags streamFlags,
4322  PaStreamCallback *streamCallback,
4323  void *userData )
4324 {
4325  PaError result = paNoError;
4326  PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation *wdmHostApi = (PaWinWdmHostApiRepresentation*)hostApi;
4327  PaWinWdmStream *stream = 0;
4328  /* unsigned long framesPerHostBuffer; these may not be equivalent for all implementations */
4329  PaSampleFormat inputSampleFormat, outputSampleFormat;
4330  PaSampleFormat hostInputSampleFormat, hostOutputSampleFormat;
4331  int userInputChannels,userOutputChannels;
4332  WAVEFORMATEXTENSIBLE wfx;
4333 
4334  PA_LOGE_;
4335  PA_DEBUG(("OpenStream:sampleRate = %f\n",sampleRate));
4336  PA_DEBUG(("OpenStream:framesPerBuffer = %lu\n",framesPerUserBuffer));
4337 
4338  if( inputParameters )
4339  {
4340  userInputChannels = inputParameters->channelCount;
4341  inputSampleFormat = inputParameters->sampleFormat;
4342 
4343  /* unless alternate device specification is supported, reject the use of
4344  paUseHostApiSpecificDeviceSpecification */
4345 
4346  if( inputParameters->device == paUseHostApiSpecificDeviceSpecification )
4347  {
4348  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paInvalidDevice, "paUseHostApiSpecificDeviceSpecification(in) not supported");
4349  return paInvalidDevice;
4350  }
4351 
4352  /* check that input device can support stream->userInputChannels */
4353  if( userInputChannels > hostApi->deviceInfos[ inputParameters->device ]->maxInputChannels )
4354  {
4355  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paInvalidChannelCount, "Invalid input channel count");
4356  return paInvalidChannelCount;
4357  }
4358 
4359  /* validate inputStreamInfo */
4360  result = ValidateSpecificStreamParameters(inputParameters, inputParameters->hostApiSpecificStreamInfo, 1 );
4361  if(result != paNoError)
4362  {
4363  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "Host API stream info not supported (in)");
4364  return result; /* this implementation doesn't use custom stream info */
4365  }
4366  }
4367  else
4368  {
4369  userInputChannels = 0;
4370  inputSampleFormat = hostInputSampleFormat = paInt16; /* Supress 'uninitialised var' warnings. */
4371  }
4372 
4373  if( outputParameters )
4374  {
4375  userOutputChannels = outputParameters->channelCount;
4376  outputSampleFormat = outputParameters->sampleFormat;
4377 
4378  /* unless alternate device specification is supported, reject the use of
4379  paUseHostApiSpecificDeviceSpecification */
4380 
4381  if( outputParameters->device == paUseHostApiSpecificDeviceSpecification )
4382  {
4383  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paInvalidDevice, "paUseHostApiSpecificDeviceSpecification(out) not supported");
4384  return paInvalidDevice;
4385  }
4386 
4387  /* check that output device can support stream->userInputChannels */
4388  if( userOutputChannels > hostApi->deviceInfos[ outputParameters->device ]->maxOutputChannels )
4389  {
4390  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paInvalidChannelCount, "Invalid output channel count");
4391  return paInvalidChannelCount;
4392  }
4393 
4394  /* validate outputStreamInfo */
4395  result = ValidateSpecificStreamParameters( outputParameters, outputParameters->hostApiSpecificStreamInfo, 0 );
4396  if (result != paNoError)
4397  {
4398  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "Host API stream info not supported (out)");
4399  return result; /* this implementation doesn't use custom stream info */
4400  }
4401  }
4402  else
4403  {
4404  userOutputChannels = 0;
4405  outputSampleFormat = hostOutputSampleFormat = paInt16; /* Supress 'uninitialized var' warnings. */
4406  }
4407 
4408  /* validate platform specific flags */
4409  if( (streamFlags & paPlatformSpecificFlags) != 0 )
4410  {
4411  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paInvalidFlag, "Invalid flag supplied");
4412  return paInvalidFlag; /* unexpected platform specific flag */
4413  }
4414 
4415  stream = (PaWinWdmStream*)PaUtil_AllocateMemory( sizeof(PaWinWdmStream) );
4416  if( !stream )
4417  {
4418  result = paInsufficientMemory;
4419  goto error;
4420  }
4421 
4422  /* Create allocation group */
4423  stream->allocGroup = PaUtil_CreateAllocationGroup();
4424  if( !stream->allocGroup )
4425  {
4426  result = paInsufficientMemory;
4427  goto error;
4428  }
4429 
4430  /* Zero the stream object */
4431  /* memset((void*)stream,0,sizeof(PaWinWdmStream)); */
4432 
4433  if( streamCallback )
4434  {
4435  PaUtil_InitializeStreamRepresentation( &stream->streamRepresentation,
4436  &wdmHostApi->callbackStreamInterface, streamCallback, userData );
4437  }
4438  else
4439  {
4440  /* PaUtil_InitializeStreamRepresentation( &stream->streamRepresentation,
4441  &wdmHostApi->blockingStreamInterface, streamCallback, userData ); */
4442 
4443  /* We don't support the blocking API yet */
4444  PA_DEBUG(("Blocking API not supported yet!\n"));
4445  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paUnanticipatedHostError, "Blocking API not supported yet");
4446  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
4447  goto error;
4448  }
4449 
4450  PaUtil_InitializeCpuLoadMeasurer( &stream->cpuLoadMeasurer, sampleRate );
4451 
4452  /* Instantiate the input pin if necessary */
4453  if(userInputChannels > 0)
4454  {
4455  PaWinWdmFilter* pFilter;
4456  PaWinWdmDeviceInfo* pDeviceInfo;
4457  PaWinWdmPin* pPin;
4458  unsigned validBitsPerSample = 0;
4459  PaWinWaveFormatChannelMask channelMask = PaWin_DefaultChannelMask( userInputChannels );
4460 
4461  result = paSampleFormatNotSupported;
4462  pDeviceInfo = (PaWinWdmDeviceInfo*)wdmHostApi->inheritedHostApiRep.deviceInfos[inputParameters->device];
4463  pFilter = pDeviceInfo->filter;
4464  pPin = pFilter->pins[pDeviceInfo->pin];
4465 
4466  stream->userInputChannels = userInputChannels;
4467 
4468  hostInputSampleFormat = PaUtil_SelectClosestAvailableFormat( pPin->formats, inputSampleFormat );
4469  if (hostInputSampleFormat == paSampleFormatNotSupported)
4470  {
4471  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
4472  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "PU_SCAF(%X,%X) failed (input)", pPin->formats, inputSampleFormat);
4473  goto error;
4474  }
4475  else if (pFilter->devInfo.streamingType == Type_kWaveRT && hostInputSampleFormat == paInt24)
4476  {
4477  /* For WaveRT, we choose 32 bit format instead of paInt24, since we MIGHT need to align buffer on a
4478  128 byte boundary (see PinGetBuffer) */
4479  hostInputSampleFormat = paInt32;
4480  /* But we'll tell the driver that it's 24 bit in 32 bit container */
4481  validBitsPerSample = 24;
4482  }
4483 
4484  while (hostInputSampleFormat <= paUInt8)
4485  {
4486  unsigned channelsToProbe = stream->userInputChannels;
4487  /* Some or all KS devices can only handle the exact number of channels
4488  * they specify. But PortAudio clients expect to be able to
4489  * at least specify mono I/O on a multi-channel device
4490  * If this is the case, then we will do the channel mapping internally
4491  * The following loop tests this case
4492  **/
4493  while (1)
4494  {
4495  PaWin_InitializeWaveFormatExtensible((PaWinWaveFormat*)&wfx,
4496  channelsToProbe,
4497  hostInputSampleFormat,
4498  PaWin_SampleFormatToLinearWaveFormatTag(hostInputSampleFormat),
4499  sampleRate,
4500  channelMask );
4501  stream->capture.bytesPerFrame = wfx.Format.nBlockAlign;
4502  if (validBitsPerSample != 0)
4503  {
4504  wfx.Samples.wValidBitsPerSample = validBitsPerSample;
4505  }
4506  stream->capture.pPin = FilterCreatePin(pFilter, pPin->pinId, (WAVEFORMATEX*)&wfx, &result);
4507  stream->deviceInputChannels = channelsToProbe;
4508 
4509  if( result != paNoError && result != paDeviceUnavailable )
4510  {
4511  /* Try a WAVE_FORMAT_PCM instead */
4512  PaWin_InitializeWaveFormatEx((PaWinWaveFormat*)&wfx,
4513  channelsToProbe,
4514  hostInputSampleFormat,
4515  PaWin_SampleFormatToLinearWaveFormatTag(hostInputSampleFormat),
4516  sampleRate);
4517  if (validBitsPerSample != 0)
4518  {
4519  wfx.Samples.wValidBitsPerSample = validBitsPerSample;
4520  }
4521  stream->capture.pPin = FilterCreatePin(pFilter, pPin->pinId, (const WAVEFORMATEX*)&wfx, &result);
4522  }
4523 
4524  if (result == paDeviceUnavailable) goto occupied;
4525 
4526  if (result == paNoError)
4527  {
4528  /* We're done */
4529  break;
4530  }
4531 
4532  if (channelsToProbe < (unsigned)pPin->maxChannels)
4533  {
4534  /* Go to next multiple of 2 */
4535  channelsToProbe = min((((channelsToProbe>>1)+1)<<1), (unsigned)pPin->maxChannels);
4536  continue;
4537  }
4538 
4539  break;
4540  }
4541 
4542  if (result == paNoError)
4543  {
4544  /* We're done */
4545  break;
4546  }
4547 
4548  /* Go to next format in line with lower resolution */
4549  hostInputSampleFormat <<= 1;
4550  }
4551 
4552  if(stream->capture.pPin == NULL)
4553  {
4554  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "Failed to create capture pin: sr=%u,ch=%u,bits=%u,align=%u",
4555  wfx.Format.nSamplesPerSec, wfx.Format.nChannels, wfx.Format.wBitsPerSample, wfx.Format.nBlockAlign);
4556  goto error;
4557  }
4558 
4559  /* Select correct mux input on MUX node of topology filter */
4560  if (pDeviceInfo->muxPosition >= 0)
4561  {
4562  assert(pPin->parentFilter->topologyFilter != NULL);
4563 
4564  result = FilterUse(pPin->parentFilter->topologyFilter);
4565  if (result != paNoError)
4566  {
4567  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "Failed to open topology filter");
4568  goto error;
4569  }
4570 
4571  result = WdmSetMuxNodeProperty(pPin->parentFilter->topologyFilter->handle,
4572  pPin->inputs[pDeviceInfo->muxPosition]->muxNodeId,
4573  pPin->inputs[pDeviceInfo->muxPosition]->muxPinId);
4574 
4575  FilterRelease(pPin->parentFilter->topologyFilter);
4576 
4577  if(result != paNoError)
4578  {
4579  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "Failed to set topology mux node");
4580  goto error;
4581  }
4582  }
4583 
4584  stream->capture.bytesPerSample = stream->capture.bytesPerFrame / stream->deviceInputChannels;
4585  stream->capture.pPin->frameSize /= stream->capture.bytesPerFrame;
4586  PA_DEBUG(("Capture pin frames: %d\n",stream->capture.pPin->frameSize));
4587  }
4588  else
4589  {
4590  stream->capture.pPin = NULL;
4591  stream->capture.bytesPerFrame = 0;
4592  }
4593 
4594  /* Instantiate the output pin if necessary */
4595  if(userOutputChannels > 0)
4596  {
4597  PaWinWdmFilter* pFilter;
4598  PaWinWdmDeviceInfo* pDeviceInfo;
4599  PaWinWdmPin* pPin;
4600  PaWinWDMKSInfo* pInfo = (PaWinWDMKSInfo*)(outputParameters->hostApiSpecificStreamInfo);
4601  unsigned validBitsPerSample = 0;
4602  PaWinWaveFormatChannelMask channelMask = PaWin_DefaultChannelMask( userOutputChannels );
4603  if (pInfo && (pInfo->flags & paWinWDMKSUseGivenChannelMask))
4604  {
4605  PA_DEBUG(("Using channelMask 0x%08X instead of default 0x%08X\n",
4606  pInfo->channelMask,
4607  channelMask));
4608  channelMask = pInfo->channelMask;
4609  }
4610 
4611  result = paSampleFormatNotSupported;
4612  pDeviceInfo = (PaWinWdmDeviceInfo*)wdmHostApi->inheritedHostApiRep.deviceInfos[outputParameters->device];
4613  pFilter = pDeviceInfo->filter;
4614  pPin = pFilter->pins[pDeviceInfo->pin];
4615 
4616  stream->userOutputChannels = userOutputChannels;
4617 
4618  hostOutputSampleFormat = PaUtil_SelectClosestAvailableFormat( pPin->formats, outputSampleFormat );
4619  if (hostOutputSampleFormat == paSampleFormatNotSupported)
4620  {
4621  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
4622  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "PU_SCAF(%X,%X) failed (output)", pPin->formats, hostOutputSampleFormat);
4623  goto error;
4624  }
4625  else if (pFilter->devInfo.streamingType == Type_kWaveRT && hostOutputSampleFormat == paInt24)
4626  {
4627  /* For WaveRT, we choose 32 bit format instead of paInt24, since we MIGHT need to align buffer on a
4628  128 byte boundary (see PinGetBuffer) */
4629  hostOutputSampleFormat = paInt32;
4630  /* But we'll tell the driver that it's 24 bit in 32 bit container */
4631  validBitsPerSample = 24;
4632  }
4633 
4634  while (hostOutputSampleFormat <= paUInt8)
4635  {
4636  unsigned channelsToProbe = stream->userOutputChannels;
4637  /* Some or all KS devices can only handle the exact number of channels
4638  * they specify. But PortAudio clients expect to be able to
4639  * at least specify mono I/O on a multi-channel device
4640  * If this is the case, then we will do the channel mapping internally
4641  * The following loop tests this case
4642  **/
4643  while (1)
4644  {
4645  PaWin_InitializeWaveFormatExtensible((PaWinWaveFormat*)&wfx,
4646  channelsToProbe,
4647  hostOutputSampleFormat,
4648  PaWin_SampleFormatToLinearWaveFormatTag(hostOutputSampleFormat),
4649  sampleRate,
4650  channelMask );
4651  stream->render.bytesPerFrame = wfx.Format.nBlockAlign;
4652  if (validBitsPerSample != 0)
4653  {
4654  wfx.Samples.wValidBitsPerSample = validBitsPerSample;
4655  }
4656  stream->render.pPin = FilterCreatePin(pFilter, pPin->pinId, (WAVEFORMATEX*)&wfx, &result);
4657  stream->deviceOutputChannels = channelsToProbe;
4658 
4659  if( result != paNoError && result != paDeviceUnavailable )
4660  {
4661  PaWin_InitializeWaveFormatEx((PaWinWaveFormat*)&wfx,
4662  channelsToProbe,
4663  hostOutputSampleFormat,
4664  PaWin_SampleFormatToLinearWaveFormatTag(hostOutputSampleFormat),
4665  sampleRate);
4666  if (validBitsPerSample != 0)
4667  {
4668  wfx.Samples.wValidBitsPerSample = validBitsPerSample;
4669  }
4670  stream->render.pPin = FilterCreatePin(pFilter, pPin->pinId, (const WAVEFORMATEX*)&wfx, &result);
4671  }
4672 
4673  if (result == paDeviceUnavailable) goto occupied;
4674 
4675  if (result == paNoError)
4676  {
4677  /* We're done */
4678  break;
4679  }
4680 
4681  if (channelsToProbe < (unsigned)pPin->maxChannels)
4682  {
4683  /* Go to next multiple of 2 */
4684  channelsToProbe = min((((channelsToProbe>>1)+1)<<1), (unsigned)pPin->maxChannels);
4685  continue;
4686  }
4687 
4688  break;
4689  };
4690 
4691  if (result == paNoError)
4692  {
4693  /* We're done */
4694  break;
4695  }
4696 
4697  /* Go to next format in line with lower resolution */
4698  hostOutputSampleFormat <<= 1;
4699  }
4700 
4701  if(stream->render.pPin == NULL)
4702  {
4703  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "Failed to create render pin: sr=%u,ch=%u,bits=%u,align=%u",
4704  wfx.Format.nSamplesPerSec, wfx.Format.nChannels, wfx.Format.wBitsPerSample, wfx.Format.nBlockAlign);
4705  goto error;
4706  }
4707 
4708  stream->render.bytesPerSample = stream->render.bytesPerFrame / stream->deviceOutputChannels;
4709  stream->render.pPin->frameSize /= stream->render.bytesPerFrame;
4710  PA_DEBUG(("Render pin frames: %d\n",stream->render.pPin->frameSize));
4711  }
4712  else
4713  {
4714  stream->render.pPin = NULL;
4715  stream->render.bytesPerFrame = 0;
4716  }
4717 
4718  /* Calculate the framesPerHostXxxxBuffer size based upon the suggested latency values */
4719  /* Record the buffer length */
4720  if(inputParameters)
4721  {
4722  /* Calculate the frames from the user's value - add a bit to round up */
4723  stream->capture.framesPerBuffer = (unsigned long)((inputParameters->suggestedLatency*sampleRate)+0.0001);
4724  if(stream->capture.framesPerBuffer > (unsigned long)sampleRate)
4725  { /* Upper limit is 1 second */
4726  stream->capture.framesPerBuffer = (unsigned long)sampleRate;
4727  }
4728  else if(stream->capture.framesPerBuffer < stream->capture.pPin->frameSize)
4729  {
4730  stream->capture.framesPerBuffer = stream->capture.pPin->frameSize;
4731  }
4732  PA_DEBUG(("Input frames chosen:%ld\n",stream->capture.framesPerBuffer));
4733 
4734  /* Setup number of packets to use */
4735  stream->capture.noOfPackets = 2;
4736 
4737  if (inputParameters->hostApiSpecificStreamInfo)
4738  {
4739  PaWinWDMKSInfo* pInfo = (PaWinWDMKSInfo*)inputParameters->hostApiSpecificStreamInfo;
4740 
4741  if (stream->capture.pPin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType == Type_kWaveCyclic &&
4742  pInfo->noOfPackets != 0)
4743  {
4744  stream->capture.noOfPackets = pInfo->noOfPackets;
4745  }
4746  }
4747  }
4748 
4749  if(outputParameters)
4750  {
4751  /* Calculate the frames from the user's value - add a bit to round up */
4752  stream->render.framesPerBuffer = (unsigned long)((outputParameters->suggestedLatency*sampleRate)+0.0001);
4753  if(stream->render.framesPerBuffer > (unsigned long)sampleRate)
4754  { /* Upper limit is 1 second */
4755  stream->render.framesPerBuffer = (unsigned long)sampleRate;
4756  }
4757  else if(stream->render.framesPerBuffer < stream->render.pPin->frameSize)
4758  {
4759  stream->render.framesPerBuffer = stream->render.pPin->frameSize;
4760  }
4761  PA_DEBUG(("Output frames chosen:%ld\n",stream->render.framesPerBuffer));
4762 
4763  /* Setup number of packets to use */
4764  stream->render.noOfPackets = 2;
4765 
4766  if (outputParameters->hostApiSpecificStreamInfo)
4767  {
4768  PaWinWDMKSInfo* pInfo = (PaWinWDMKSInfo*)outputParameters->hostApiSpecificStreamInfo;
4769 
4770  if (stream->render.pPin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType == Type_kWaveCyclic &&
4771  pInfo->noOfPackets != 0)
4772  {
4773  stream->render.noOfPackets = pInfo->noOfPackets;
4774  }
4775  }
4776  }
4777 
4778  /* Host buffer size is bound to the largest of the input and output frame sizes */
4779  result = PaUtil_InitializeBufferProcessor( &stream->bufferProcessor,
4780  stream->userInputChannels, inputSampleFormat, hostInputSampleFormat,
4781  stream->userOutputChannels, outputSampleFormat, hostOutputSampleFormat,
4782  sampleRate, streamFlags, framesPerUserBuffer,
4783  max(stream->capture.framesPerBuffer, stream->render.framesPerBuffer),
4784  paUtilBoundedHostBufferSize,
4785  streamCallback, userData );
4786  if( result != paNoError )
4787  {
4788  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "PaUtil_InitializeBufferProcessor failed: ich=%u, isf=%u, hisf=%u, och=%u, osf=%u, hosf=%u, sr=%lf, flags=0x%X, fpub=%u, fphb=%u",
4789  stream->userInputChannels, inputSampleFormat, hostInputSampleFormat,
4790  stream->userOutputChannels, outputSampleFormat, hostOutputSampleFormat,
4791  sampleRate, streamFlags, framesPerUserBuffer,
4792  max(stream->capture.framesPerBuffer, stream->render.framesPerBuffer));
4793  goto error;
4794  }
4795 
4796  /* Allocate/get all the buffers for host I/O */
4797  if (stream->userInputChannels > 0)
4798  {
4799  stream->streamRepresentation.streamInfo.inputLatency = stream->capture.framesPerBuffer / sampleRate;
4800 
4801  switch (stream->capture.pPin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType)
4802  {
4803  case Type_kWaveCyclic:
4804  {
4805  unsigned size = stream->capture.noOfPackets * stream->capture.framesPerBuffer * stream->capture.bytesPerFrame;
4806  /* Allocate input host buffer */
4807  stream->capture.hostBuffer = (char*)PaUtil_GroupAllocateMemory(stream->allocGroup, size);
4808  PA_DEBUG(("Input buffer allocated (size = %u)\n", size));
4809  if( !stream->capture.hostBuffer )
4810  {
4811  PA_DEBUG(("Cannot allocate host input buffer!\n"));
4812  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paInsufficientMemory, "Failed to allocate input buffer");
4813  result = paInsufficientMemory;
4814  goto error;
4815  }
4816  stream->capture.hostBufferSize = size;
4817  PA_DEBUG(("Input buffer start = %p (size=%u)\n",stream->capture.hostBuffer, stream->capture.hostBufferSize));
4818  stream->capture.pPin->fnEventHandler = PaPinCaptureEventHandler_WaveCyclic;
4819  stream->capture.pPin->fnSubmitHandler = PaPinCaptureSubmitHandler_WaveCyclic;
4820  }
4821  break;
4822  case Type_kWaveRT:
4823  {
4824  const DWORD dwTotalSize = 2 * stream->capture.framesPerBuffer * stream->capture.bytesPerFrame;
4825  DWORD dwRequestedSize = dwTotalSize;
4826  BOOL bCallMemoryBarrier = FALSE;
4827  ULONG hwFifoLatency = 0;
4828  ULONG dummy;
4829  result = PinGetBuffer(stream->capture.pPin, (void**)&stream->capture.hostBuffer, &dwRequestedSize, &bCallMemoryBarrier);
4830  if (!result)
4831  {
4832  PA_DEBUG(("Input buffer start = %p, size = %u\n", stream->capture.hostBuffer, dwRequestedSize));
4833  if (dwRequestedSize != dwTotalSize)
4834  {
4835  PA_DEBUG(("Buffer length changed by driver from %u to %u !\n", dwTotalSize, dwRequestedSize));
4836  /* Recalculate to what the driver has given us */
4837  stream->capture.framesPerBuffer = dwRequestedSize / (2 * stream->capture.bytesPerFrame);
4838  }
4839  stream->capture.hostBufferSize = dwRequestedSize;
4840 
4841  if (stream->capture.pPin->pinKsSubType == SubType_kPolled)
4842  {
4843  stream->capture.pPin->fnEventHandler = PaPinCaptureEventHandler_WaveRTPolled;
4844  stream->capture.pPin->fnSubmitHandler = PaPinCaptureSubmitHandler_WaveRTPolled;
4845  }
4846  else
4847  {
4848  stream->capture.pPin->fnEventHandler = PaPinCaptureEventHandler_WaveRTEvent;
4849  stream->capture.pPin->fnSubmitHandler = PaPinCaptureSubmitHandler_WaveRTEvent;
4850  }
4851 
4852  stream->capture.pPin->fnMemBarrier = bCallMemoryBarrier ? MemoryBarrierRead : MemoryBarrierDummy;
4853  }
4854  else
4855  {
4856  PA_DEBUG(("Failed to get input buffer (WaveRT)\n"));
4857  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paUnanticipatedHostError, "Failed to get input buffer (WaveRT)");
4858  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
4859  goto error;
4860  }
4861 
4862  /* Get latency */
4863  result = PinGetHwLatency(stream->capture.pPin, &hwFifoLatency, &dummy, &dummy);
4864  if (result == paNoError)
4865  {
4866  stream->capture.pPin->hwLatency = hwFifoLatency;
4867 
4868  /* Add HW latency into total input latency */
4869  stream->streamRepresentation.streamInfo.inputLatency += ((hwFifoLatency / stream->capture.bytesPerFrame) / sampleRate);
4870  }
4871  else
4872  {
4873  PA_DEBUG(("Failed to get size of FIFO hardware buffer (is set to zero)\n"));
4874  stream->capture.pPin->hwLatency = 0;
4875  }
4876  }
4877  break;
4878  default:
4879  /* Undefined wave type!! */
4880  assert(0);
4881  result = paInternalError;
4882  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "Wave type %u ??", stream->capture.pPin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType);
4883  goto error;
4884  }
4885  }
4886  else
4887  {
4888  stream->capture.hostBuffer = 0;
4889  }
4890 
4891  if (stream->userOutputChannels > 0)
4892  {
4893  stream->streamRepresentation.streamInfo.outputLatency = stream->render.framesPerBuffer / sampleRate;
4894 
4895  switch (stream->render.pPin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType)
4896  {
4897  case Type_kWaveCyclic:
4898  {
4899  unsigned size = stream->render.noOfPackets * stream->render.framesPerBuffer * stream->render.bytesPerFrame;
4900  /* Allocate output device buffer */
4901  stream->render.hostBuffer = (char*)PaUtil_GroupAllocateMemory(stream->allocGroup, size);
4902  PA_DEBUG(("Output buffer allocated (size = %u)\n", size));
4903  if( !stream->render.hostBuffer )
4904  {
4905  PA_DEBUG(("Cannot allocate host output buffer!\n"));
4906  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paInsufficientMemory, "Failed to allocate output buffer");
4907  result = paInsufficientMemory;
4908  goto error;
4909  }
4910  stream->render.hostBufferSize = size;
4911  PA_DEBUG(("Output buffer start = %p (size=%u)\n",stream->render.hostBuffer, stream->render.hostBufferSize));
4912 
4913  stream->render.pPin->fnEventHandler = PaPinRenderEventHandler_WaveCyclic;
4914  stream->render.pPin->fnSubmitHandler = PaPinRenderSubmitHandler_WaveCyclic;
4915  }
4916  break;
4917  case Type_kWaveRT:
4918  {
4919  const DWORD dwTotalSize = 2 * stream->render.framesPerBuffer * stream->render.bytesPerFrame;
4920  DWORD dwRequestedSize = dwTotalSize;
4921  BOOL bCallMemoryBarrier = FALSE;
4922  ULONG hwFifoLatency = 0;
4923  ULONG dummy;
4924  result = PinGetBuffer(stream->render.pPin, (void**)&stream->render.hostBuffer, &dwRequestedSize, &bCallMemoryBarrier);
4925  if (!result)
4926  {
4927  PA_DEBUG(("Output buffer start = %p, size = %u, membarrier = %u\n", stream->render.hostBuffer, dwRequestedSize, bCallMemoryBarrier));
4928  if (dwRequestedSize != dwTotalSize)
4929  {
4930  PA_DEBUG(("Buffer length changed by driver from %u to %u !\n", dwTotalSize, dwRequestedSize));
4931  /* Recalculate to what the driver has given us */
4932  stream->render.framesPerBuffer = dwRequestedSize / (2 * stream->render.bytesPerFrame);
4933  }
4934  stream->render.hostBufferSize = dwRequestedSize;
4935 
4936  if (stream->render.pPin->pinKsSubType == SubType_kPolled)
4937  {
4938  stream->render.pPin->fnEventHandler = PaPinRenderEventHandler_WaveRTPolled;
4939  stream->render.pPin->fnSubmitHandler = PaPinRenderSubmitHandler_WaveRTPolled;
4940  }
4941  else
4942  {
4943  stream->render.pPin->fnEventHandler = PaPinRenderEventHandler_WaveRTEvent;
4944  stream->render.pPin->fnSubmitHandler = PaPinRenderSubmitHandler_WaveRTEvent;
4945  }
4946 
4947  stream->render.pPin->fnMemBarrier = bCallMemoryBarrier ? MemoryBarrierWrite : MemoryBarrierDummy;
4948  }
4949  else
4950  {
4951  PA_DEBUG(("Failed to get output buffer (with notification)\n"));
4952  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paUnanticipatedHostError, "Failed to get output buffer (with notification)");
4953  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
4954  goto error;
4955  }
4956 
4957  /* Get latency */
4958  result = PinGetHwLatency(stream->render.pPin, &hwFifoLatency, &dummy, &dummy);
4959  if (result == paNoError)
4960  {
4961  stream->render.pPin->hwLatency = hwFifoLatency;
4962 
4963  /* Add HW latency into total output latency */
4964  stream->streamRepresentation.streamInfo.outputLatency += ((hwFifoLatency / stream->render.bytesPerFrame) / sampleRate);
4965  }
4966  else
4967  {
4968  PA_DEBUG(("Failed to get size of FIFO hardware buffer (is set to zero)\n"));
4969  stream->render.pPin->hwLatency = 0;
4970  }
4971  }
4972  break;
4973  default:
4974  /* Undefined wave type!! */
4975  assert(0);
4976  result = paInternalError;
4977  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "Wave type %u ??", stream->capture.pPin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType);
4978  goto error;
4979  }
4980  }
4981  else
4982  {
4983  stream->render.hostBuffer = 0;
4984  }
4985 
4986  stream->streamRepresentation.streamInfo.sampleRate = sampleRate;
4987 
4988  PA_DEBUG(("BytesPerInputFrame = %d\n",stream->capture.bytesPerFrame));
4989  PA_DEBUG(("BytesPerOutputFrame = %d\n",stream->render.bytesPerFrame));
4990 
4991  /* memset(stream->hostBuffer,0,size); */
4992 
4993  /* Abort */
4994  stream->eventAbort = CreateEvent(NULL, TRUE, FALSE, NULL);
4995  if (stream->eventAbort == 0)
4996  {
4997  result = paInsufficientMemory;
4998  goto error;
4999  }
5000  stream->eventStreamStart[0] = CreateEvent(NULL, TRUE, FALSE, NULL);
5001  if (stream->eventStreamStart[0] == 0)
5002  {
5003  result = paInsufficientMemory;
5004  goto error;
5005  }
5006  stream->eventStreamStart[1] = CreateEvent(NULL, TRUE, FALSE, NULL);
5007  if (stream->eventStreamStart[1] == 0)
5008  {
5009  result = paInsufficientMemory;
5010  goto error;
5011  }
5012 
5013  if(stream->userInputChannels > 0)
5014  {
5015  const unsigned bufferSizeInBytes = stream->capture.framesPerBuffer * stream->capture.bytesPerFrame;
5016  const unsigned ringBufferFrameSize = NextPowerOf2( 1024 + 2 * max(stream->capture.framesPerBuffer, stream->render.framesPerBuffer) );
5017 
5018  stream->capture.events = (HANDLE*)PaUtil_GroupAllocateMemory(stream->allocGroup, stream->capture.noOfPackets * sizeof(HANDLE));
5019  if (stream->capture.events == NULL)
5020  {
5021  result = paInsufficientMemory;
5022  goto error;
5023  }
5024 
5025  stream->capture.packets = (DATAPACKET*)PaUtil_GroupAllocateMemory(stream->allocGroup, stream->capture.noOfPackets * sizeof(DATAPACKET));
5026  if (stream->capture.packets == NULL)
5027  {
5028  result = paInsufficientMemory;
5029  goto error;
5030  }
5031 
5032  switch(stream->capture.pPin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType)
5033  {
5034  case Type_kWaveCyclic:
5035  {
5036  /* WaveCyclic case */
5037  unsigned i;
5038  for (i = 0; i < stream->capture.noOfPackets; ++i)
5039  {
5040  /* Set up the packets */
5041  DATAPACKET *p = stream->capture.packets + i;
5042 
5043  /* Record event */
5044  stream->capture.events[i] = CreateEvent(NULL, TRUE, FALSE, NULL);
5045 
5046  p->Signal.hEvent = stream->capture.events[i];
5047  p->Header.Data = stream->capture.hostBuffer + (i*bufferSizeInBytes);
5048  p->Header.FrameExtent = bufferSizeInBytes;
5049  p->Header.DataUsed = 0;
5050  p->Header.Size = sizeof(p->Header);
5051  p->Header.PresentationTime.Numerator = 1;
5052  p->Header.PresentationTime.Denominator = 1;
5053  }
5054  }
5055  break;
5056  case Type_kWaveRT:
5057  {
5058  /* Set up the "packets" */
5059  DATAPACKET *p = stream->capture.packets + 0;
5060 
5061  /* Record event: WaveRT has a single event for 2 notification per buffer */
5062  stream->capture.events[0] = CreateEvent(NULL, FALSE, FALSE, NULL);
5063 
5064  p->Header.Data = stream->capture.hostBuffer;
5065  p->Header.FrameExtent = bufferSizeInBytes;
5066  p->Header.DataUsed = 0;
5067  p->Header.Size = sizeof(p->Header);
5068  p->Header.PresentationTime.Numerator = 1;
5069  p->Header.PresentationTime.Denominator = 1;
5070 
5071  ++p;
5072  p->Header.Data = stream->capture.hostBuffer + bufferSizeInBytes;
5073  p->Header.FrameExtent = bufferSizeInBytes;
5074  p->Header.DataUsed = 0;
5075  p->Header.Size = sizeof(p->Header);
5076  p->Header.PresentationTime.Numerator = 1;
5077  p->Header.PresentationTime.Denominator = 1;
5078 
5079  if (stream->capture.pPin->pinKsSubType == SubType_kNotification)
5080  {
5081  result = PinRegisterNotificationHandle(stream->capture.pPin, stream->capture.events[0]);
5082 
5083  if (result != paNoError)
5084  {
5085  PA_DEBUG(("Failed to register capture notification handle\n"));
5086  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paUnanticipatedHostError, "Failed to register capture notification handle");
5087  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
5088  goto error;
5089  }
5090  }
5091 
5092  result = PinRegisterPositionRegister(stream->capture.pPin);
5093 
5094  if (result != paNoError)
5095  {
5096  unsigned long pos = 0xdeadc0de;
5097  PA_DEBUG(("Failed to register capture position register, using PinGetAudioPositionViaIOCTLWrite\n"));
5098  stream->capture.pPin->fnAudioPosition = PinGetAudioPositionViaIOCTLWrite;
5099  /* Test position function */
5100  result = (stream->capture.pPin->fnAudioPosition)(stream->capture.pPin, &pos);
5101  if (result != paNoError || pos != 0x0)
5102  {
5103  PA_DEBUG(("Failed to read capture position register (IOCTL)\n"));
5104  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paUnanticipatedHostError, "Failed to read capture position register (IOCTL)");
5105  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
5106  goto error;
5107  }
5108  }
5109  else
5110  {
5111  stream->capture.pPin->fnAudioPosition = PinGetAudioPositionMemoryMapped;
5112  }
5113  }
5114  break;
5115  default:
5116  /* Undefined wave type!! */
5117  assert(0);
5118  result = paInternalError;
5119  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "Wave type %u ??", stream->capture.pPin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType);
5120  goto error;
5121  }
5122 
5123  /* Setup the input ring buffer here */
5124  stream->ringBufferData = (char*)PaUtil_GroupAllocateMemory(stream->allocGroup, ringBufferFrameSize * stream->capture.bytesPerFrame);
5125  if (stream->ringBufferData == NULL)
5126  {
5127  result = paInsufficientMemory;
5128  goto error;
5129  }
5130  PaUtil_InitializeRingBuffer(&stream->ringBuffer, stream->capture.bytesPerFrame, ringBufferFrameSize, stream->ringBufferData);
5131  }
5132  if(stream->userOutputChannels > 0)
5133  {
5134  const unsigned bufferSizeInBytes = stream->render.framesPerBuffer * stream->render.bytesPerFrame;
5135 
5136  stream->render.events = (HANDLE*)PaUtil_GroupAllocateMemory(stream->allocGroup, stream->render.noOfPackets * sizeof(HANDLE));
5137  if (stream->render.events == NULL)
5138  {
5139  result = paInsufficientMemory;
5140  goto error;
5141  }
5142 
5143  stream->render.packets = (DATAPACKET*)PaUtil_GroupAllocateMemory(stream->allocGroup, stream->render.noOfPackets * sizeof(DATAPACKET));
5144  if (stream->render.packets == NULL)
5145  {
5146  result = paInsufficientMemory;
5147  goto error;
5148  }
5149 
5150  switch(stream->render.pPin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType)
5151  {
5152  case Type_kWaveCyclic:
5153  {
5154  /* WaveCyclic case */
5155  unsigned i;
5156  for (i = 0; i < stream->render.noOfPackets; ++i)
5157  {
5158  /* Set up the packets */
5159  DATAPACKET *p = stream->render.packets + i;
5160 
5161  /* Playback event */
5162  stream->render.events[i] = CreateEvent(NULL, TRUE, FALSE, NULL);
5163 
5164  /* In this case, we just use the packets as ptr to the device buffer */
5165  p->Signal.hEvent = stream->render.events[i];
5166  p->Header.Data = stream->render.hostBuffer + (i*bufferSizeInBytes);
5167  p->Header.FrameExtent = bufferSizeInBytes;
5168  p->Header.DataUsed = bufferSizeInBytes;
5169  p->Header.Size = sizeof(p->Header);
5170  p->Header.PresentationTime.Numerator = 1;
5171  p->Header.PresentationTime.Denominator = 1;
5172  }
5173  }
5174  break;
5175  case Type_kWaveRT:
5176  {
5177  /* WaveRT case */
5178 
5179  /* Set up the "packets" */
5180  DATAPACKET *p = stream->render.packets;
5181 
5182  /* The only playback event */
5183  stream->render.events[0] = CreateEvent(NULL, FALSE, FALSE, NULL);
5184 
5185  /* In this case, we just use the packets as ptr to the device buffer */
5186  p->Header.Data = stream->render.hostBuffer;
5187  p->Header.FrameExtent = stream->render.framesPerBuffer*stream->render.bytesPerFrame;
5188  p->Header.DataUsed = stream->render.framesPerBuffer*stream->render.bytesPerFrame;
5189  p->Header.Size = sizeof(p->Header);
5190  p->Header.PresentationTime.Numerator = 1;
5191  p->Header.PresentationTime.Denominator = 1;
5192 
5193  ++p;
5194  p->Header.Data = stream->render.hostBuffer + stream->render.framesPerBuffer*stream->render.bytesPerFrame;
5195  p->Header.FrameExtent = stream->render.framesPerBuffer*stream->render.bytesPerFrame;
5196  p->Header.DataUsed = stream->render.framesPerBuffer*stream->render.bytesPerFrame;
5197  p->Header.Size = sizeof(p->Header);
5198  p->Header.PresentationTime.Numerator = 1;
5199  p->Header.PresentationTime.Denominator = 1;
5200 
5201  if (stream->render.pPin->pinKsSubType == SubType_kNotification)
5202  {
5203  result = PinRegisterNotificationHandle(stream->render.pPin, stream->render.events[0]);
5204 
5205  if (result != paNoError)
5206  {
5207  PA_DEBUG(("Failed to register rendering notification handle\n"));
5208  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paUnanticipatedHostError, "Failed to register rendering notification handle");
5209  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
5210  goto error;
5211  }
5212  }
5213 
5214  result = PinRegisterPositionRegister(stream->render.pPin);
5215 
5216  if (result != paNoError)
5217  {
5218  unsigned long pos = 0xdeadc0de;
5219  PA_DEBUG(("Failed to register rendering position register, using PinGetAudioPositionViaIOCTLRead\n"));
5220  stream->render.pPin->fnAudioPosition = PinGetAudioPositionViaIOCTLRead;
5221  /* Test position function */
5222  result = (stream->render.pPin->fnAudioPosition)(stream->render.pPin, &pos);
5223  if (result != paNoError || pos != 0x0)
5224  {
5225  PA_DEBUG(("Failed to read render position register (IOCTL)\n"));
5226  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(paUnanticipatedHostError, "Failed to read render position register (IOCTL)");
5227  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
5228  goto error;
5229  }
5230  }
5231  else
5232  {
5233  stream->render.pPin->fnAudioPosition = PinGetAudioPositionMemoryMapped;
5234  }
5235  }
5236  break;
5237  default:
5238  /* Undefined wave type!! */
5239  assert(0);
5240  result = paInternalError;
5241  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "Wave type %u ??", stream->capture.pPin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType);
5242  goto error;
5243  }
5244  }
5245 
5246  stream->streamStarted = 0;
5247  stream->streamActive = 0;
5248  stream->streamStop = 0;
5249  stream->streamAbort = 0;
5250  stream->streamFlags = streamFlags;
5251  stream->oldProcessPriority = REALTIME_PRIORITY_CLASS;
5252 
5253  /* Increase ref count on filters in use, so that a CommitDeviceInfos won't delete them */
5254  if (stream->capture.pPin != 0)
5255  {
5256  FilterAddRef(stream->capture.pPin->parentFilter);
5257  }
5258  if (stream->render.pPin != 0)
5259  {
5260  FilterAddRef(stream->render.pPin->parentFilter);
5261  }
5262 
5263  /* Ok, now update our host API specific stream info */
5264  if (stream->userInputChannels)
5265  {
5266  PaWinWdmDeviceInfo *pDeviceInfo = (PaWinWdmDeviceInfo*)wdmHostApi->inheritedHostApiRep.deviceInfos[inputParameters->device];
5267 
5268  stream->hostApiStreamInfo.input.device = Pa_HostApiDeviceIndexToDeviceIndex(Pa_HostApiTypeIdToHostApiIndex(paWDMKS), inputParameters->device);
5269  stream->hostApiStreamInfo.input.channels = stream->deviceInputChannels;
5270  stream->hostApiStreamInfo.input.muxNodeId = -1;
5271  if (stream->capture.pPin->inputs)
5272  {
5273  stream->hostApiStreamInfo.input.muxNodeId = stream->capture.pPin->inputs[pDeviceInfo->muxPosition]->muxNodeId;
5274  }
5275  stream->hostApiStreamInfo.input.endpointPinId = pDeviceInfo->endpointPinId;
5276  stream->hostApiStreamInfo.input.framesPerHostBuffer = stream->capture.framesPerBuffer;
5277  stream->hostApiStreamInfo.input.streamingSubType = stream->capture.pPin->pinKsSubType;
5278  }
5279  else
5280  {
5281  stream->hostApiStreamInfo.input.device = paNoDevice;
5282  }
5283  if (stream->userOutputChannels)
5284  {
5285  stream->hostApiStreamInfo.output.device = Pa_HostApiDeviceIndexToDeviceIndex(Pa_HostApiTypeIdToHostApiIndex(paWDMKS), outputParameters->device);
5286  stream->hostApiStreamInfo.output.channels = stream->deviceOutputChannels;
5287  stream->hostApiStreamInfo.output.framesPerHostBuffer = stream->render.framesPerBuffer;
5288  stream->hostApiStreamInfo.output.endpointPinId = stream->render.pPin->endpointPinId;
5289  stream->hostApiStreamInfo.output.streamingSubType = stream->render.pPin->pinKsSubType;
5290  }
5291  else
5292  {
5293  stream->hostApiStreamInfo.output.device = paNoDevice;
5294  }
5295  /*stream->streamRepresentation.streamInfo.hostApiTypeId = paWDMKS;
5296  stream->streamRepresentation.streamInfo.hostApiSpecificStreamInfo = &stream->hostApiStreamInfo;*/
5297  stream->streamRepresentation.streamInfo.structVersion = 2;
5298 
5299  *s = (PaStream*)stream;
5300 
5301  PA_LOGL_;
5302  return result;
5303 
5304 occupied:
5305  /* Ok, someone else is hogging the pin, bail out */
5306  assert (result == paDeviceUnavailable);
5307  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "Device is occupied");
5308 
5309 error:
5310  PaUtil_TerminateBufferProcessor( &stream->bufferProcessor );
5311 
5312  CloseStreamEvents(stream);
5313 
5314  if (stream->allocGroup)
5315  {
5316  PaUtil_FreeAllAllocations(stream->allocGroup);
5317  PaUtil_DestroyAllocationGroup(stream->allocGroup);
5318  stream->allocGroup = 0;
5319  }
5320 
5321  if(stream->render.pPin)
5322  PinClose(stream->render.pPin);
5323  if(stream->capture.pPin)
5324  PinClose(stream->capture.pPin);
5325 
5326  PaUtil_FreeMemory( stream );
5327 
5328  PA_LOGL_;
5329  return result;
5330 }
5331 
5332 /*
5333 When CloseStream() is called, the multi-api layer ensures that
5334 the stream has already been stopped or aborted.
5335 */
5336 static PaError CloseStream( PaStream* s )
5337 {
5338  PaError result = paNoError;
5339  PaWinWdmStream *stream = (PaWinWdmStream*)s;
5340 
5341  PA_LOGE_;
5342 
5343  assert(!stream->streamStarted);
5344  assert(!stream->streamActive);
5345 
5346  PaUtil_TerminateBufferProcessor( &stream->bufferProcessor );
5347  PaUtil_TerminateStreamRepresentation( &stream->streamRepresentation );
5348 
5349  CloseStreamEvents(stream);
5350 
5351  if (stream->allocGroup)
5352  {
5353  PaUtil_FreeAllAllocations(stream->allocGroup);
5354  PaUtil_DestroyAllocationGroup(stream->allocGroup);
5355  stream->allocGroup = 0;
5356  }
5357 
5358  if(stream->render.pPin)
5359  {
5360  PinClose(stream->render.pPin);
5361  }
5362  if(stream->capture.pPin)
5363  {
5364  PinClose(stream->capture.pPin);
5365  }
5366 
5367  if (stream->render.pPin)
5368  {
5369  FilterFree(stream->render.pPin->parentFilter);
5370  }
5371  if (stream->capture.pPin)
5372  {
5373  FilterFree(stream->capture.pPin->parentFilter);
5374  }
5375 
5376  PaUtil_FreeMemory( stream );
5377 
5378  PA_LOGL_;
5379  return result;
5380 }

5382 /*
5383 Write the supplied packet to the pin
5384 Asynchronous
5385 Should return paNoError on success
5386 */
5387 static PaError PinWrite(HANDLE h, DATAPACKET* p)
5388 {
5389  PaError result = paNoError;
5390  unsigned long cbReturned = 0;
5391  BOOL fRes = DeviceIoControl(h,
5392  IOCTL_KS_WRITE_STREAM,
5393  NULL,
5394  0,
5395  &p->Header,
5396  p->Header.Size,
5397  &cbReturned,
5398  &p->Signal);
5399  if (!fRes)
5400  {
5401  unsigned long error = GetLastError();
5402  if (error != ERROR_IO_PENDING)
5403  {
5404  result = paInternalError;
5405  }
5406  }
5407  return result;
5408 }
5409 
5410 /*
5411 Read to the supplied packet from the pin
5412 Asynchronous
5413 Should return paNoError on success
5414 */
5415 static PaError PinRead(HANDLE h, DATAPACKET* p)
5416 {
5417  PaError result = paNoError;
5418  unsigned long cbReturned = 0;
5419  BOOL fRes = DeviceIoControl(h,
5420  IOCTL_KS_READ_STREAM,
5421  NULL,
5422  0,
5423  &p->Header,
5424  p->Header.Size,
5425  &cbReturned,
5426  &p->Signal);
5427  if (!fRes)
5428  {
5429  unsigned long error = GetLastError();
5430  if (error != ERROR_IO_PENDING)
5431  {
5432  result = paInternalError;
5433  }
5434  }
5435  return result;
5436 }

5438 /*
5439 Copy the first interleaved channel of 16 bit data to the other channels
5440 */
5441 static void DuplicateFirstChannelInt16(void* buffer, int channels, int samples)
5442 {
5443  unsigned short* data = (unsigned short*)buffer;
5444  int channel;
5445  unsigned short sourceSample;
5446  while( samples-- )
5447  {
5448  sourceSample = *data++;
5449  channel = channels-1;
5450  while( channel-- )
5451  {
5452  *data++ = sourceSample;
5453  }
5454  }
5455 }
5456 
5457 /*
5458 Copy the first interleaved channel of 24 bit data to the other channels
5459 */
5460 static void DuplicateFirstChannelInt24(void* buffer, int channels, int samples)
5461 {
5462  unsigned char* data = (unsigned char*)buffer;
5463  int channel;
5464  unsigned char sourceSample[3];
5465  while( samples-- )
5466  {
5467  sourceSample[0] = data[0];
5468  sourceSample[1] = data[1];
5469  sourceSample[2] = data[2];
5470  data += 3;
5471  channel = channels-1;
5472  while( channel-- )
5473  {
5474  data[0] = sourceSample[0];
5475  data[1] = sourceSample[1];
5476  data[2] = sourceSample[2];
5477  data += 3;
5478  }
5479  }
5480 }
5481 
5482 /*
5483 Copy the first interleaved channel of 32 bit data to the other channels
5484 */
5485 static void DuplicateFirstChannelInt32(void* buffer, int channels, int samples)
5486 {
5487  unsigned long* data = (unsigned long*)buffer;
5488  int channel;
5489  unsigned long sourceSample;
5490  while( samples-- )
5491  {
5492  sourceSample = *data++;
5493  channel = channels-1;
5494  while( channel-- )
5495  {
5496  *data++ = sourceSample;
5497  }
5498  }
5499 }
5500 
5501 /*
5502 Increase the priority of the calling thread to RT
5503 */
5504 static HANDLE BumpThreadPriority()
5505 {
5506  HANDLE hThread = GetCurrentThread();
5507  DWORD dwTask = 0;
5508  HANDLE hAVRT = NULL;
5509 
5510  /* If we have access to AVRT.DLL (Vista and later), use it */
5511  if (paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.AvSetMmThreadCharacteristics != NULL)
5512  {
5513  hAVRT = paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.AvSetMmThreadCharacteristics("Pro Audio", &dwTask);
5514  if (hAVRT != NULL && hAVRT != INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE)
5515  {
5516  BOOL bret = paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.AvSetMmThreadPriority(hAVRT, PA_AVRT_PRIORITY_CRITICAL);
5517  if (!bret)
5518  {
5519  PA_DEBUG(("Set mm thread prio to critical failed!\n"));
5520  }
5521  else
5522  {
5523  return hAVRT;
5524  }
5525  }
5526  else
5527  {
5528  PA_DEBUG(("Set mm thread characteristic to 'Pro Audio' failed, reverting to SetThreadPriority\n"));
5529  }
5530  }
5531 
5532  /* For XP and earlier, or if AvSetMmThreadCharacteristics fails (MMCSS disabled ?) */
5533  if (timeBeginPeriod(1) != TIMERR_NOERROR) {
5534  PA_DEBUG(("timeBeginPeriod(1) failed!\n"));
5535  }
5536 
5537  if (!SetThreadPriority(hThread, THREAD_PRIORITY_TIME_CRITICAL)) {
5538  PA_DEBUG(("SetThreadPriority failed!\n"));
5539  }
5540 
5541  return hAVRT;
5542 }
5543 
5544 /*
5545 Decrease the priority of the calling thread to normal
5546 */
5547 static void DropThreadPriority(HANDLE hAVRT)
5548 {
5549  HANDLE hThread = GetCurrentThread();
5550 
5551  if (hAVRT != NULL)
5552  {
5553  paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.AvSetMmThreadPriority(hAVRT, PA_AVRT_PRIORITY_NORMAL);
5554  paWinWDMKSAvRtEntryPoints.AvRevertMmThreadCharacteristics(hAVRT);
5555  return;
5556  }
5557 
5558  SetThreadPriority(hThread, THREAD_PRIORITY_NORMAL);
5559  timeEndPeriod(1);
5560 }
