5562 static PaError PreparePinForStart(PaWinWdmPin* pin)
5563 {
5564  PaError result;
5565  result = PinSetState(pin, KSSTATE_ACQUIRE);
5566  if (result != paNoError)
5567  {
5568  goto error;
5569  }
5570  result = PinSetState(pin, KSSTATE_PAUSE);
5571  if (result != paNoError)
5572  {
5573  goto error;
5574  }
5575  return result;
5576 
5577 error:
5578  PinSetState(pin, KSSTATE_STOP);
5579  return result;
5580 }
5581 
5582 static PaError PreparePinsForStart(PaProcessThreadInfo* pInfo)
5583 {
5584  PaError result = paNoError;
5585  /* Submit buffers */
5586  if (pInfo->stream->capture.pPin)
5587  {
5588  if ((result = PreparePinForStart(pInfo->stream->capture.pPin)) != paNoError)
5589  {
5590  goto error;
5591  }
5592 
5593  if (pInfo->stream->capture.pPin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType == Type_kWaveCyclic)
5594  {
5595  unsigned i;
5596  for(i=0; i < pInfo->stream->capture.noOfPackets; ++i)
5597  {
5598  if ((result = PinRead(pInfo->stream->capture.pPin->handle, pInfo->stream->capture.packets + i)) != paNoError)
5599  {
5600  goto error;
5601  }
5602  ++pInfo->pending;
5603  }
5604  }
5605  else
5606  {
5607  pInfo->pending = 2;
5608  }
5609  }
5610 
5611  if(pInfo->stream->render.pPin)
5612  {
5613  if ((result = PreparePinForStart(pInfo->stream->render.pPin)) != paNoError)
5614  {
5615  goto error;
5616  }
5617 
5618  pInfo->priming += pInfo->stream->render.noOfPackets;
5619  ++pInfo->pending;
5620  SetEvent(pInfo->stream->render.events[0]);
5621  if (pInfo->stream->render.pPin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType == Type_kWaveCyclic)
5622  {
5623  unsigned i;
5624  for(i=1; i < pInfo->stream->render.noOfPackets; ++i)
5625  {
5626  SetEvent(pInfo->stream->render.events[i]);
5627  ++pInfo->pending;
5628  }
5629  }
5630  }
5631 
5632 error:
5633  PA_DEBUG(("PreparePinsForStart = %d\n", result));
5634  return result;
5635 }
5636 
5637 static PaError StartPin(PaWinWdmPin* pin)
5638 {
5639  return PinSetState(pin, KSSTATE_RUN);
5640 }
5641 
5642 static PaError StartPins(PaProcessThreadInfo* pInfo)
5643 {
5644  PaError result = paNoError;
5645  /* Start the pins as synced as possible */
5646  if (pInfo->stream->capture.pPin)
5647  {
5648  result = StartPin(pInfo->stream->capture.pPin);
5649  }
5650  if(pInfo->stream->render.pPin)
5651  {
5652  result = StartPin(pInfo->stream->render.pPin);
5653  }
5654  PA_DEBUG(("StartPins = %d\n", result));
5655  return result;
5656 }

5671  {
5672  StopPin(pInfo->stream->render.pPin);
5673  }

5680 
5681 typedef void (*TSetInputFrameCount)(PaUtilBufferProcessor*, unsigned long);
5682 typedef void (*TSetInputChannel)(PaUtilBufferProcessor*, unsigned int, void *, unsigned int);
5683 static const TSetInputFrameCount fnSetInputFrameCount[2] = { PaUtil_SetInputFrameCount, PaUtil_Set2ndInputFrameCount };
5684 static const TSetInputChannel fnSetInputChannel[2] = { PaUtil_SetInputChannel, PaUtil_Set2ndInputChannel };
5685 
5686 static PaError PaDoProcessing(PaProcessThreadInfo* pInfo)
5687 {
5688  PaError result = paNoError;
5689  int i, framesProcessed = 0, doChannelCopy = 0;
5690  ring_buffer_size_t inputFramesAvailable = PaUtil_GetRingBufferReadAvailable(&pInfo->stream->ringBuffer);
5691 
5692  /* Do necessary buffer processing (which will invoke user callback if necessary) */
5693  if (pInfo->cbResult == paContinue &&
5694  (pInfo->renderHead != pInfo->renderTail || inputFramesAvailable))
5695  {
5696  unsigned processFullDuplex = pInfo->stream->capture.pPin && pInfo->stream->render.pPin && (!pInfo->priming);
5697 
5698  PA_HP_TRACE((pInfo->stream->hLog, "DoProcessing: InputFrames=%u", inputFramesAvailable));
5699 
5700  PaUtil_BeginCpuLoadMeasurement( &pInfo->stream->cpuLoadMeasurer );
5701 
5702  pInfo->ti.currentTime = PaUtil_GetTime();
5703 
5704  PaUtil_BeginBufferProcessing(&pInfo->stream->bufferProcessor, &pInfo->ti, pInfo->underover);
5705  pInfo->underover = 0; /* Reset the (under|over)flow status */
5706 
5707  if (pInfo->renderTail != pInfo->renderHead)
5708  {
5709  DATAPACKET* packet = pInfo->renderPackets[pInfo->renderTail & cPacketsArrayMask].packet;
5710 
5711  assert(packet != 0);
5712  assert(packet->Header.Data != 0);
5713 
5714  PaUtil_SetOutputFrameCount(&pInfo->stream->bufferProcessor, pInfo->stream->render.framesPerBuffer);
5715 
5716  for(i=0;i<pInfo->stream->userOutputChannels;i++)
5717  {
5718  /* Only write the user output channels. Leave the rest blank */
5719  PaUtil_SetOutputChannel(&pInfo->stream->bufferProcessor,
5720  i,
5721  ((unsigned char*)(packet->Header.Data))+(i*pInfo->stream->render.bytesPerSample),
5722  pInfo->stream->deviceOutputChannels);
5723  }
5724 
5725  /* We will do a copy to the other channels after the data has been written */
5726  doChannelCopy = ( pInfo->stream->userOutputChannels == 1 );
5727  }
5728 
5729  if (inputFramesAvailable && (!pInfo->stream->userOutputChannels || inputFramesAvailable >= (int)pInfo->stream->render.framesPerBuffer))
5730  {
5731  unsigned wrapCntr = 0;
5732  void* data[2] = {0};
5733  ring_buffer_size_t size[2] = {0};
5734 
5735  /* If full-duplex, we just extract output buffer number of frames */
5736  if (pInfo->stream->userOutputChannels)
5737  {
5738  inputFramesAvailable = min(inputFramesAvailable, (int)pInfo->stream->render.framesPerBuffer);
5739  }
5740 
5741  inputFramesAvailable = PaUtil_GetRingBufferReadRegions(&pInfo->stream->ringBuffer,
5742  inputFramesAvailable,
5743  &data[0],
5744  &size[0],
5745  &data[1],
5746  &size[1]);
5747 
5748  for (wrapCntr = 0; wrapCntr < 2; ++wrapCntr)
5749  {
5750  if (size[wrapCntr] == 0)
5751  break;
5752 
5753  fnSetInputFrameCount[wrapCntr](&pInfo->stream->bufferProcessor, size[wrapCntr]);
5754  for(i=0;i<pInfo->stream->userInputChannels;i++)
5755  {
5756  /* Only read as many channels as the user wants */
5757  fnSetInputChannel[wrapCntr](&pInfo->stream->bufferProcessor,
5758  i,
5759  ((unsigned char*)(data[wrapCntr]))+(i*pInfo->stream->capture.bytesPerSample),
5760  pInfo->stream->deviceInputChannels);
5761  }
5762  }
5763  }
5764  else
5765  {
5766  /* We haven't consumed anything from the ring buffer... */
5767  inputFramesAvailable = 0;
5768  /* If we have full-duplex, this is at startup, so mark no-input! */
5769  if (pInfo->stream->userOutputChannels>0 && pInfo->stream->userInputChannels>0)
5770  {
5771  PA_HP_TRACE((pInfo->stream->hLog, "Input startup, marking no input."));
5772  PaUtil_SetNoInput(&pInfo->stream->bufferProcessor);
5773  }
5774  }
5775 
5776  if (processFullDuplex) /* full duplex */
5777  {
5778  /* Only call the EndBufferProcessing function when the total input frames == total output frames */
5779  const unsigned long totalInputFrameCount = pInfo->stream->bufferProcessor.hostInputFrameCount[0] + pInfo->stream->bufferProcessor.hostInputFrameCount[1];
5780  const unsigned long totalOutputFrameCount = pInfo->stream->bufferProcessor.hostOutputFrameCount[0] + pInfo->stream->bufferProcessor.hostOutputFrameCount[1];
5781 
5782  if(totalInputFrameCount == totalOutputFrameCount && totalOutputFrameCount != 0)
5783  {
5784  framesProcessed = PaUtil_EndBufferProcessing(&pInfo->stream->bufferProcessor, &pInfo->cbResult);
5785  }
5786  else
5787  {
5788  framesProcessed = 0;
5789  }
5790  }
5791  else
5792  {
5793  framesProcessed = PaUtil_EndBufferProcessing(&pInfo->stream->bufferProcessor, &pInfo->cbResult);
5794  }
5795 
5796  PA_HP_TRACE((pInfo->stream->hLog, "Frames processed: %u %s", framesProcessed, (pInfo->priming ? "(priming)":"")));
5797 
5798  if( doChannelCopy )
5799  {
5800  DATAPACKET* packet = pInfo->renderPackets[pInfo->renderTail & cPacketsArrayMask].packet;
5801  /* Copy the first output channel to the other channels */
5802  switch (pInfo->stream->render.bytesPerSample)
5803  {
5804  case 2:
5805  DuplicateFirstChannelInt16(packet->Header.Data, pInfo->stream->deviceOutputChannels, pInfo->stream->render.framesPerBuffer);
5806  break;
5807  case 3:
5808  DuplicateFirstChannelInt24(packet->Header.Data, pInfo->stream->deviceOutputChannels, pInfo->stream->render.framesPerBuffer);
5809  break;
5810  case 4:
5811  DuplicateFirstChannelInt32(packet->Header.Data, pInfo->stream->deviceOutputChannels, pInfo->stream->render.framesPerBuffer);
5812  break;
5813  default:
5814  assert(0); /* Unsupported format! */
5815  break;
5816  }
5817  }
5818  PaUtil_EndCpuLoadMeasurement( &pInfo->stream->cpuLoadMeasurer, framesProcessed );
5819 
5820  if (inputFramesAvailable)
5821  {
5822  PaUtil_AdvanceRingBufferReadIndex(&pInfo->stream->ringBuffer, inputFramesAvailable);
5823  }
5824 
5825  if (pInfo->renderTail != pInfo->renderHead)
5826  {
5827  if (!pInfo->stream->streamStop)
5828  {
5829  result = pInfo->stream->render.pPin->fnSubmitHandler(pInfo, pInfo->renderTail);
5830  if (result != paNoError)
5831  {
5832  PA_HP_TRACE((pInfo->stream->hLog, "Capture submit handler failed with result %d", result));
5833  return result;
5834  }
5835  }
5836  pInfo->renderTail++;
5837  if (!pInfo->pinsStarted && pInfo->priming == 0)
5838  {
5839  /* We start the pins here to allow "prime time" */
5840  if ((result = StartPins(pInfo)) == paNoError)
5841  {
5842  PA_HP_TRACE((pInfo->stream->hLog, "Starting pins!"));
5843  pInfo->pinsStarted = 1;
5844  }
5845  }
5846  }
5847  }
5848 
5849  return result;
5850 }
5851 
5852 static VOID CALLBACK TimerAPCWaveRTPolledMode(
5853  LPVOID lpArgToCompletionRoutine,
5854  DWORD dwTimerLowValue,
5855  DWORD dwTimerHighValue)
5856 {
5857  HANDLE* pHandles = (HANDLE*)lpArgToCompletionRoutine;
5858  if (pHandles[0]) SetEvent(pHandles[0]);
5859  if (pHandles[1]) SetEvent(pHandles[1]);
5860 }
5861 
5862 static DWORD GetCurrentTimeInMillisecs()
5863 {
5864  return timeGetTime();
5865 }
5866 
5867 PA_THREAD_FUNC ProcessingThread(void* pParam)
5868 {
5869  PaError result = paNoError;
5870  HANDLE hAVRT = NULL;
5871  HANDLE hTimer = NULL;
5872  HANDLE *handleArray = NULL;
5873  HANDLE timerEventHandles[2] = {0};
5874  unsigned noOfHandles = 0;
5875  unsigned captureEvents = 0;
5876  unsigned renderEvents = 0;
5877  unsigned timerPeriod = 0;
5878  DWORD timeStamp[2] = {0};
5879 
5880  PaProcessThreadInfo info;
5881  memset(&info, 0, sizeof(PaProcessThreadInfo));
5882  info.stream = (PaWinWdmStream*)pParam;
5883 
5884  info.stream->threadResult = paNoError;
5885 
5886  PA_LOGE_;
5887 
5888  info.ti.inputBufferAdcTime = 0.0;
5889  info.ti.currentTime = 0.0;
5890  info.ti.outputBufferDacTime = 0.0;
5891 
5892  PA_DEBUG(("In buffer len: %.3f ms\n",(2000*info.stream->capture.framesPerBuffer) / info.stream->streamRepresentation.streamInfo.sampleRate));
5893  PA_DEBUG(("Out buffer len: %.3f ms\n",(2000*info.stream->render.framesPerBuffer) / info.stream->streamRepresentation.streamInfo.sampleRate));
5894  info.timeout = (DWORD)max(
5895  (2000*info.stream->render.framesPerBuffer/info.stream->streamRepresentation.streamInfo.sampleRate + 0.5),
5896  (2000*info.stream->capture.framesPerBuffer/info.stream->streamRepresentation.streamInfo.sampleRate + 0.5));
5897  info.timeout = max(info.timeout*8, 100);
5898  timerPeriod = info.timeout;
5899  PA_DEBUG(("Timeout = %ld ms\n",info.timeout));
5900 
5901  /* Allocate handle array */
5902  handleArray = (HANDLE*)PaUtil_AllocateMemory((info.stream->capture.noOfPackets + info.stream->render.noOfPackets + 1) * sizeof(HANDLE));
5903 
5904  /* Setup handle array for WFMO */
5905  if (info.stream->capture.pPin != 0)
5906  {
5907  handleArray[noOfHandles++] = info.stream->capture.events[0];
5908  if (info.stream->capture.pPin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType == Type_kWaveCyclic)
5909  {
5910  unsigned i;
5911  for(i=1; i < info.stream->capture.noOfPackets; ++i)
5912  {
5913  handleArray[noOfHandles++] = info.stream->capture.events[i];
5914  }
5915  }
5916  captureEvents = noOfHandles;
5917  renderEvents = noOfHandles;
5918  }
5919 
5920  if (info.stream->render.pPin != 0)
5921  {
5922  handleArray[noOfHandles++] = info.stream->render.events[0];
5923  if (info.stream->render.pPin->parentFilter->devInfo.streamingType == Type_kWaveCyclic)
5924  {
5925  unsigned i;
5926  for(i=1; i < info.stream->render.noOfPackets; ++i)
5927  {
5928  handleArray[noOfHandles++] = info.stream->render.events[i];
5929  }
5930  }
5931  renderEvents = noOfHandles;
5932  }
5933  handleArray[noOfHandles++] = info.stream->eventAbort;
5934  assert(noOfHandles <= (info.stream->capture.noOfPackets + info.stream->render.noOfPackets + 1));
5935 
5936  /* Prepare render and capture pins */
5937  if ((result = PreparePinsForStart(&info)) != paNoError)
5938  {
5939  PA_DEBUG(("Failed to prepare device(s)!\n"));
5940  goto error;
5941  }
5942 
5943  /* Init high speed logger */
5944  if (PaUtil_InitializeHighSpeedLog(&info.stream->hLog, 1000000) != paNoError)
5945  {
5946  PA_DEBUG(("Failed to init high speed logger!\n"));
5947  goto error;
5948  }
5949 
5950  /* Heighten priority here */
5951  hAVRT = BumpThreadPriority();
5952 
5953  /* If input only, we start the pins immediately */
5954  if (info.stream->render.pPin == 0)
5955  {
5956  if ((result = StartPins(&info)) != paNoError)
5957  {
5958  PA_DEBUG(("Failed to start device(s)!\n"));
5959  goto error;
5960  }
5961  info.pinsStarted = 1;
5962  }
5963 
5964  /* Handle WaveRT polled mode */
5965  {
5966  const unsigned fs = (unsigned)info.stream->streamRepresentation.streamInfo.sampleRate;
5967  if (info.stream->capture.pPin != 0 && info.stream->capture.pPin->pinKsSubType == SubType_kPolled)
5968  {
5969  timerEventHandles[0] = info.stream->capture.events[0];
5970  timerPeriod = min(timerPeriod, (1000*info.stream->capture.framesPerBuffer)/fs);
5971  }
5972 
5973  if (info.stream->render.pPin != 0 && info.stream->render.pPin->pinKsSubType == SubType_kPolled)
5974  {
5975  timerEventHandles[1] = info.stream->render.events[0];
5976  timerPeriod = min(timerPeriod, (1000*info.stream->render.framesPerBuffer)/fs);
5977  }
5978 
5979  if (timerEventHandles[0] || timerEventHandles[1])
5980  {
5981  LARGE_INTEGER dueTime = {0};
5982 
5983  timerPeriod=max(timerPeriod/5,1);
5984  PA_DEBUG(("Timer event handles=0x%04X,0x%04X period=%u ms", timerEventHandles[0], timerEventHandles[1], timerPeriod));
5985  hTimer = CreateWaitableTimer(0, FALSE, NULL);
5986  if (hTimer == NULL)
5987  {
5988  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
5989  goto error;
5990  }
5991  /* invoke first timeout immediately */
5992  if (!SetWaitableTimer(hTimer, &dueTime, timerPeriod, TimerAPCWaveRTPolledMode, timerEventHandles, FALSE))
5993  {
5994  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
5995  goto error;
5996  }
5997  PA_DEBUG(("Waitable timer started, period = %u ms\n", timerPeriod));
5998  }
5999  }
6000 
6001  /* Mark stream as active */
6002  info.stream->streamActive = 1;
6003  info.stream->threadResult = paNoError;
6004 
6005  /* Up and running... */
6006  SetEvent(info.stream->eventStreamStart[StreamStart_kOk]);
6007 
6008  /* Take timestamp here */
6009  timeStamp[0] = timeStamp[1] = GetCurrentTimeInMillisecs();
6010 
6011  while(!info.stream->streamAbort)
6012  {
6013  unsigned doProcessing = 1;
6014  unsigned wait = WaitForMultipleObjects(noOfHandles, handleArray, FALSE, 0);
6015  unsigned eventSignalled = wait - WAIT_OBJECT_0;
6016  DWORD dwCurrentTime = 0;
6017 
6018  if (wait == WAIT_FAILED)
6019  {
6020  PA_DEBUG(("Wait failed = %ld! \n",wait));
6021  break;
6022  }
6023  if (wait == WAIT_TIMEOUT)
6024  {
6025  wait = WaitForMultipleObjectsEx(noOfHandles, handleArray, FALSE, 50, TRUE);
6026  eventSignalled = wait - WAIT_OBJECT_0;
6027  }
6028  else
6029  {
6030  if (eventSignalled < captureEvents)
6031  {
6032  if (PaUtil_GetRingBufferWriteAvailable(&info.stream->ringBuffer) == 0)
6033  {
6034  PA_HP_TRACE((info.stream->hLog, "!!!!! Input overflow !!!!!"));
6035  info.underover |= paInputOverflow;
6036  }
6037  }
6038  else if (eventSignalled < renderEvents)
6039  {
6040  if (!info.priming && info.renderHead - info.renderTail > 1)
6041  {
6042  PA_HP_TRACE((info.stream->hLog, "!!!!! Output underflow !!!!!"));
6043  info.underover |= paOutputUnderflow;
6044  }
6045  }
6046  }
6047 
6048  /* Get event time */
6049  dwCurrentTime = GetCurrentTimeInMillisecs();
6050 
6051  /* Since we can mix capture/render devices between WaveCyclic, WaveRT polled and WaveRT notification (3x3 combinations),
6052  we can't rely on the timeout of WFMO to check for device timeouts, we need to keep tally. */
6053  if (info.stream->capture.pPin && (dwCurrentTime - timeStamp[0]) >= info.timeout)
6054  {
6055  PA_DEBUG(("Timeout for capture device (%u ms)!", info.timeout, (dwCurrentTime - timeStamp[0])));
6056  result = paTimedOut;
6057  break;
6058  }
6059  if (info.stream->render.pPin && (dwCurrentTime - timeStamp[1]) >= info.timeout)
6060  {
6061  PA_DEBUG(("Timeout for render device (%u ms)!", info.timeout, (dwCurrentTime - timeStamp[1])));
6062  result = paTimedOut;
6063  break;
6064  }
6065 
6066  if (wait == WAIT_IO_COMPLETION)
6067  {
6068  /* Waitable timer has fired! */
6069  PA_HP_TRACE((info.stream->hLog, "WAIT_IO_COMPLETION"));
6070  continue;
6071  }
6072 
6073  if (wait == WAIT_TIMEOUT)
6074  {
6075  continue;
6076  }
6077  else
6078  {
6079  if (eventSignalled < captureEvents)
6080  {
6081  if (info.stream->capture.pPin->fnEventHandler(&info, eventSignalled) == paNoError)
6082  {
6083  timeStamp[0] = dwCurrentTime;
6084 
6085  /* Since we use the ring buffer, we can submit the buffers directly */
6086  if (!info.stream->streamStop)
6087  {
6088  result = info.stream->capture.pPin->fnSubmitHandler(&info, info.captureTail);
6089  if (result != paNoError)
6090  {
6091  PA_HP_TRACE((info.stream->hLog, "Capture submit handler failed with result %d", result));
6092  break;
6093  }
6094  }
6095  ++info.captureTail;
6096  /* If full-duplex, let _only_ render event trigger processing. We still need the stream stop
6097  handling working, so let that be processed anyways... */
6098  if (info.stream->userOutputChannels > 0)
6099  {
6100  doProcessing = 0;
6101  }
6102  }
6103  }
6104  else if (eventSignalled < renderEvents)
6105  {
6106  timeStamp[1] = dwCurrentTime;
6107  eventSignalled -= captureEvents;
6108  info.stream->render.pPin->fnEventHandler(&info, eventSignalled);
6109  }
6110  else
6111  {
6112  assert(info.stream->streamAbort);
6113  PA_HP_TRACE((info.stream->hLog, "Stream abort!"));
6114  continue;
6115  }
6116  }
6117 
6118  /* Handle processing */
6119  if (doProcessing)
6120  {
6121  result = PaDoProcessing(&info);
6122  if (result != paNoError)
6123  {
6124  PA_HP_TRACE((info.stream->hLog, "PaDoProcessing failed!"));
6125  break;
6126  }
6127  }
6128 
6129  if(info.stream->streamStop && info.cbResult != paComplete)
6130  {
6131  PA_HP_TRACE((info.stream->hLog, "Stream stop! pending=%d",info.pending));
6132  info.cbResult = paComplete; /* Stop, but play remaining buffers */
6133  }
6134 
6135  if(info.pending<=0)
6136  {
6137  PA_HP_TRACE((info.stream->hLog, "pending==0 finished..."));
6138  break;
6139  }
6140  if((!info.stream->render.pPin)&&(info.cbResult!=paContinue))
6141  {
6142  PA_HP_TRACE((info.stream->hLog, "record only cbResult=%d...",info.cbResult));
6143  break;
6144  }
6145  }
6146 
6147  PA_DEBUG(("Finished processing loop\n"));
6148 
6149  info.stream->threadResult = result;
6150  goto bailout;
6151 
6152 error:
6153  PA_DEBUG(("Error starting processing thread\n"));
6154  /* Set the "error" event together with result */
6155  info.stream->threadResult = result;
6156  SetEvent(info.stream->eventStreamStart[StreamStart_kFailed]);
6157 
6158 bailout:
6159  if (hTimer)
6160  {
6161  PA_DEBUG(("Waitable timer stopped\n", timerPeriod));
6162  CancelWaitableTimer(hTimer);
6163  CloseHandle(hTimer);
6164  hTimer = 0;
6165  }
6166 
6167  if (info.pinsStarted)
6168  {
6169  StopPins(&info);
6170  }
6171 
6172  /* Lower prio here */
6173  DropThreadPriority(hAVRT);
6174 
6175  if (handleArray != NULL)
6176  {
6177  PaUtil_FreeMemory(handleArray);
6178  }
6179 
6180 #if PA_TRACE_REALTIME_EVENTS
6181  if (info.stream->hLog)
6182  {
6183  PA_DEBUG(("Dumping highspeed trace...\n"));
6184  PaUtil_DumpHighSpeedLog(info.stream->hLog, "hp_trace.log");
6185  PaUtil_DiscardHighSpeedLog(info.stream->hLog);
6186  info.stream->hLog = 0;
6187  }
6188 #endif
6189  info.stream->streamActive = 0;
6190 
6191  if((!info.stream->streamStop)&&(!info.stream->streamAbort))
6192  {
6193  /* Invoke the user stream finished callback */
6194  /* Only do it from here if not being stopped/aborted by user */
6195  if( info.stream->streamRepresentation.streamFinishedCallback != 0 )
6196  info.stream->streamRepresentation.streamFinishedCallback( info.stream->streamRepresentation.userData );
6197  }
6198  info.stream->streamStop = 0;
6199  info.stream->streamAbort = 0;
6200 
6201  PA_LOGL_;
6202  return 0;
6203 }
6204 
6205 
6206 static PaError StartStream( PaStream *s )
6207 {
6208  PaError result = paNoError;
6209  PaWinWdmStream *stream = (PaWinWdmStream*)s;
6210 
6211  PA_LOGE_;
6212 
6213  if (stream->streamThread != NULL)
6214  {
6215  return paStreamIsNotStopped;
6216  }
6217 
6218  stream->streamStop = 0;
6219  stream->streamAbort = 0;
6220 
6221  ResetStreamEvents(stream);
6222 
6223  PaUtil_ResetBufferProcessor( &stream->bufferProcessor );
6224 
6225  stream->oldProcessPriority = GetPriorityClass(GetCurrentProcess());
6226  /* Uncomment the following line to enable dynamic boosting of the process
6227  * priority to real time for best low latency support
6228  * Disabled by default because RT processes can easily block the OS */
6229  /*ret = SetPriorityClass(GetCurrentProcess(),REALTIME_PRIORITY_CLASS);
6230  PA_DEBUG(("Class ret = %d;",ret));*/
6231 
6232  stream->streamThread = CREATE_THREAD_FUNCTION (NULL, 0, ProcessingThread, stream, CREATE_SUSPENDED, NULL);
6233  if(stream->streamThread == NULL)
6234  {
6235  result = paInsufficientMemory;
6236  goto end;
6237  }
6238  ResumeThread(stream->streamThread);
6239 
6240  switch (WaitForMultipleObjects(2, stream->eventStreamStart, FALSE, 5000))
6241  {
6242  case WAIT_OBJECT_0 + StreamStart_kOk:
6243  PA_DEBUG(("Processing thread started!\n"));
6244  result = paNoError;
6245  /* streamActive is set in processing thread */
6246  stream->streamStarted = 1;
6247  break;
6248  case WAIT_OBJECT_0 + StreamStart_kFailed:
6249  PA_DEBUG(("Processing thread start failed! (result=%d)\n", stream->threadResult));
6250  result = stream->threadResult;
6251  /* Wait for the stream to really exit */
6252  WaitForSingleObject(stream->streamThread, 200);
6253  CloseHandle(stream->streamThread);
6254  stream->streamThread = 0;
6255  break;
6256  case WAIT_TIMEOUT:
6257  default:
6258  result = paTimedOut;
6259  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "Failed to start processing thread (timeout)!");
6260  break;
6261  }
6262 
6263 end:
6264  PA_LOGL_;
6265  return result;
6266 }
6267 
6268 
6269 static PaError StopStream( PaStream *s )
6270 {
6271  PaError result = paNoError;
6272  PaWinWdmStream *stream = (PaWinWdmStream*)s;
6273  BOOL doCb = FALSE;
6274 
6275  PA_LOGE_;
6276 
6277  if(stream->streamActive)
6278  {
6279  DWORD dwExitCode;
6280  doCb = TRUE;
6281  stream->streamStop = 1;
6282  if (GetExitCodeThread(stream->streamThread, &dwExitCode) && dwExitCode == STILL_ACTIVE)
6283  {
6284  if (WaitForSingleObject(stream->streamThread, INFINITE) != WAIT_OBJECT_0)
6285  {
6286  PA_DEBUG(("StopStream: stream thread terminated\n"));
6287  TerminateThread(stream->streamThread, -1);
6288  result = paTimedOut;
6289  }
6290  }
6291  else
6292  {
6293  PA_DEBUG(("StopStream: GECT says not active, but streamActive is not false ??"));
6294  result = paUnanticipatedHostError;
6295  PaWinWDM_SetLastErrorInfo(result, "StopStream: GECT says not active, but streamActive = %d", stream->streamActive);
6296  }
6297  }
6298  else
6299  {
6300  if (stream->threadResult != paNoError)
6301  {
6302  PA_DEBUG(("StopStream: Stream not active (%d)\n", stream->threadResult));
6303  result = stream->threadResult;
6304  stream->threadResult = paNoError;
6305  }
6306  }
6307 
6308  if (stream->streamThread != NULL)
6309  {
6310  CloseHandle(stream->streamThread);
6311  stream->streamThread = 0;
6312  }
6313  stream->streamStarted = 0;
6314  stream->streamActive = 0;
6315 
6316  if(doCb)
6317  {
6318  /* Do user callback now after all state has been reset */
6319  /* This means it should be safe for the called function */
6320  /* to invoke e.g. StartStream */
6321  if( stream->streamRepresentation.streamFinishedCallback != 0 )
6322  stream->streamRepresentation.streamFinishedCallback( stream->streamRepresentation.userData );
6323  }
6324 
6325  PA_LOGL_;
6326  return result;
6327 }
6328 
6329 static PaError AbortStream( PaStream *s )
6330 {
6331  PaError result = paNoError;
6332  PaWinWdmStream *stream = (PaWinWdmStream*)s;
6333  int doCb = 0;
6334 
6335  PA_LOGE_;
6336 
6337  if(stream->streamActive)
6338  {
6339  doCb = 1;
6340  stream->streamAbort = 1;
6341  SetEvent(stream->eventAbort); /* Signal immediately */
6342  if (WaitForSingleObject(stream->streamThread, 10000) != WAIT_OBJECT_0)
6343  {
6344  TerminateThread(stream->streamThread, -1);
6345  result = paTimedOut;
6346 
6347  PA_DEBUG(("AbortStream: stream thread terminated\n"));
6348  }
6349  assert(!stream->streamActive);
6350  }
6351  CloseHandle(stream->streamThread);
6352  stream->streamThread = NULL;
6353  stream->streamStarted = 0;
6354 
6355  if(doCb)
6356  {
6357  /* Do user callback now after all state has been reset */
6358  /* This means it should be safe for the called function */
6359  /* to invoke e.g. StartStream */
6360  if( stream->streamRepresentation.streamFinishedCallback != 0 )
6361  stream->streamRepresentation.streamFinishedCallback( stream->streamRepresentation.userData );
6362  }
6363 
6364  stream->streamActive = 0;
6365  stream->streamStarted = 0;
6366 
6367  PA_LOGL_;
6368  return result;
6369 }

6493 
6494 /***************************************************************************************/
6495 /* Event and submit handlers for WaveCyclic */
6496 /***************************************************************************************/
6497 
6498 static PaError PaPinCaptureEventHandler_WaveCyclic(PaProcessThreadInfo* pInfo, unsigned eventIndex)
6499 {
6500  PaError result = paNoError;
6501  ring_buffer_size_t frameCount;
6502  DATAPACKET* packet = pInfo->stream->capture.packets + eventIndex;
6503 
6504  assert( eventIndex < pInfo->stream->capture.noOfPackets );
6505 
6506  if (packet->Header.DataUsed == 0)
6507  {
6508  PA_HP_TRACE((pInfo->stream->hLog, ">>> Capture bogus event (no data): idx=%u", eventIndex));
6509 
6510  /* Bogus event, reset! This is to handle the behavior of this USB mic: http://shop.xtz.se/measurement-system/microphone-to-dirac-live-room-correction-suite
6511  on startup of streaming, where it erroneously sets the event without the corresponding buffer being filled (DataUsed == 0) */
6512  ResetEvent(packet->Signal.hEvent);
6513 
6514  result = -1; /* Only need this to be NOT paNoError */
6515  }
6516  else
6517  {
6518  pInfo->capturePackets[pInfo->captureHead & cPacketsArrayMask].packet = packet;
6519 
6520  frameCount = PaUtil_WriteRingBuffer(&pInfo->stream->ringBuffer, packet->Header.Data, pInfo->stream->capture.framesPerBuffer);
6521 
6522  PA_HP_TRACE((pInfo->stream->hLog, ">>> Capture event: idx=%u (frames=%u)", eventIndex, frameCount));
6523  ++pInfo->captureHead;
6524  }
6525 
6526  --pInfo->pending; /* This needs to be done in either case */
6527  return result;
6528 }
6529 
6530 static PaError PaPinCaptureSubmitHandler_WaveCyclic(PaProcessThreadInfo* pInfo, unsigned eventIndex)
6531 {
6532  PaError result = paNoError;
6533  DATAPACKET* packet = pInfo->capturePackets[pInfo->captureTail & cPacketsArrayMask].packet;
6534  pInfo->capturePackets[pInfo->captureTail & cPacketsArrayMask].packet = 0;
6535  assert(packet != 0);
6536  PA_HP_TRACE((pInfo->stream->hLog, "Capture submit: %u", eventIndex));
6537  packet->Header.DataUsed = 0; /* Reset for reuse */
6538  ResetEvent(packet->Signal.hEvent);
6539  result = PinRead(pInfo->stream->capture.pPin->handle, packet);
6540  ++pInfo->pending;
6541  return result;
6542 }
6543 
6544 static PaError PaPinRenderEventHandler_WaveCyclic(PaProcessThreadInfo* pInfo, unsigned eventIndex)
6545 {
6546  assert( eventIndex < pInfo->stream->render.noOfPackets );
6547 
6548  pInfo->renderPackets[pInfo->renderHead & cPacketsArrayMask].packet = pInfo->stream->render.packets + eventIndex;
6549  PA_HP_TRACE((pInfo->stream->hLog, "<<< Render event : idx=%u head=%u", eventIndex, pInfo->renderHead));
6550  ++pInfo->renderHead;
6551  --pInfo->pending;
6552  return paNoError;
6553 }
6554 
6555 static PaError PaPinRenderSubmitHandler_WaveCyclic(PaProcessThreadInfo* pInfo, unsigned eventIndex)
6556 {
6557  PaError result = paNoError;
6558  DATAPACKET* packet = pInfo->renderPackets[pInfo->renderTail & cPacketsArrayMask].packet;
6559  pInfo->renderPackets[pInfo->renderTail & cPacketsArrayMask].packet = 0;
6560  assert(packet != 0);
6561 
6562  PA_HP_TRACE((pInfo->stream->hLog, "Render submit : %u idx=%u", pInfo->renderTail, (unsigned)(packet - pInfo->stream->render.packets)));
6563  ResetEvent(packet->Signal.hEvent);
6564  result = PinWrite(pInfo->stream->render.pPin->handle, packet);
6565  /* Reset event, just in case we have an analogous situation to capture (see PaPinCaptureSubmitHandler_WaveCyclic) */
6566  ++pInfo->pending;
6567  if (pInfo->priming)
6568  {
6569  --pInfo->priming;
6570  }
6571  return result;
6572 }
6573 
6574 /***************************************************************************************/
6575 /* Event and submit handlers for WaveRT */
6576 /***************************************************************************************/
6577 
6578 static PaError PaPinCaptureEventHandler_WaveRTEvent(PaProcessThreadInfo* pInfo, unsigned eventIndex)
6579 {
6580  unsigned long pos;
6581  unsigned realInBuf;
6582  unsigned frameCount;
6583  PaWinWdmIOInfo* pCapture = &pInfo->stream->capture;
6584  const unsigned halfInputBuffer = pCapture->hostBufferSize >> 1;
6585  PaWinWdmPin* pin = pCapture->pPin;
6586  DATAPACKET* packet = 0;
6587 
6588  /* Get hold of current ADC position */
6589  pin->fnAudioPosition(pin, &pos);
6590  /* Wrap it (robi: why not use hw latency compensation here ?? because pos then gets _way_ off from
6591  where it should be, i.e. at beginning or half buffer position. Why? No idea.) */
6592 
6593  pos %= pCapture->hostBufferSize;
6594  /* Then realInBuf will point to "other" half of double buffer */
6595  realInBuf = pos < halfInputBuffer ? 1U : 0U;
6596 
6597  packet = pInfo->stream->capture.packets + realInBuf;
6598 
6599  /* Call barrier (or dummy) */
6600  pin->fnMemBarrier();
6601 
6602  /* Put it in queue */
6603  frameCount = PaUtil_WriteRingBuffer(&pInfo->stream->ringBuffer, packet->Header.Data, pCapture->framesPerBuffer);
6604 
6605  pInfo->capturePackets[pInfo->captureHead & cPacketsArrayMask].packet = packet;
6606 
6607  PA_HP_TRACE((pInfo->stream->hLog, "Capture event (WaveRT): idx=%u head=%u (pos = %4.1lf%%, frames=%u)", realInBuf, pInfo->captureHead, (pos * 100.0 / pCapture->hostBufferSize), frameCount));
6608 
6609  ++pInfo->captureHead;
6610  --pInfo->pending;
6611 
6612  return paNoError;
6613 }
6614 
6615 static PaError PaPinCaptureEventHandler_WaveRTPolled(PaProcessThreadInfo* pInfo, unsigned eventIndex)
6616 {
6617  unsigned long pos;
6618  unsigned bytesToRead;
6619  PaWinWdmIOInfo* pCapture = &pInfo->stream->capture;
6620  const unsigned halfInputBuffer = pCapture->hostBufferSize>>1;
6621  PaWinWdmPin* pin = pInfo->stream->capture.pPin;
6622 
6623  /* Get hold of current ADC position */
6624  pin->fnAudioPosition(pin, &pos);
6625  /* Wrap it (robi: why not use hw latency compensation here ?? because pos then gets _way_ off from
6626  where it should be, i.e. at beginning or half buffer position. Why? No idea.) */
6627  /* Compensate for HW FIFO to get to last read buffer position */
6628  pos += pin->hwLatency;
6629  pos %= pCapture->hostBufferSize;
6630  /* Need to align position on frame boundary */
6631  pos &= ~(pCapture->bytesPerFrame - 1);
6632 
6633  /* Call barrier (or dummy) */
6634  pin->fnMemBarrier();
6635 
6636  /* Put it in "queue" */
6637  bytesToRead = (pCapture->hostBufferSize + pos - pCapture->lastPosition) % pCapture->hostBufferSize;
6638  if (bytesToRead > 0)
6639  {
6640  unsigned frameCount = PaUtil_WriteRingBuffer(&pInfo->stream->ringBuffer,
6641  pCapture->hostBuffer + pCapture->lastPosition,
6642  bytesToRead / pCapture->bytesPerFrame);
6643 
6644  pCapture->lastPosition = (pCapture->lastPosition + frameCount * pCapture->bytesPerFrame) % pCapture->hostBufferSize;
6645 
6646  PA_HP_TRACE((pInfo->stream->hLog, "Capture event (WaveRTPolled): pos = %4.1lf%%, framesRead=%u", (pos * 100.0 / pCapture->hostBufferSize), frameCount));
6647  ++pInfo->captureHead;
6648  --pInfo->pending;
6649  }
6650  return paNoError;
6651 }

6655  pInfo->capturePackets[pInfo->captureTail & cPacketsArrayMask].packet = 0;

6667 static PaError PaPinRenderEventHandler_WaveRTEvent(PaProcessThreadInfo* pInfo, unsigned eventIndex)
6668 {
6669  unsigned long pos;
6670  unsigned realOutBuf;
6671  PaWinWdmIOInfo* pRender = &pInfo->stream->render;
6672  const unsigned halfOutputBuffer = pRender->hostBufferSize >> 1;
6673  PaWinWdmPin* pin = pInfo->stream->render.pPin;
6674  PaIOPacket* ioPacket = &pInfo->renderPackets[pInfo->renderHead & cPacketsArrayMask];
6675 
6676  /* Get hold of current DAC position */
6677  pin->fnAudioPosition(pin, &pos);
6678  /* Compensate for HW FIFO to get to last read buffer position */
6679  pos += pin->hwLatency;
6680  /* Wrap it */
6681  pos %= pRender->hostBufferSize;
6682  /* And align it, not sure its really needed though */
6683  pos &= ~(pRender->bytesPerFrame - 1);
6684  /* Then realOutBuf will point to "other" half of double buffer */
6685  realOutBuf = pos < halfOutputBuffer ? 1U : 0U;
6686 
6687  if (pInfo->priming)
6688  {
6689  realOutBuf = pInfo->renderHead & 0x1;
6690  }
6691  ioPacket->packet = pInfo->stream->render.packets + realOutBuf;
6692  ioPacket->startByte = realOutBuf * halfOutputBuffer;
6693  ioPacket->lengthBytes = halfOutputBuffer;
6694 
6695  PA_HP_TRACE((pInfo->stream->hLog, "Render event (WaveRT) : idx=%u head=%u (pos = %4.1lf%%)", realOutBuf, pInfo->renderHead, (pos * 100.0 / pRender->hostBufferSize) ));
6696 
6697  ++pInfo->renderHead;
6698  --pInfo->pending;
6699  return paNoError;
6700 }
6701 
6702 static PaError PaPinRenderEventHandler_WaveRTPolled(PaProcessThreadInfo* pInfo, unsigned eventIndex)
6703 {
6704  unsigned long pos;
6705  unsigned realOutBuf;
6706  unsigned bytesToWrite;
6707 
6708  PaWinWdmIOInfo* pRender = &pInfo->stream->render;
6709  const unsigned halfOutputBuffer = pRender->hostBufferSize >> 1;
6710  PaWinWdmPin* pin = pInfo->stream->render.pPin;
6711  PaIOPacket* ioPacket = &pInfo->renderPackets[pInfo->renderHead & cPacketsArrayMask];
6712 
6713  /* Get hold of current DAC position */
6714  pin->fnAudioPosition(pin, &pos);
6715  /* Compensate for HW FIFO to get to last read buffer position */
6716  pos += pin->hwLatency;
6717  /* Wrap it */
6718  pos %= pRender->hostBufferSize;
6719  /* And align it, not sure its really needed though */
6720  pos &= ~(pRender->bytesPerFrame - 1);
6721 
6722  if (pInfo->priming)
6723  {
6724  realOutBuf = pInfo->renderHead & 0x1;
6725  ioPacket->packet = pInfo->stream->render.packets + realOutBuf;
6726  ioPacket->startByte = realOutBuf * halfOutputBuffer;
6727  ioPacket->lengthBytes = halfOutputBuffer;
6728  ++pInfo->renderHead;
6729  --pInfo->pending;
6730  }
6731  else
6732  {
6733  bytesToWrite = (pRender->hostBufferSize + pos - pRender->lastPosition) % pRender->hostBufferSize;
6734  ++pRender->pollCntr;
6735  if (bytesToWrite >= halfOutputBuffer)
6736  {
6737  realOutBuf = (pos < halfOutputBuffer) ? 1U : 0U;
6738  ioPacket->packet = pInfo->stream->render.packets + realOutBuf;
6739  pRender->lastPosition = realOutBuf ? 0U : halfOutputBuffer;
6740  ioPacket->startByte = realOutBuf * halfOutputBuffer;
6741  ioPacket->lengthBytes = halfOutputBuffer;
6742  ++pInfo->renderHead;
6743  --pInfo->pending;
6744  PA_HP_TRACE((pInfo->stream->hLog, "Render event (WaveRTPolled) : idx=%u head=%u (pos = %4.1lf%%, cnt=%u)", realOutBuf, pInfo->renderHead, (pos * 100.0 / pRender->hostBufferSize), pRender->pollCntr));
6745  pRender->pollCntr = 0;
6746  }
6747  }
6748  return paNoError;
6749 }
